<DIV2 TYPE="chapter" N="4">
<HEAD>What is anticrist in special wi&thorn; hise &thorn;re parties.</HEAD>
<HEAD>Capitulum .IIII<SUP>m</SUP>..</HEAD>
<P>But of &thorn;e greet cheef anticrist. &thorn;at passingli &amp; in special maner|bringi&thorn; for&thorn; fals lawes a&yogh;ens Iesu Crist &amp; pretendi&thorn; him silf moost
<PB N="14">|hooli&meper; &thorn;us techi&thorn; &thorn;e Lord God bi &thorn;e prophete Isaie ix<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Longeuus|&amp; venerabilis ipse est caput. propheta docens mendacium. ipse est<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="13b">| cauda'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Isaias ix. 15 'Longaevus &amp; honorabilis ipse est caput,' etc.</NOTE> &Verbar; A man of greet agee | &amp; worschipful holden to &thorn;e|world&meper; he is heed and cheef anticrist/ a prophete or a prechour|techyng lesing&meper; he is &thorn;e taile of &thorn;is anticrist<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'The longe lyvende and the w(o)rschepefull, he is the hed, and|the profete techende lesyng, he is the tail.'  1388, 'An elde man and onourable,|he is the heed, and a profete techynge a leesyng, he is the tail.'</NOTE> &Verbar; Of &thorn;is taile speki&thorn;|seint Petir more pleynli &amp; sei&thorn;. II. Pe. ii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Fictis verbis in auaricia|de vobis negociabuntur'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. 2 Pet. ii. 3.</NOTE> &Verbar; &THORN;at is to seie. &THORN;ise ben goostli|marchauntis &thorn;at schal chaffare wi&thorn; &thorn;e peple&meper; in feyned wordis<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'And thei shulen marchaundise of &yogh;ou in coueitise bi feynyd wordis.'|1388, 'And thei schulen make marchaundie of &yogh;ou in coueytise bi feyned|wordis.'</NOTE>/|&amp; wi&thorn; her sweet likerouse speche&meper; &thorn;ei bigilen &thorn;e hertis of innocentis.|for Iude sei&thorn;. ii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Mirantes personas hominum questus|causa'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Jud. 16 'Mirantes personas questus causa.'</NOTE>/ &THORN;at is to seie. &thorn;ei schal worschip &thorn;e persoones of men&meper;|bicause of wynnyng &Verbar; &THORN;is taile of anticrist schal not preche freeli|Thomas Alquin sei&thorn;. li<SUP>o</SUP>. Vii<SUP>o</SUP>. ca. viii<SUP>o</SUP> but for 'mammona iniquitatis'/|&thorn;at is for coueitise. so ferfor&thorn;e crueli a&yogh;enstonding &thorn;e prechours of|trou&thorn;e. &thorn;at &thorn;ei schul be holden in &thorn;er daies as cursid of &thorn;e peple &Verbar;|And seint Ion euaungelist sei&thorn;. Apoc. xiii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Quod nemo emet neque|vendet nisi habuerit carecterem bestie'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Apoc. xiii. 17 'Et ne quis possit emere aut vendere nisi qui habet|characterem bestiae.'</NOTE> &Verbar; &thorn;er schal no man in<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="14a">| &thorn;at | tyme bie ne selle be he boond be he free. but if he haue &thorn;e|mark of &thorn;e beest. ei&thorn;er in his forhed or in his ri&yogh;t hond or ellis in|noumbre/<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'No man mai bye, or sille, no but thei that han the caracter, (or|lettre) or the name, or the noumbre of his name.'  1388, 'No man may bie,|ethir sille, but thei han the caracter, ether the name of the beest, ether the|noumbre of his name.'</NOTE> &thorn;at is to seie. &thorn;er schal no man preche Goddis word in|&thorn;oo daies nei&thorn;er heere it. but if he haue a special lettir of lisence|&thorn;at is clepid &thorn;e mark of &thorn;is beest anticrist/ or ellis &thorn;at &thorn;ei maynten|bi word or bi dede. or in bo&thorn;e. &thorn;at his lawe &amp; his ordinaunce is|good &amp; trewe/ &amp; wor&thorn;i to be holden of &thorn;e peple &Verbar; But it is ferful|&thorn;at folowi&thorn; aftir.  Apoc. xiiii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Si quis acceperit carecterem|bestie &amp;c.;'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Apoc. xiv. 9.</NOTE> &Verbar; Seynt Ion sei&thorn;. who &thorn;at euer worschipi&thorn; &thorn;is beest
<PB N="15">|anticrist. &amp; taki&thorn; &thorn;is forseid mark&meper; he schal drink a drau&yogh;t of &thorn;e|wyn of Goddis wra&thorn;&thorn;e/ &amp; he schal be turmentid in fire &amp; brymston&meper;|in &thorn;e si&yogh;t of holi aungelis &amp; in &thorn;e si&yogh;t of &thorn;e lombe/ &amp; &thorn;e|smoke of her turmentrie. schal sti&yogh;e vp in to &thorn;e world of worldis&meper;|&thorn;at is wi&thorn;outen ende<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'If ony man shal worschipe the beest, and the image of it, and take|the tokne in his forhed, or in his hand, &amp; &thorn;is shal drinke of the wijn of Goddis|wrath ... and shal be tourmentid with fijr and brunston, in the si&yogh;t of holy|aungelis, and before the si&yogh;t of the lomb.  And the smoke of her tourmentis|shal sti&yogh;e up in to worldlis of worldlis.'</NOTE> &Verbar;</P>
<P>Of &thorn;is anticrist God sei&thorn; to &thorn;e prophete Zachare | xi<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Sume <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="14b">|tibi vasa pastoris stulti'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Zach. xi. 15.</NOTE> &Verbar; &thorn;at is to seie. take &thorn;ou to &thorn;ee. &thorn;e|vessellis of a foltid schepard/ for loo. I schal suffre anticrist to be|rerid vp in lond. &thorn;e which schal not visite hem &thorn;at ben forsaken.|nei&thorn;ir he schal seke hem &thorn;at ben scatrid. nei&thorn;ir he schal hele hem|&thorn;at ben sore<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. '&YOGH;it take to thee vessels of a foltishe sheperd; for loo! I shal reyse|a sheperd in erthe whiche shal not visite forsaken thingus, ... and shal not|heele the broken togydre.'  1388, '&YOGH;it take to thee vessels of a fonned scheepherde;|for lo! I shal reise a scheepherde in erthe,' etc.</NOTE> &Verbar; O. &thorn;ou foltid schepard anticrist.  God sei&thorn; &thorn;ou art|an ydole hauyng a bischopis habit. but nei&thorn;ir vertu ne spirit. lijf|ne dede. &thorn;at longi&thorn; to a bischop &Verbar; for Poul sei&thorn;. Rom. viii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Qui|non habet spiritum Christi nec est eius'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Rom. viii. 9 'Si quis autem spiritum Christi non habet, hic non est|eius.'</NOTE>/  He &thorn;at ha&thorn; not &thorn;e|spirit of Crist&meper; he is not his seruaunt.<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'If ony hath not the spirit of Crist, this is not his.'</NOTE> albeit &thorn;at he haue &thorn;e outward|tookenes/ &amp; &thorn;erfore sei&thorn; seint Ion. Apoc. xvi<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Quintus|angelus effudit phiolam suam super sedem bestie &amp;c.;'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Apoc. xvi. 10.</NOTE>/ &THORN;e fif&thorn;e|aungel pourid his cruet vpon &thorn;e seete of &thorn;e beest&meper; &amp; his rewme|is made derke/ &amp; &thorn;ei eeten her toungis togidir for sorow. &amp; &thorn;ei|blasfemeden God of heuen for her sorowis &amp; her woundis. &amp; &thorn;ei|diden no penaunce of her dedis<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'The fyvethe aungel shedde out his viole on the seete of the beest,|and his kingdom is maad derk, and thei eeten togydere her tunges for sorowe,|and thei blasfemedem God of heven, for sorowis and her woundis; and thei|diden not penaunce of her werkis.'</NOTE>/  &THORN;at is to mene | Archbischopis <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="15a">|&amp; bischopis. ben &thorn;e seet of &thorn;e beest anticrist&meper; for in hem he sitti&thorn;|&amp; regne&thorn; ouer o&thorn;ir peple. in &thorn;e derknes of his heresie &amp; in &thorn;is &thorn;ei|deliten hem. magnifiyng wi&thorn; her tungis her fals ordinaunce&meper; &thorn;e
<PB N="16">|whiche is sorow to men of trewe vndirstonding/ &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ei putten|abak Goddis holi lawe. for prechyng of Cristis gospel&meper; &thorn;e whiche|ben sorowis to hem. gendring synnes in her sowlis. &thorn;at wounden|hem to &thorn;e dee&thorn;/ And &thorn;ei &thorn;us woundid schullen neuer do medeful|penaunce of dedis&meper; for &thorn;e whiche &thorn;ei schal be dampned &Verbar; Lyncoln|sei&thorn;. I quake I drede &amp; vgli I am aferde&meper; but I dare not be stille/|leste perauenture &thorn;at sentence falle on me. &thorn;at &thorn;e prophete sei&thorn;.|Isaie. vi<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Ve mihi quia tacui'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Isaias vi. 5.</NOTE>/ wo to me&meper; for I haue stilled<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Wo to me, for I heeld my pees.'  1388, 'Wo to me, for I was|stille.'</NOTE> &Verbar;|&THORN;e welle &thorn;e bigynnyng &amp; &thorn;e cause of al ruyn &amp; myschef. is &thorn;e|court of Rome<NOTE PLACE="foot">'Sermo Roberti Lincolniensis Episcopi propositus coram Papa &amp; Cardinalibus|in Consilio Lugdunensi' (<I>Fasciculus Rerum expetendarum, etc.</I>, Brown,|1690, vol. ii, p. 252).</NOTE> &Verbar;  Now bi &thorn;e autorite of God. &amp; oone acordaunce|of hise holi seintis&meper; sue&thorn; an open conclucioun. sadli groundid in<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="15b">| trewe bileue/ &thorn;at in &thorn;e | court of Rome&meper; is &thorn;e heed of anticrist/|And in archebischopis &amp; bischopis&meper; is &thorn;e bodi of anticrist &Verbar; But|in &thorn;ise cloutid sectis. as mounkis chanouns. &amp; freris&meper; is &thorn;e venymous|taile of anticrist &Verbar;  &THORN;ise &thorn;re parties ben waried of &thorn;e apostle|seint Iude&meper; seiyng in &thorn;is forme. ca.<SUP>o</SUP> 1<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Ve qui in via Caym|abierunt. &amp; in errore Balaam mercede effuci sunt&meper; &amp; in contradiccione|Chore perierunt'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Jud. i. 11 'Vae illis quia in via,' etc.</NOTE> &thorn;at is to seie. woo to hem &thorn;at walken|in &thorn;e weye of Caym&meper; &thorn;ise ben fals possessioners&meper; And woo to|hem &thorn;at ben schadde out for mede in &thorn;e errour of Balaam&meper; &thorn;ise|ben mi&yogh;ti nedles mendiners &Verbar;  And woo to hem &thorn;at han perischide|in &thorn;e a&yogh;enseiyng of Chore<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Wo to hem that wenten the weye of Caym; and bi errour of|Balaam for meede ben shed out, and perschiden in the a&yogh;en seiynge of|Chore.'</NOTE>&meper; &thorn;ise ben proude sturdi maynteners &Verbar;</P>
<P>How &thorn;is anticrist schal be destroied.  God him silf techi&thorn; bi &thorn;e|prophete Daniel. &amp; sei&thorn;. ca.<SUP>o</SUP> viii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Sine manu conteretur'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Dan. viii. 25.</NOTE> &Verbar; &thorn;at|is to seie. &thorn;is anticrist schal be destried wi&thorn;outen hand&meper;<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Withouten hond he shal be broken togydre.'  1388, 'Withouten|hond he shal be al to-brokun.'</NOTE> &thorn;at is|wi&thorn;outen power of man &Verbar;  For Poul sei&thorn;. II. Thess. ii<SUP>o</SUP>.  'Antichristum|deus interficiet spiritu oris sui &amp; destruet illustracione
<PB N="17">|aduentus sui'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. 2 Thess. ii. 8 'Ille iniquus, quem Dominus Iesus interficiet spiritu|oris sui &amp; destruet illustratione adventus sui eum.'</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;at is to seie. Crist schal slee anticrist&meper; wi&thorn; | &thorn;e <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="16a">|spirit of his mou&thorn;e. &thorn;at is wi&thorn; &thorn;e holi word of his lawe &Verbar;  And &thorn;e|lord schal destrie him wi&thorn; schynnyng of his comyng.<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'And thanne the ilke wickid man schal be schewid, whom the Lord|Jhesu schal sle with the spirit of his mouth, and schal distroye with the|illumynyng (or schynyng), of his coming.'  1388, 'And thanne thilke wickid|man, etc. ... and schal distrie with li&yogh;tnyng of his comyng.'</NOTE>  &thorn;at is wi&thorn;|turnyng of mennes hertis bi his grace to his lawe. a litil aforne|his doome &Verbar;  But God tau&yogh;t more pleynli &thorn;is loore to Ioob&meper; and|seide/ Iob xl. ca<SUP>o</SUP>.. 'Ecce spes eius frustrabitur eum &amp; videntibus|cuntis precipitabitur'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Job xl. 28; A. V. Job xli. 9.</NOTE> &Verbar; Loo sei&thorn; God &thorn;at hope &thorn;at anticrist ha&thorn;|in richessis &amp; in worldli fauour schal bring him to nou&yogh;t/ &amp; alle|men seing&meper; he schal be &thorn;rowen doun heedlingis<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Lo! the hope of hym shal maken hym veyn; and alle men seende|he shal ben kast doun.'  1388, 'Lo! his hope schal disseyve hym; and in the|si&yogh;t of alle men he schal be cast doun.'</NOTE>/ so &thorn;at alle &thorn;e|peple schal take a weiling vpon him wi greet lamentacioun.|wariyng him &amp; dampnyng him. wi&thorn; alle hise fals ordinauncis &Verbar;</P>
