<DIV2 TYPE="chapter" N="5">
<HEAD>What is anticrist in special&meper; wi&thorn; fyue condiciouns &Verbar;</HEAD>
<HEAD>Capitulum .V<SUP>m</SUP>. &Verbar;</HEAD>
<P>But now at &thorn;e last we schullen bring to mynde &amp; to witnesse&meper;|holi Daui&thorn; &thorn;e kyng/ &thorn;at hadde &yogh;ouun to him&meper; &thorn;e ful spirit of|prophecie/ &amp; he seing &thorn;e comyng of anticrist&meper; his lyuyng &amp; his|fal/ marki&thorn; fyue hidouse sau&yogh;tis&meper; &thorn;e whiche he schal haunt a&yogh;en &Verbar;&thorn;e seruauntis of God.  Ps. foure score &amp; ten/ <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="16b"></P>
<P>&thorn;e firste sau&yogh;t of anticrist is constitucioun as &thorn;e prophete sei&thorn; &Verbar;|'Constitue domine legis latorem super eos'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ps. ix. 21 (A. V. Ps. ix. 20).</NOTE> &Verbar; Lord suffre &thorn;ou to|ordeyne a lawemaker vpon &thorn;e peple&meper;<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Sett, Lord a lawe &yogh;ivere upon hem.'  1388, 'Lord, ordeine thou|a lawe makere on hem.'</NOTE> in peyne of her synne. for|&thorn;ei wole not consent to &thorn;e trou&thorn;e &Verbar;  &THORN;at is &thorn;us to mene. Anticrist|vse&thorn; fals lucratif or wynnyng lawis as ben absoluciouns. indulgence.|pardouns. priuelegis. &amp; alle o&thorn;ir heuenli tresour. &thorn;at is brou&yogh;t in|to sale for to spoile &thorn;e peple of her worldli goodis/ &amp; principali|&thorn;ise newe constituciouns.  bi whos streng&thorn;e anticrist enterditi&thorn;|chirchis. soumne&thorn; prechours. suspendi&thorn; resceyuours. &amp; priue&thorn; hem|&thorn;er bennefice. cursi&thorn; heerars. &amp; taki&thorn; awey &thorn;e goodis of hem.
<PB N="18">|&thorn;at for&thorn;eren &thorn;e precheing of a prest&meper; &yogh;he &thorn;ou&yogh; it were an aungel|of heuene. but if &thorn;at prest schewe &thorn;e mark of &thorn;e beest. &thorn;e whiche|is turned in to a newe name. &amp; clepid a special lettir of lisence&meper;|for &thorn;e more blyndyng of &thorn;e lewid peple &Verbar;</P>
<P>&THORN;e secounde sau&yogh;t of anticrist&meper; is tribulacioun as &thorn;e prophet<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="17a">| sei&thorn;.  'Despicis in oportunitatibus in tribulacione'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ps. x. 1.</NOTE> &Verbar; | &thorn;at is to|seie.  Anticrist vexi&thorn; &thorn;e peple ouer mi&yogh;t&meper; in hunting hem on|mawmentrie &amp; doyng of ydolatrie/ but euer anticrist make&thorn; hem|to wene&meper; &thorn;at &thorn;ei gon on pilgrimage/ &amp; &thorn;erfor he is waried of|God. &thorn;at sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e prophete Isaye. v<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Ve qui dicitis bonum|malum uel malum bonum. ponentes tenebras lucem &amp; lucem tenebras|ponentes amarum in dulce &amp; dulce in amarum'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Isaias v. 20 'Vae qui dicitis malum bonum &amp; bonum malum,' etc.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;at is to|seie. woo to &yogh;ou &thorn;at seyn&meper; good is yuel &amp; yuel is good/ putting|li&yogh;t in to derknes&meper; &amp; derknes in to li&yogh;t/ turnyng sweet in to bittir&meper;|&amp; bittir in to sweet<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Wo that seyn euel good, and good euel, puttende derknesses li&yogh;t|and li&yogh;t derknesses; puttende bitter into swete and sweete into bittir.' 1388,|'Wo to &yogh;ou that seien yuel good, and good yuel; and putten derknessis li&yogh;t,|and li&yogh;t derknessis; and putten bittir thing into swete, and swete thing in to|bittir.'</NOTE> &Verbar;  And &thorn;us do&thorn; anticrist whanne he transposi&thorn;|vertues in to vicis&meper; &amp; vicis in to vertues/ as pilgrimage in|to outrage&meper; &amp; outrage in to pilgrimage/  And for &thorn;is weywarde|entent. God dispisi&thorn; anticrist&meper; wi&thorn; alle hise blindfelt peple/ &|wlati&thorn; alle her mysdispendid goodis&meper; in her moost tribulaciouns &Verbar;</P>
<P>&THORN;e &thorn;ridde sau&yogh;t of anticrist&meper; is Inquisiscioun.  as &thorn;e prophet|sei&thorn; 'Secundum multitudinem ire sue non queret'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ps. x. 5 (A. V. x. 4).</NOTE>/ &thorn;at is to seie.<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="17b">| Anticrist enqueri&thorn; | sechi&thorn; &amp; herkne&thorn;. where he mai fynde ony man|or womman. &thorn;at writi&thorn;. redi&thorn;. lerne&thorn;. or studie&thorn; Goddis lawe in|her modir tung&meper; to lede her lijf aftir &thorn;e plesing wille of God/ and|soone he cacche&thorn; hem in hise sensuris&meper; &amp; aftir smyti&thorn; as he mai|moost greuousli hirten hem &Verbar;  But he schal not make &thorn;is inquisisioun&meper;|aftir &thorn;e multitude or greetnes of his wra&thorn;&thorn;e/ for God schal|refreyne &amp; abregge&meper; &thorn;e powere of his malice/ so &thorn;at he schal no|more do&meper; &thorn;an God wole suffre him.  &thorn;at knowi&thorn; &thorn;e mesure of hise|dedis/ to proue hise seruauntis bi &thorn;e furneise of penaunce acceptable&meper;|&amp; anticrist wi&thorn; hise meyne. &thorn;us hardid in malice. inexcusable&Verbar;|</P>
<P>
<PB N="19">&THORN;e four&thorn;e sau&yogh;t of anticrist&meper; is persecucioun as &thorn;e prophet sei&thorn;|'Insidiatur ut rapiat pauperem'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ps. x. 9.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;at is to seie. Anticrist sitti&thorn;|&amp; sotti&thorn; in pees of &thorn;is world&meper; wi&thorn; riche men in her dennes/ but|&thorn;e pore meke symple and loweli&meper; hem he aspise&thorn; &amp; pursue&thorn;/ hem|he ouer-lepi&thorn; &amp; ouer-renne&thorn;.  raveisching hem bo&thorn;e bodili &|goostli/ for God seid vnto Iob. xl<SUP>o</SUP>.| 'Habet fudiciam quod influat <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="18a">|Iordanis in os eius'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Job xl. 18 (A. V. xl. 23).</NOTE>/  Anticrist ha&thorn; a triste &amp; a trowing&meper; &thorn;at|Iordan mai flowe in to his mou&thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'He hath trost, that Jordan flowe in to the mouth of hym.'</NOTE>/ &amp; &thorn;erfor he maki&thorn; his dwelling|place&meper; in &thorn;e herte of &thorn;e see. as God sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e prophete Ezechiel.|xxviii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'In cathedra<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. chathidera.</NOTE> dei sedi in corde maris&meper; cum sis homo &|non deus'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ezech. xxviii. 2.</NOTE>/ Anticrist maki&thorn; his boost &amp; sei&thorn;/ I haue sitten in &thorn;e|chaier of God&meper; in &thorn;e herte of &thorn;e see/ whane &thorn;ou art but a man&meper;|&amp; not God/ but euer in wlank countre. fat &amp; habunding of worldli|goodis&meper; &thorn;ere anticrist wi&thorn; hise clerkis. bilden her nestis/ And if|&thorn;ou loke vttirli aboute &thorn;ee. &thorn;ou schalt fynde hem among woodis|&amp; watris.  as seint Ion sei&thorn;. Apoc. xvi<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Vidi de ore draconis|&amp; de ore bestie. &amp; de ore pseudoprophete spiritus tres immundos|exisse in modum ranarum'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Apoc. xvi. 13, 'exisse' omitted.</NOTE> &Verbar; I saw sei&thorn; seint Ion. out of &thorn;e mou&thorn;e|of &thorn;e dragoun&meper; &thorn;at is &thorn;e heed of anticrist/ &amp; out of &thorn;e mou&thorn;e of|&thorn;e beest&meper; &thorn;at is &thorn;e bodi of anticrist/ &amp; out of &thorn;e mou&thorn;e of &thorn;e|pseudo-prophete or fals precheour&meper; &thorn;at is &thorn;e taile of anticrist/ &thorn;re vnclene|spiritis to haue passid out&meper; in &thorn;e maner of froggis &Verbar;  Froggis|sitting | in hoolis bi &thorn;e watir-brink&meper; purchassen of &thorn;e ground. <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="18b">|abouen hem. &amp; on ei&thorn;er si&yogh;de hem/ But &thorn;at &thorn;at is vndirne&thorn;en hem&meper;|&thorn;ei wole not her &thorn;ankis. nei&thorn;er leesen it ne loosen it &Verbar;  So &thorn;ise &thorn;re|spiritis croking in coueitis. glotenie &amp; leccherie. bitokenen anticrist.|in hise &thorn;re partise/  For &thorn;ei purchassen of lordis&meper; &thorn;at ben|abouen hem/ miche parte of her good&meper; wi&thorn; &thorn;e tung of flatering &|feyned ypocrisie/ And of &thorn;e comunes abouten hem. &thorn;ei whi&yogh;len in|to her handis&meper; miche parte of her catel/ But &thorn;at &thorn;at &thorn;ei han|wonnen. &thorn;ei holden fast&meper; a&yogh;en &thorn;e autorite. of bo&thorn;e Goddis lawes/|&amp; wi&thorn; &thorn;ise richessis &thorn;ei nurischen wilde. sturdi. &amp; laweles hi&yogh;nen.|&thorn;at pursuen hem &thorn;at wollen ou&yogh;t seie a&yogh;ens &thorn;is cursid synne &Verbar;  But|God in &thorn;is persecucioun. &thorn;oru&yogh; his prophete counforti&thorn; hise seruauntis&meper;
<PB N="20">|&amp; sei&thorn; Ps. xlv. 'Deus noster refugium &amp; virtus adiutor|in tribulacionibus que inuenerunt nos nimis propterea non timebimus|dum turbabitur terra&meper; &amp; transferentur montes in cor|maris'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ps. xlv. 2, 3.</NOTE> &Verbar; &THORN;at is to seie.  Oure God is refute &amp; vertu.  oure God|is help in tribulaciouns. &thorn;e whiche ha&thorn; founden vs passingli &Verbar; |<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="19a">| Wherefore we schal not drede.  whilis &thorn;at men lyuyng aftir &thorn;is|world schullen be troublid. &amp; hillis schullen be born ouer in to|&thorn;e hert of &thorn;e see<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Oure God refut, and vertue: helpere in tribulaciouns, that founden|us ful myche.  Therefore wee shul not drede, whil the erthe shal be disturbid;|and hillis shul be born ouer in to the herte of the se.'  1388, 'Oure God, thou|art refuyt, and vertu; helpere in tribulaciouns that han founde us greetly.|Therfore we schullen not drede, while the erthe schal be troblid; and the|hillis schulen be borun ouer in to the herte of the see.'</NOTE> &Verbar; &thorn;at is. trewe men schal not be abaschid&meper; &thorn;ou&yogh;|proud fleischeli men be confedrid to anticrist&meper; &amp; helpe him in his|persecucioun &Verbar;</P>
<P>&THORN;e fif&thorn;e sau&yogh;t of anticrist is execucioun.  as &thorn;e prophet sei&thorn;.|'rapere pauperem dum atrahit eum'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ps, x. 9.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &thorn;at is to seie. whanne|anticrist se&thorn; &thorn;at he availi&thorn; not in &thorn;ise forseid turmentis&meper; &thorn;anne|he executi&thorn; his malice a&yogh;ens Cristis chosen &Verbar;  To &thorn;is acordi&thorn; seint|Ion in his Apoc. xiii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Faciat ut quicunque non adorauerint|ymagynem bestie occidantur'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Apoc. xiii. 15.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &thorn;at is to seie. &thorn;e beest of &thorn;e er&thorn;e&meper;|schal &yogh;yue power to &thorn;e beest of &thorn;e see/ for in &thorn;is tyme of execucioun.|&thorn;e viciouse parte of &thorn;e laite. fro &thorn;e hi&yogh;est vnto &thorn;e lowest. schullen|consent to execute &thorn;e wickidnes of &thorn;is viciouse part of &thorn;e clergie/|&thorn;anne schal &thorn;is prophecie be fulfillid.  Ps. lxxviii.  'Effuderunt|sanguinem eorum tanquam aquam &amp; non erat qui sepeliret posuerunt<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="19b">| morticina | seruorum tuorum escas volatilibus celi&meper; carnes|sanctorum tuorum bestijs terre'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ps. lxxviii. 3, 2 'Effuderunt sanguinem eorum tanquam aquam|in circuitu Ierusalem,' etc.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;ei schal scheed out innocent|blood&meper; &amp; &thorn;er schal no man dore birie &thorn;er bodies/ for &thorn;ei schal cast|&thorn;er fleische to foulis of &thorn;e heire&meper; &amp; her careynes to beestis of|&thorn;e er&thorn;e.<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Thei shadden out the blod of hem, as water in the envyroun of|Jerusalem; and ther was not that shulde birie.  Thei putte the smyten to|deth of thi servauntis, metis to the foulis of hevene; fleish of thi seintis to the|bestis of erthe.'  1388, 'Thei schedden out the blod of hem, as watir in the|cumpas of Jerusalem; and noon was that biriede.  Thei settiden the slayn|bodies of thi servauntis meetis to the volatilis of hevenes; the fleischis of thi|seyntis to the beestes of the erthe.'</NOTE> &thorn;anne sei&thorn; &thorn;e prophete. 'Cadet cum dominatus fuerit
<PB N="21">|pauperum'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ps. x. 10.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &thorn;at is to seie. as seynt Austin declari&thorn;/ whanne|anticrist wene&thorn; &thorn;at he ha&thorn; lordschip&meper; ouere alle &thorn;e seruauntis of|God/ rering vpon hem&meper; diuerse gynnes of turmentrie/ &thorn;anne schal|he falle to open reprofe&meper; for euermore &Verbar;</P>
<P>&THORN;e ful tyme of anticrist duri&thorn;&meper; &thorn;re &yogh;eer &amp; an half/ but &thorn;at|&thorn;e gospel make&thorn; remyssioun&meper; &amp; elles schulde not alle fleische be|saaf&Verbar;  &THORN;is tyme was figurid vnder Helie &thorn;e prophete &amp; kyng Acab|&thorn;at wickid man/ &thorn;ere telli&thorn; &thorn;e stori &thorn;at reyn was stoppid. III. Reg.|xvii<SUP>o</SUP>. &thorn;re &yogh;eere &amp; sixe mone&thorn;es.  &thorn;at no drope fel on &thorn;e erthe/|Seint Iame beri&thorn; witnes of &thorn;is &thorn;ing&meper; in his epistil canonysid/<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Jac. v. 17, 18.</NOTE> &THORN;e|fleeyng of Dauid from kyng Saule&meper; marki&thorn; &thorn;is &thorn;ing.  who so|taki&thorn; hede. I. Reg. xviii<SUP>o</SUP>. &amp; rede | &thorn;at book to &thorn;e last ende/  Also <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="20a">|&thorn;e bisecheing of Ierusalem&meper; make&thorn; knowen &thorn;is tyme as Iosophus|telli&thorn;.  Daniel tau&yogh;t &thorn;is noumbre also&meper; in tyme &amp; tymes &amp; half|a tyme. Dan. vii<SUP>o</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Dan. vii. 25.</NOTE> &amp; &thorn;is is &thorn;re &yogh;eere &amp; an half&meper; as seint Ierom|declari&thorn; in his book of seyntis&Verbar;  &THORN;e mi&yogh;ti Machabeies&meper; vndir &thorn;is|noumbre made clene her temple/ wherfore seint Ion in his Apocalyps|feele si&thorn;is rehersi&thorn; &thorn;is noumbre. whanne he speki&thorn; of anticrist/|And Crist kept &thorn;is noumbre&meper; for tyme of his precheing/ outake|&thorn;at leest. bi vertu of his passioun &Verbar;  Seint Ion Crisostum vpon|Mat. Om. lvii<SUP>o</SUP>. sei&thorn; &thorn;us. 'In tribus annis &amp; sex mensibus. hoc|sacrificium christianorum tollendum<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. tellendum.</NOTE> est ab antichristo fugientibus|christianis per loca deserta/ non erit qui aut in ecclesiam|intret aut oblacionem offerat deo'<NOTE PLACE="foot">S. Ioan. Chrysostomus, <I>Homilia XLIX (Opera,</I> ed. 1547, tom. ii, col.|1086).</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;at