<PB N="22">|lawe. and doing of verry penaunce&meper; as Poul sei&thorn;. Ro. xi<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Cecitas|ex parte contigit in Israel donec plenitudo gencium intraret&meper; &amp; sic|omnis Israel saluus fieret'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Rom. xi. 25, 26.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &thorn;at is to seie. Blyndnes fel partie in|Israel. vntil &thorn;e tyme &thorn;at plente of he&thorn;en men&meper; schulde entre in|to cristendom/ &amp; &thorn;anne in &thorn;e ende of &thorn;e world. &thorn;at is after &thorn;e|distruccioun of anticrist. al Israel schulde be mad saaf<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Blyndnesse hath felde of party in Israel, til the plente of hethen|men entriden, and so all Israel schulde be maad saaf.'</NOTE>/  No man|loke aftir Ennok &amp; Hely in persoone&meper; for &thorn;anne he mai li&yogh;tli be|bigilid/ but in spirit &amp; in vertu&meper; now &thorn;ei ben comen/ to make|mennes hertis redi&meper; aforn Cristis doome/ to whom be glori now &|euere.  Amen &Verbar;</P>
