<DIV2 TYPE="chapter" N="6">
<HEAD>What is &thorn;e chirche oonli proprid to God&meper; wi&thorn; hir names</HEAD><MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="21a">
<P>licknes-|-sis and condiciouns. &Verbar;  Capitulum .VI<SUP>m</SUP>.. &Verbar;</P>
<P>To speke of holi chirche.  firste we taken ground of &thorn;e gospel&meper;|where Crist sei&thorn;. Mat. xvi<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Porte inferi non preualebunt aduersus|eam'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. xvi. 18.</NOTE>/ &yogh;atis of helle schullen not mow haue mi&yogh;t a&yogh;en holi chirche<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. '&YOGH;atis of helle shulen not han mi&yogh;t, (or strengthe) a&yogh;eins it.'</NOTE>/|vpon &thorn;is tixte sei&thorn; Lire &thorn;us 'Ecclesia non consistit in hominibus|ratione potestatis vel dignitatis ecclesiastice uel secularis. quia|multi principes &amp; summi pontifices inventi sunt apostatasse a fide.|propterea quod ecclesia consistit in illis personis in quibus est|noticia &amp; vera confessio fidei &amp; veritatis'/<NOTE PLACE="foot">Nicolai de Lyra, <I>Biblia Sacra cum glossis</I> on St. Matt. xvi. 18.</NOTE>  &THORN;e chirche is not in|men bi weye of powere or dignite spiritual or temperal/ for manye|princis &amp; hi&yogh;e bischopis &amp; o&thorn;ir of lowere degree. state or dignite&meper;|are founden to be apostataas. or haue gon abak from &thorn;e bileue/|wherfore &thorn;e chirch stondi&thorn; in &thorn;oo persoones&meper; in whom is knowyng|&amp; verri confessioun of fei&thorn; &amp; trou&thorn;e &Verbar;  But for &thorn;e more cleere|declaring of &thorn;is mater. and avoiding of obiecciouns &thorn;at mai be putt|for&thorn;e&meper; we schullen vndirstonde &thorn;at &thorn;er ben &thorn;re chirchis/ of &thorn;e<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="21b">| whiche Goddis lawe&meper; often maki&thorn; mencioun/ | and miche &thorn;ei|diuersen iche from o&thorn;ir&meper; to hem &thorn;at taken good hede &Verbar;  But witles|foolis ben marrid here. &thorn;at wil not lerne to knowe iche atwynne/</P>
<P>&THORN;e firste is clepid a litil flok as Crist sei&thorn; in Luc. xii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Nolite
<PB N="23">|timere pusillus grex'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Luc. xii. 32.</NOTE> &Verbar;  Nile &yogh;e drede my litil flok&meper; it plesi&thorn; &yogh;oure|fadir to &yogh;yue &yogh;ou a kyngdom.</P>
<P>And &thorn;is chirche is clepid &thorn;e chosun noumbre of hem &thorn;at schullen|be saued.  as it is writen.  Ecci. iii<SUP>o</SUP>.  'Filii sapientie ecclesia|iustorum &amp; nacio illorum obediencia &amp; dileccio'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ecclesiasticus iii. 1.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;e sones of|wisdam ben &thorn;e chirche of ri&yogh;twise men. &amp; &thorn;e nacioun of hem&meper; is|buxumnesse to God. &amp; loue to her euenecristen<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'The sonns of wisdam the chirche of ri&yogh;twis men, and the nacioun|of hem obeisaunce and loovyng.'  1388, 'The sones of wisdom ben the chirche|of iust men, and the nacioun of hem is obedience and love.'</NOTE> &Verbar;</P>
<P>&THORN;e &thorn;ridde tyme &thorn;is chirche is clepid a clene chaast maiden&meper; as|Poul sei&thorn;.  Ephe. v<SUP>o</SUP>.  'Christus elegit sibi gloriosam ecclesiam|non habentem maculam aut rugam aut aliquid huiusmodi ut sit|sancta &amp; immaculata'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Eph. v. 25, 27, 'Christus dilexit ecclesiam ... ut exhiberet ipse|sibi gloriosam ecclesiam,' etc.</NOTE> &Verbar;  Crist ha&thorn; chosun him a gloriouse chirche.|nei&thorn;ir hauyng spott ne bleyne. or ony suche o&thorn;ir &thorn;ing&meper; but &thorn;at|&thorn;is chirche mai be holi and vndefoulid<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Crist louede the chirche ... that he shulde &yogh;yue the chirche|glorious to himsilf, not havyng wem (or spot) or ryuelyng, or ony such thing,|but that it be hooli and undefoulid.'</NOTE>/ To &thorn;is acordi&thorn; Lincoln|dictio CXXXV. &amp; | sei&thorn;/ 'Ecclesia dei catholica est virgo casta <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="22a">|sponsa christi gloriosa sine macula &amp; ruga' &Verbar;  &thorn;e holi chirche of|God. is a chaast virgyn Cristis gloriouse spouse. wi&thorn;outen spott or|bleyne &Verbar;</P>
<P>&thorn;e four&thorn;e tyme. &thorn;is chirche is clepid Cristis spouse&meper; &amp; of &thorn;is|mariage Poul beri&thorn; witnes &amp; sei&thorn;. II Cor. x<SUP>o</SUP>/ 'Despondi vos vni viro|virginem castam exhibere christo'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. 2 Cor. xi. 2.</NOTE>/ I haue maried &yogh;ou to oo man&meper;|&thorn;is is not to a wowtrere. but to a laweful man Crist Iesu/ &thorn;at I|mai present &yogh;ou to God. a clene chaast maiden&meper; at &thorn;e daie of doom<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Sothly I haue bihi&yogh;t, (or become borwe) for to &yogh;yue &yogh;ou a chast|virgyne to a man Crist.'  1388, 'I have spousid &yogh;ou to oon hosebonde, to &yogh;elde|a chast virgyn to Crist.'</NOTE> &Verbar;|And &thorn;us we seyn in &thorn;e dedicacioun of &thorn;e chirche &Verbar;  'Qua sponso|sponsa iuncta est ecclesia'/ &thorn;is dai holi chirche a gloriouse spouse&meper;|is maried to Crist her souereyn &Verbar;</P>
<P>&THORN;is chirche is lickned to a womman wi&thorn; childe&meper; &amp; &thorn;us sei&thorn; Crist|in &thorn;e gospel of Ion xvi<SUP>o</SUP>. 'mulier cum parit tristiciam habet'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Joh. xvi. 21.</NOTE>/
<PB N="24">|A womman whanne sche traueili&thorn;&meper; sche ha&thorn; peynes<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'A womman whanne sche berith child, hath sorowe.'  1388, 'A|womman whanne sche berith child, hath heuynesse.'</NOTE> &Verbar;  &thorn;is|chirche is lickned to a womman&meper; clad in &thorn;e sunne. as seint Ion|sei&thorn; in his apocalyps xii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'mulier amicta sole'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Apoc. xii. 1.</NOTE>/ I sau&yogh; a woundirful<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="22b">| si&yogh;t&meper; &amp; &thorn;at was a womman cladde in &thorn;e | sunne<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'A womman coverid, or clothid, with the sunne.'</NOTE></P>
<P>&THORN;is chirche is lickned to Petris litile boot. &thorn;e whiche was in|myddis of &thorn;e see as it is writen in &thorn;e gospel. Mat. xiiii<SUP>o</SUP>.  Mark vi<SUP>o</SUP>.|Luk. viii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Nauicula autem in medio mari iactabatur fluctibus'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. xiv. 24, Marc. vi. 47, Luc. viii. 22, 23.</NOTE> &Verbar;|Forso&thorn;e &thorn;e litil boot was cast aboute in middis of &thorn;e see&meper; wi&thorn; &thorn;e|wawis<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Sothely the boot in the mydil see was throwen with wawis.'|1388, 'And the boot in the myddel of the see was schoggid with wawis.'</NOTE>/ &thorn;is boot bo&thorn;e sank &amp; swam&meper; but drowne my&yogh;t it neuere/|so holi chirche suffri&thorn; many periles. &amp; sumtyme bodili dee&thorn;. bi|purswet of enemyes&meper; but it schal neuer be dampned/</P>
<P>&THORN;is chirche is lickned to paradise&meper; &amp; &thorn;us sei&thorn; &thorn;e prophete|Ezechiel xxx<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Cedri non fuerunt altiores eo in paradiso dei'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ezech. xxxi. 8 'Cedri non fuerunt altiores illo in paradiso dei.'</NOTE>/|Cedre-trees weren not hi&yogh;er &thorn;an he&meper; in &thorn;e paradise of God/ vpon|&thorn;is sei&thorn; seint Austin.  de. ci. dei. li<SUP>o</SUP>. xiii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Paradisus est ecclesia.|quattuor flumina quattuor euangelia. ligna fructifera sunt sancti.|fructus opera eorum. lignum vite. sanctus sanctorum christus. lignum|scientie boni et mali proprium voluntatis arbitrium'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Augustinus, <I>De civitate Dei</I>, Lib. XIII. 21 (Migne, tom. 41, col. 395).</NOTE> &Verbar;  Paradis|is holi chirche.  &thorn;e foure floodis ben &thorn;e foure gospeleris/ &amp; &thorn;ise<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="23a">| weren writen of Mathwe. Mark. Luk. &amp; Ioon/ | &thorn;e whiche weren|figurid in licknesse of foure beestis&meper; a man. a lioun. a calf. &amp; an|egle/ for &thorn;ei prechiden Crist. &thorn;e whiche is man. kni&yogh;t. prest. &|God/ &amp; bi &thorn;ise foure we ben tau&yogh;t in stori.  what is don in allegori&meper;|what we schal bileue/ in moral&meper; what we shall do/ in anagogy&meper;|what we schal hope/ &THORN;e trees &thorn;at beren fruyt&meper; ben good hooli lyuars|here in er&thorn;e/ &THORN;e fruytis of &thorn;ise trees&meper; ben &thorn;e werkis of holi seintis.|&THORN;e tree of lijf&meper; is &thorn;e seint passing alle seyntis. oure Lord Iesu Crist &Verbar;|&THORN;e tree of knowyng good &amp; yuel&meper; is &thorn;e free choise of mannes wille &Verbar;|&THORN;is is &thorn;e holi chirche oonli proprid vnto God&meper; &thorn;at seruen him in|vertu ny&yogh;t &amp; dai &Verbar;
<PB N="25"></P>
<P>But how euere we speken in diuerse names. or licknessis of &thorn;is|holi chirche&meper; &thorn;ei techen nou&yogh;t ellis but &thorn;is oo name. &thorn;at is to seie|&thorn;e congregacioun or gedering togidir of fei&thorn;ful soulis/ &thorn;at lastingli|kepen fei&thorn; &amp; trou&thorn;e&meper; in word &amp; in dede to God &amp; to man/ &|reisen her lijf in siker hope of mercy &amp; grace &amp; blisse at her ende/|and ouer-|-coueren or hillen &thorn;is bilding in perfite charite. &thorn;at schal <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="23b">|not faile in wele ne in woo &Verbar;  Of &thorn;is spak seint Poul to &thorn;e|Corinthis&meper; &amp; in hem to alle o&thorn;ir seiyng. Cor. iii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Templum|enim dei sanctum est quod estis vos'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. 1 Cor. iii. 17.</NOTE> &Verbar; &THORN;e temple of God is holi&meper;|&amp; &thorn;at ben &yogh;e/ &amp; bi &thorn;is we vndirstand. &thorn;at &thorn;e soule of a ri&yogh;twise|man. is &thorn;e seet of God &Verbar;  Wel au&yogh;t suche a man to be waker &|wise. &thorn;at ha&thorn; &thorn;e greet God Lord of Israel&meper; dwelling in hise soule.|&amp; so sei&thorn; seint Austin. in li<SUP>o</SUP>. de doctrina christiana/ 'O anima|christiana euigila. &amp; si que in te sit virtus caritatis que omnia|sustinet&meper; domini tui imitari vestigia/  Considera quot milia|martirum tritam tibi fecerunt viam/ transierunt virgines. transierunt|pueri &amp; puelle. &amp; adhuc times/ ducet te qui est via veritas|&amp; vita. via non errans. veritas non fallens. vita non deficiens. via|in exemplo veritas in promisso. &amp; vita in premio'&Verbar;  O. &thorn;ou cristen|soule awake. &amp; if &thorn;er be in &thorn;ee ony vertu of charite &thorn;at susteyne&thorn;|alle &thorn;ingis&meper; folow &thorn;ou &thorn;e steppis of &thorn;is Lord/  take hede how|mani &thorn;ousand of martris. han made a sme&thorn; | pleyne weye to &thorn;ee/ <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="24a">|&thorn;er han passid bifore &thorn;ee virgynes. &thorn;er han passid bifore children|&amp; &yogh;ong damysellis&meper; &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ou dredist/  arise &thorn;ou soule. for he|schal lede &thorn;ee. &thorn;at is weye. trou&thorn;e. &amp; lijf/ weye. not erring/|trou&thorn;e. not bigiling/ &amp; lijf. not failing &Verbar; weye. in ensaumple/|trou&thorn;e in promissioun/ &amp; lijf in mede/  And to &thorn;is entent Crist<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. Cristis.</NOTE>|lickned manis soule&meper; to a womman wi&thorn; childe/  For a womman|whanne sche traueili&thorn;&meper; sche ha&thorn; strong peynes/ but whanne &thorn;er|is a man born in to &thorn;e world&meper; sche ha&thorn; no mynde of hir peyne.|for ioye of &thorn;is childe &Verbar; &THORN;us wandri&thorn; holi chirche in er&thorn;e&meper; in preiers.|fastingis. &amp; in wakingis/ in abstinence.  tribulaciouns. &amp; in|angwische/ in persecutiouns. in miche nede. &amp; in prisouns/ in|boondis. in coolde. &amp; in greet heuynes/ in &thorn;rist. in hounger. &|in blamyngis/ in reprouyngis. in sclaundris. &amp; in pacience/ in|longabiding. in symplenes. and in weeping/ in for&yogh;yuyng. in|soburnes. &amp; in chastite/ in spedines. in largenes. and in charite &Verbar;
