<P>&THORN;e four&thorn;e resoun &amp; &thorn;e laste&meper; is ful cleere seide | &amp; on &thorn;is <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="39a">|manere/ Goddis lawe chargi&thorn; on alwise&meper; to loue &thorn;i nei&yogh;bor as &thorn;i|silf/  But &thorn;is loue is beest made knowen&meper; bi good ensaumple in|worde &amp; dede &Verbar;  In what &thorn;ing mowen &thorn;ise sectis profite&meper; &thorn;at|reuersen here Cristis rule/ &amp; &yogh;yuen yuel ensaumple to her nei&yogh;bore&meper;|in pride &amp; false couetise/ &amp; schewen hem richest &amp; moost worldli&meper;|in mete in cloo&thorn;e in curiouse bilding/ But &thorn;is forebedi&thorn; &thorn;e doctour|Bernard&meper; whom we han often aforn rehersid &Verbar; 'Humiles enim|domus &amp; pauperes aliis refrenant concupiscentiam &amp; mirari debemus|pocius in aspectu celi&meper; quam tecti/ &amp; pocius mirari opera dei|quam hominum' &Verbar;  Forso&thorn;e loweli housis &amp; pore&meper; refreynen &thorn;e|coueitise of o&thorn;ir/ &amp; we owen ra&thorn;ir to mervaile in &thorn;e si&yogh;t of heuene&meper;|&thorn;an in &thorn;e si&yogh;t of bilding of mannes handiwerk/ &amp; miche more|schulde we mervaile&meper; &thorn;e greet werkis of God/ &thorn;an &thorn;e werkis of|deedli men&meper; &thorn;at duren but a while &Verbar;</P>
<P>Alle holi seyntis&meper; acorden in &thorn;is/ &thorn;at oure chirche material&meper;|&thorn;at is ordeyned for parischynes. where &thorn;ei comen togidir/ | schal <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="39b">|be made wi&thorn; vertuouse meenes&meper; &amp; in an honest mesure/  But on|alwise it must be fled&meper; &thorn;at in &thorn;is chirche &thorn;er schewe no pride/|nei&thorn;ir outtrage passingli&meper; ouer &thorn;e boundis of pouert/ nei&thorn;ir in|stoon. tymber or leed&meper; nei&thorn;ir in glasse. lyme or plaistir/ nei&thorn;ir|in belle laump or li&yogh;t&meper; nei&thorn;ir in chalise booke or vestment/ nei&thorn;ir|in stepile seetis or peynting&meper; or o&thorn;ir hournementis &thorn;at longen to|&thorn;is chirche/ &amp; diligentli &thorn;is must be markid&meper; &thorn;at &thorn;ei bowe to|pouerte/ to eschewe veyn glory of &thorn;is world&meper; &amp; glorifie &thorn;e cros|of God/  But &thorn;is word of Cristis cros&meper; is foli to hem &thorn;at schal be|dampned/ &thorn;at tenten to signes as comune hooris&meper; &amp; leesen &thorn;e
<PB N="42">|vertu of her soule &Verbar;  Poul comendi&thorn; &thorn;e coming of Crist&meper; &amp; &thorn;e lowe|meking in his manhed/ ii<SUP>o</SUP> Cor. viii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Scitis enim gratiam domini|nostri Iesu Christi quoniam propter vos egenus factus est cum esset|diues in omnibus vt illius inopia vos diuites essetis'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. 2 Cor. viii. 9 'Scitis enim gratiam domini nostri Iesu Christi|quoniam propter vos egenus factus est, cum esset dives, ut illius inopia vos|divites essetis.'</NOTE> &Verbar;  Forso&thorn;e|&yogh;e owen for to knowe&meper; &thorn;e grace of oure Lord Iesu Crist/ for whanne|he was riche in alle &thorn;ingis&meper; he was made pore in man for &yogh;ou/ |<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="40a">| &thorn;at &yogh;e schulden be riche in goostli &thorn;ing&meper; &thorn;oru&yogh; &thorn;is vertuouse nede|in Crist<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Sothli &yogh;e witen the grace of oure Lorde Jhesu Christ, forwhi he|was made nedy for us, whanne he was ryche, that &yogh;e schulden be maad ryche|by his myseste (or nedynesse).'</NOTE> &Verbar; Crist &thorn;at blame&thorn; alle viciouse meenes&meper; in &thorn;e seruyce|of hise peple/ wil not autorise it to him silf&meper; ne defend it in his|owene hous/ as seint Mathew sei&thorn;. &thorn;e xxiiii<SUP>o</SUP>. Mar. xiii<SUP>o</SUP>. &|Luk. xxi<SUP>o</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">Matt. xxiv. 1, 2; Marc. xiii. 1, 2; Luc. xxi. 5, 6.</NOTE>/ 'Egressus Iesu de templo ibat &amp; accesserunt ad eum|discipuli eius ut ostenderent ei edificaciones templi. ipse autem|respondens dixit eis. videtis hec omnia/ amen dico vobis. non|relinquitur hic lapis super lapidem. qui non destruatur' &Verbar; Mathew|Mark &amp; seint Luk. acorden togidir in &thorn;is oo sentence/ &thorn;at whanne|Iesu went out of &thorn;e temple&meper; &thorn;er nei&yogh;ed to him hise disciplis/ for|to schewe him &thorn;e bildyng &thorn;erof&meper; &amp; &thorn;e curiouse werk in stoones/|wenyng &thorn;us to plese her maistir&meper; in seing of so faire a temple &Verbar;|But Crist &thorn;at had an ynward si&yogh;t&meper; how &thorn;e dwellars &thorn;erynne|brooken his lawe/ went awey wi&thorn; doulful chere&meper; &amp; tau&yogh;t hise|disciplis of &thorn;ingis to come/ hou &thorn;is temple schulde be destried&meper;<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="40b">| &amp; bad hem bi war &thorn;at no man bigile hem/  And soore Crist | wept|vpon &thorn;is citee&meper; for mannes bilding stood ful strong/ but bodi &|soule &thorn;at he made&meper; to be his owene dwelling place/ were fallen|from keping of his lawe&meper; in to &thorn;e sowel of stinking synne/  But|scribis &amp; pharisees weren in cause&meper; of &thorn;is greet mischef. as|Mathew sei&thorn;/  wherefore Crist waried hem as hise greetest|enemyes&meper; &amp; alle her folowars to &thorn;e worldis ende/ Mat. xxiii<SUP>o</SUP>.|'Ve vobis scribe &amp; pharisei qui mundatis quod deforis est&meper; intus|autem estis pleni rapina &amp; immunditia'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. xxiii. 25 'Vae vobis Scribae et Pharisaei hypocritae, quia|mundatis quod deforis est calicis et paropsidis: intus autem pleni estis rapina|et immunditia.'</NOTE> &Verbar;  Crist sei&thorn;. woo to &yogh;ou
<PB N="43">|scribis &amp; pharises&meper; &thorn;at clensen clene. al &thorn;at is outward/ but|certis wi&thorn;ynne &yogh;e ben replete&meper; wi&thorn; miche raveyn &amp; vnclennes<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Woo to &yogh;ou, scribis and Pharisees, ipocritis, that maken clene|that thing of the cuppe and plater, that is without forth; forsothe with ynne|&yogh;e ben ful of raueyne and unclennesse.'  1388, 'Woo to &yogh;ou, scribis and|Farisees, ypocritis, that clensen the cuppe and the plater with outforth; but|with ynne &yogh;e ben ful of raueyne and unclennesse.'</NOTE>/|&yogh;e bilden &thorn;e toumbes of holi prophetis. &amp; wondirfulli honouren her|graues/ but &yogh;e swen &yogh;oure fadris steppis&meper; in purswyng of ri&yogh;twise|blood/ &amp; &thorn;ise sectis don &thorn;e same&meper; but wi&thorn; more malice. in worde|&amp; dede/ O. &yogh;e eddris venymus welpis&meper; hou schullen &yogh;e flee &thorn;e|iugement of helle/ &thorn;us sei&thorn; oure Lord Iesu Crist/ Wherto make|&yogh;e schry-|-nes to seyntis&meper; &amp; &yogh;it &yogh;e drawen. hangen &amp; brennen <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="41a">|hem &thorn;at holden &thorn;e weie of Crist&meper; and wandren aftir hise holi|seyntis/ &amp; &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;is schewe not in &yogh;oure outwarde dede&meper; &yogh;e don &thorn;is|slaw&yogh;tir in worde &amp; wille/ As pharises wi&thorn; bischopis in &thorn;e &thorn;ridde|oure&meper; foriuggid oure Lord wi&thorn; her toungis/ &amp; aftirward kni&yogh;tis|at &thorn;e sixte our&meper; hangid his bodi vpon &thorn;e cros &Verbar; So &thorn;ise sectis goon|biforn&meper; to smyte &thorn;e peple wi&thorn; her tung/ &amp; aftir kny&yogh;tis of Herowdis|hous&meper; ben ful redi to make an ende &Verbar;  But &thorn;e cause of &thorn;is pursute&meper;|ben two viciouse extremytees/  Oone is temperal possessioun&meper; &thorn;at|wrongfulli standi&thorn; in prestis handis/  &thorn;e secounde is synful begry|of mi&yogh;ti men&meper; wi&thorn; hoge bildyng of many waast placis/ and nedis|&thorn;ei must be mendid&meper; for charite of God to saue her soulis &Verbar;  For|&thorn;oo &thorn;at maynten &thorn;ise twoo outstraies&meper; ben ful of many foule disclandris/|bi teching of &thorn;e deuel of helle&meper; leest hise retenwe forsake|him/  For &thorn;anne | we schal fynde pees in er&thorn;e&meper; whanne we kepen <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="41b">|Cristis ordinaunce/ &amp; stynt &thorn;ou not &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ou be sclaundrid&meper; so|if &thorn;ou lyue iust lijf&meper; to mende &thorn;is mys put to &thorn;in hond. &amp; &thorn;enk|on Cristis rewarde.  Mar. viii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Qui perdiderit animam suam|propter me &amp; euangelium&meper; saluam eam faciet'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Marc. viii. 35.</NOTE>/  &thorn;at is to seie.|who &thorn;at ha&thorn; loost his lijf&meper; for me &amp; for &thorn;e gospel/ he schal make|his soule saaf&meper; in to &thorn;e blisse of heuene<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'He that schal leese his soule (that is, his lyf) for me, and the|gospel, schal make it saf.'</NOTE> &Verbar;</P>
