<PB N="48">
<HEAD>Of | discrecioun to knowe &thorn;e good from &thorn;e yuel/</HEAD>
<HEAD>Capitulum IX<SUP>o</SUP>/</HEAD>
<P>Noon may discryue &thorn;ise twoo parties&meper; verrili iche from o&thorn;ir/|wandiryng in &thorn;is secounde chirche&meper; for licknessis &thorn;at &thorn;ei vsen/|and also &thorn;ei han in comune mani heuenli &thorn;ingis &Verbar; For oure Lord|ha&thorn; in his chirche&meper; laburers aboute his vintre/ bo&thorn;e fastars.|preiars&meper; &amp; also wakears &Verbar; Almisdoars ben in &thorn;is chirche&meper; wi&thorn;|prechours. &amp; redars of lessouns/ &amp; singars traueilen here also&meper; wi&thorn;|minastrars of sacramentis/ wi&thorn; studiars in Goddis lawe&meper; &amp; men|&thorn;at maken louedaies &Verbar;  And like seruauntis ha&thorn; &thorn;e fende&meper; in &thorn;e|&thorn;ridde chirche/ but &thorn;ei don her seruyse&meper; in a straunge manere/|Ne&thorn;eles &thorn;ei ben hard to knowe&meper; &thorn;erfore we schal marke hem/ hou|wondirfulli &thorn;ei varien&meper; in &thorn;ise forseide condiciouns/</P>
<P>Certis Fastars in Cristis chirche&meper; abstynen hem from lustis/|for to tempir &thorn;e coragenes&meper; of &thorn;e reble fleishe/ &amp; kepe her bodi|clene chast&meper; &amp; suget to her soule/ for seint Austin in his book&meper;<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="46a">| techi&thorn; &thorn;is loore &Verbar; 'Caro tua viuit de anima tua.  anima | tua de|tuo deo/ vnaquamque eorum secundum vitam suam viuunt/ tunc|enim caro tua recte secundum animam tuam viuit&meper; si anima viuat|secundum deum &Verbar;  Deus est summe bonum. &amp; anima est magnum|bonum viuens inter summum bonum &amp; paruum bonum/ quia caro|paruum bonum est&meper; quia creatura dei est &Verbar;  Anima enim debetrix|non est carni ut secundum carnem viuat. sed e contra mortificanda|est caro. &amp; illi dum consentis mortificas cum ceperit omnino non|delectari mortificasti/ Hec est accio nostra. hec est milicia nostra'/|Hec Augustinus de verbis apostoli sermone iiixx. xviii.<NOTE PLACE="foot">S. Augustinus, <I>Sermo CLVI</I>, cc. vi-ix (Migne, tom. 38. col. 853-855).</NOTE> &THORN;i bodi lyue&thorn;|of &thorn;i soule&meper; &thorn;e soule ha&thorn; hir lyuyng of God/ &thorn;e bodi lyue&thorn; ri&yogh;t lijf|aftir &thorn;e soule&meper; whanne &thorn;e soule lyue&thorn; aftir God/ God is oure hi&yogh;e|souereyn good&meper; &amp; &thorn;e soule a greet good/ &thorn;at lyue&thorn; bitwixe &thorn;e|souereyn good&meper; &amp; &thorn;e bodi a litil good/ for it is Goddis creature&meper;|&thorn;erfore it is clepid a litil good/ Forso&thorn;e &thorn;e soule is not debitrice&meper;|to folowe &thorn;e lijf aftir &thorn;e fleische/ but euene on contrari wise&meper;|&thorn;e fleische mut nede be mortified/ and whanne &thorn;ou leeuest<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="46b">| foule desiris&meper; &thorn;anne is &thorn;i fleische | mortified/ &thorn;is is &thorn;e dede|&thorn;at we schal do&meper; &thorn;is is &thorn;e office of oure kny&yogh;thod/ &thorn;us sei&thorn;|Austin &Verbar;</P>
<P>But fastars in &thorn;e fendis chirche&meper; fasten for vngroundid cause/
<PB N="49">|summe fasten for ypocrisie&meper; &amp; schewen hem ruful to &thorn;e peple/|suche Crist blame&thorn; in his gospel&meper; &amp; clepi&thorn; hem sorowful ypocritis.|Mat. vi<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Cum ieiunatis nolite fieri sicut ypocrite tristes'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. vi. 16.</NOTE>/ for|of &thorn;e veyn preising of mannes mou&thorn;e&meper; &thorn;ei han resceyued al her|mede/ Summe wi&thorn;drawen from her wombe&meper; bo&thorn;e mete &amp; drink to|spare her purse/ and Gregor sei&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;is fasting&meper; is for her sachel|&amp; not for God/ and &thorn;is is a carful fasting&meper; to peyne oure fleische|&amp; leese oure mede/ as &thorn;e wise man sei&thorn;.  Ecc1. vi<SUP>o</SUP>.  'Est &amp; aliud|malum quod vidi sub sole &amp; quidem frequens apud homines vir cui|deus dedit diuicias substantiam et honorem. &amp; nihil deest anime sue|ex omnibus que desiderat . nec tribuet ei potestatem deus ut|comedat ex eo. sed homo extraneus vorabit illud/ sed hoc vanitas|&amp; magna miseria'&Verbar;<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Eccles. vi. 1, 2 'Est et aliud malum quod vidi sub sole . . . vir|cui dedit deus divitias et substantiam et honorem &meper; sed homo extraneus|vorabit illud.  Hoc vanitas et magna miseria est.'</NOTE> &THORN;er is also &thorn;e wise man sei&thorn;&meper; &thorn;at he sau&yogh;|vndir &thorn;e sunne/ ano&thorn;ir yuel &thorn;at | is ful rijf&meper; &amp; comune amonge &thorn;e <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="47a">|peple/ a man &thorn;at God ha&thorn; &yogh;yuen richesse&meper; wi&thorn; catel &amp; miche|worschip/ &amp; no &thorn;ing faili&thorn; to his lijf&meper; of al &thorn;at he desiri&thorn;/ but him|wanti&thorn; grace &amp; powere&meper; to eete or take his parte &thorn;erof/ But a man|&thorn;at is a straungere&meper; schal deuoure it aftir his dai/ but &thorn;is a sorowful|vanite&meper; &amp; a greete wrecchidnes<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'There is and an other euel, that I sa&yogh; under the sunne: and|forsothe ofte anentis men.  A man to whom God &yogh;af richessis, and substaunce,|and worshepe; and no thing lacketh to his soule of alle thingis that he|desireth; and God &yogh;yueth not power to hym, that he ete of it, but a straunge|man shal deuouren it.  This is vanyte, and gret wrecchidnesse.'  1388, 'Also|another yuel is, which Y si&yogh; undur the sunne; and certis it is oft usid anentis|men.  A man is, to whom God &yogh;af richessis and catel, and onour; and no|thing faileth to his soule of alle thingis which he desirith; and God &yogh;yueth|not power to him, that he ete therof, but a straunge man shal deuoure it.|This is vanyte, and a greet wretchidnesse.'</NOTE> &Verbar; Summe fasten for a medicyn&meper;|for to gete hem bodili heele/ nei&thorn;ir for God ne for &thorn;e soule&meper; but|for to clense her beaute/ seint Ierom blame&thorn; &thorn;is fasting&meper; &amp; &thorn;at on|a ful blessid maner &Verbar;  'Tunc preclara est apud deum abstinentia|corporis&meper; cum animus intus ieiunat a viciis/ Quid prodest corpus|tenuare inedia&meper; cum animus intus tumescit superbia/  Hec|Ieromus super Amos &Verbar;  &THORN;at is to seie.  &thorn;anne abstinence of|bodi is clere to God&meper; whanne &thorn;e mynde fasti&thorn; from vicis/ what|profite&thorn; it to tere &thorn;e bodi wi&thorn; hounger&meper; whanne mynde wi&thorn;ynne|swelli&thorn; wi&thorn; pride &Verbar; what fasting is &thorn;is to wi&thorn;drawe lijflod
<PB N="50">|from &thorn;e beli&meper; &amp; to be wood in envie or foule hastite? God sei&thorn; bi<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="47b">| &thorn;e prophete Isaie. lviii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Ecce ad lites | &amp; contenciones ieiunatis|etcetera'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Isaias lviii. 4.</NOTE> idem Zaca. viii<SUP>o</SUP>.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Zech. vii. 5, 6.</NOTE> 'Loo whanne &yogh;e fasten &yogh;e maken strijf&meper;|&amp; debatis among &yogh;oure silf'<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Lo! to ples and to striues &yogh;ee fasten.'  1388, 'Lo! &yogh;e fasten to|chidyngis and stryuyngis.'</NOTE>/ &thorn;is is not &thorn;e fasting &thorn;at I cheese&meper;|sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord God/ And si&thorn;en &thorn;e fende nei&thorn;ir eeti&thorn; ne drinki&thorn;&meper;|nei&thorn;ir is wlappid in precious clo&thorn;is/ &yogh;it he schal be euir in peyne&meper;|for him lacki&thorn; charite &Verbar;  &thorn;anne is &thorn;is an evidence&meper; &thorn;at alle suche|recheles fastars/ ben membris in &thorn;e fendis chirche&meper; in folowyng|her fadir &Verbar;</P>
<P>Preiers &thorn;at ben in Cristis chirche&meper; priien wi&thorn; deuocioun/ wi&thorn;|al &thorn;e streng&thorn;e of her herte&meper; &amp; her mou&thorn;e acording/ knocking wi&thorn;|a perfite dede&meper; aftir helpe of God/ of mercy &amp; for&yogh;yuenes&meper; of tymes|mys dispendid/ &amp; aftir grace &amp; gouerneaunce&meper; for tyme &thorn;at is|present/ and for good contynuaunce&meper; for tyme &thorn;at is to come/|Frecheli bringyng to her mynde&meper; &thorn;e kyndenes of God/ hou he ha&thorn;|rulid hem in &thorn;is lijf&meper; &amp; kept hem fro mischef/ as &thorn;ou&yogh; he had noo|moo but oon&meper; so he saue&thorn; alle &thorn;at loue&thorn; him/ &thorn;anne &thorn;ei &thorn;enken on|foule synnes&meper; &amp; feele &thorn;at &thorn;ei haue don/ bo&thorn;e witingli &amp; wilfulli |<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="48a">| a&yogh;ens Goddis wille/ &THORN;ei han ben recheles in his seruice&meper; &amp; &thorn;at hem|rwi&thorn; soore/ and whanne &thorn;ei &thorn;enken on &thorn;is world&meper; how it passi&thorn;|sodenli &amp; of &thorn;e turmentrie in helle&meper; &thorn;at dampned soulis schullen|suffre/ &amp; on &thorn;e blisse &thorn;at God ha&thorn; ordeyned&meper; for hise trewe|seruauntis &Verbar; Anoon &thorn;ei finden a waschinge welle&meper; &thorn;at springi&thorn; fro &thorn;e|herte/ &amp; renne&thorn; for&thorn;e from her i&yogh;en&meper; bi manye warme streemes &Verbar;|as Gregor sei&thorn;. 'Diuisiones aquarum ducimus cum pro singulis|peccatis lacrimas fundimus' &Verbar; &thorn;anne we fynden rendels of watris&meper;|whanne we wepen for al oure synnes/ to wasche clene bo&thorn;e bodi|&amp; soule&meper; &amp; clense hem of corrupcioun &Verbar;</P>
<P>But preiars in &thorn;e fendis chirche&meper; maken miche noise/ mumling|wi&thorn; her lippis&meper; &thorn;ei reche neuir what/ so &thorn;at men preise fast.  her|feyned occupacioun/ as Crist sei&thorn; in his gospel.  Mat. xv<SUP>o</SUP> &Verbar;|'Populus hic labijs me honorat&meper; cor autem eorum longe est a me'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. xv. 8.</NOTE>&Verbar;|&THORN;is peple worschipi&thorn; me wi&thorn; her lippis&meper; but her herte is feer fro<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="48b">| me<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'This peple honoureth me with lippis, forsothe her herte is fer fro|me.'</NOTE>/ Lord! whanne &thorn;i body is in &thorn;e chirche | and &thorn;i herte in &thorn;e
<PB N="51">|world/ or cumbrid wi&thorn; vnclene &thorn;ou&yogh;tis&meper; &amp; wi&thorn; veyn fantasies/ &amp; &thorn;i|tounge in minstralsie&meper; or on lewid iangling/ &amp; &thorn;i wittis oueresett&meper;|wi&thorn; seculere nedis/ art &thorn;ou not &thorn;anne wrechidli diuidid in &thorn;i silf<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. in &thorn;i &thorn;i silf.</NOTE>?|Seint Iame sei&thorn;. i<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Non estimet homo ille quod accipiat aliquid|a domino'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Jac i. 7.</NOTE>/ suppose not &thorn;is veyn man&meper; &thorn;at he mai take ony &thorn;ing|of &thorn;e Lord<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Therfore gesse not the ilke man, that he shal take ony thing of|the Lord.'</NOTE>/ he mai in nowise be herde in preiour&meper; &thorn;at suffre&thorn; his|herte to sleepe in synne &Verbar; And efte God sei&thorn; bi Isaie&meper; in general|wordis to wickid lyuars. i<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Cum multiplicaueritis orationes uestras.|ego non exaudiam. quia manus uestre plene sanguinum sunt'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Isaias i. 15 'Cum multiplicaveritis orationem, non exaudiam: manus|enim vestrae sanguine plenae sunt.'</NOTE> &Verbar;|whanne &yogh;e han multiplied &yogh;oure preiours&meper; I schal not heere &yogh;ou|graciouseli/ &amp; &thorn;e cause whi is &thorn;is&meper; for &yogh;oure handis ben ful of|blood<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Whan zee shul multeplien orisoun, I shal not heren; forsothe|&yogh;oure hondis ben ful of blod.'  1388, 'Whanne &yogh;e multiplien preyer, Y schal|not here; for whi &yogh;oure hondis ben ful of blood.'</NOTE>/ &thorn;at is. &yogh;oure werkis ben ful of synne&meper; &thorn;at parten &yogh;ou &amp; me|atwynne/ &THORN;us sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord God &Verbar;  But wite &yogh;e wel &yogh;e viciouse|preestis&meper; &thorn;at gon from Crist in viciouse lyuyng/ and wil not swe|hise holi steppis&meper; but | terren him from dai to dai/ &thorn;erfore &yogh;oure <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="49a">|preiours ben dispisid&meper; as Crist sei&thorn; &thorn;at mai not lie.  Mat. xxiii<SUP>o</SUP>.|'ve vobis scribe &amp; pharisei ypocrite qui comeditis domos viduarum|orationes longas orantes. propter hoc accipietis iudicium amplius'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. xxiii. 14.</NOTE> &Verbar;|Woo to &yogh;ou scribis &amp; pharisees ypocritis/ &thorn;at eeten &thorn;e housis of|widowis&meper; bi &yogh;oure long preiers/ for &thorn;is &thorn;ing &yogh;e schal take&meper; &thorn;e|largear iugement<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Woo to &yogh;ou, scribis and Pharisees, ypocritis, that eten the housis|of widues, in longe preier preyinge: for this thing &yogh;e schulen take the more|dom.'  1388, 'Wo to &yogh;ou, scribis and Farisees, ipocritis, that eten the housis|of widowis, and preien bi longe prier; for this thing &yogh;e schulen take more|doom.'</NOTE> &Verbar;  vpon &thorn;is sei&thorn; Crisostom. om. xliiii. 'Inposturas|ypocritarum mulieres non possunt facile cognoscere &amp;c'<NOTE PLACE="foot">S. Ioan. Chrysostomus, <I>Homilia XLIV (Opera</I>, ed. 1547, tom. ii, col.|1052).</NOTE>/|&THORN;e slei&yogh;tis or &thorn;e whilis of ypocritis&meper; wommen mai not li&yogh;tli knowe/|&amp; bicause of her religioun&meper; &thorn;ei wile soone bowe to hem/ for &thorn;at
