<PB N="67">But pees-makars in &thorn;e fendis chirche&meper; confidren hem togidir in|a fals pees/ aftir &thorn;e maner of &thorn;is world&meper; &thorn;at Cristis gospel|dampne&thorn;/ Mat. x<SUP>o</SUP>. &amp; Luk. xii<SUP>o</SUP>.  'Non veni pacem mittere&meper; sed|gladium'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. x. 34; Luc. xii. 51.</NOTE> &Verbar;  I haue not comen sei&thorn; Crist&meper; to maynten viciouse|pees/ but to sende a scharpe sweride<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'I cam not to sende pees in to erthe, but swerd.'</NOTE>&meper; to smyte synne from|mannes soule/ &amp; &thorn;is &thorn;ise synful wrechid foolis&meper; &thorn;rowen vndir foot/|Fei&thorn;. trou&thorn;e. &amp; ri&yogh;twisenesse&meper; &thorn;ei counten at no prijs/ for &thorn;ei|ouereleden &thorn;e countre&meper; aftir her owene lust/ &thorn;erfore &thorn;e prophete|Daui&thorn;&meper; sorowi&thorn; on &thorn;is mischef/ Ps. lxxii/ 'Zelaui super iniquos.|pacem peccatorum videns'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ps. lxxii. 3.</NOTE>/ I haue sorowid on wickid | men&meper; seyng <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="64b">|&thorn;e pees of synnars<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'For I enuyde up on wicke men; seande the pes of synners.'|1388, 'For I louede feruentli on wickid men; seynge the pees of synneris.'</NOTE> &Verbar;</P>
<P>But prestis &amp; kny&yogh;tis&meper; of &thorn;is synne ben moost to blame/ Prestis|&thorn;at schulden be goostli lechis&meper; and recounseile &thorn;e peple/ bi good|counseile to her God&meper; &amp; heele hem wi&thorn; his lawe/ what wi&thorn; pride &|coueitise&meper; &amp; many fleischeli lustis/ &thorn;ise prestis ben so blyndid&meper;|&thorn;at &thorn;ei knowe no wisdam/ for Iob sei&thorn;.  xxviii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'vbi invenitur|sapientia&meper; non enim in terra suauiter viuencium'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Job xxviii. 12, 13 'Sapientia vero ubi invenitur? ... nec invenitus|in terra suaviter viventium.'</NOTE>/ Iob axi&thorn; &thorn;is|questioun&meper; where wisdam mai be founden/ anoon he answeri&thorn; wi&thorn;|&thorn;e spirit of God&meper; not in &thorn;e lond of lusti lyuars<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Wisdam forsothe, wher is it founde? ... ne it is founde in the|lond of sweteli lyuende men.'</NOTE>/ And vpon &thorn;is|sei&thorn; Gregor in hise morals&meper; &thorn;ise wordis of greet sorow. to hem &thorn;at|ben gilti/ 'Quisquis presentis vite voluptatibus pascitur procul|dubio eterne sapientie intellectu separatur'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Gregorius Magnus, <I>Moralium</I> Lib. XVIII, cap. xli. 66 (Migne, tom. 76,|col. 75).</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;at is to seie. who|&thorn;at is fedde&meper; wi&thorn; lustis of &thorn;is present lijf/ wi&thorn;outen ony doute&meper;|&thorn;at man is departid/ fro &thorn;e vndirstanding&meper; of euerlasting wisdam &Verbar;|And si&thorn;en &thorn;ise prestis&meper; ben moost &yogh;ouun/ to &thorn;ise fleischeli lustis&meper;|&thorn;ei failen | goostli si&yogh;t/ and wisdam to ransake&meper; ony goostli <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="65a">|sijknes/ or to serche al aboute&meper; &thorn;e perel of a wounde/ &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ei ben|presumptuouse&meper; to profre fals medicyn/ &amp; vndirtake greet curis&meper;
<PB N="68">|for to make hem hool/ But &thorn;ei hirten myche sorer&meper; &thorn;an &thorn;ei were|aforn/ as &thorn;e Lord mone&thorn; him&meper; bi &thorn;e prophet Ieremye. Iere. viii<SUP>o</SUP>.|'Sanabant contricionem populi mei ad ignominiam dicentes.  Pax.|pax. cum non esset pax/ Confusi sunt qui abhominacionem fecerunt/|Quinimo confusione<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. confuc&omacr;e.</NOTE> non sunt confusi&meper; &amp; erubescere nescierunt'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Jer. viii. 11, 12 'Sanabant contritionem filiae populi,' etc.</NOTE> &Verbar;|&THORN;ise prestis<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. perstis.</NOTE> heliden &thorn;e contricioun of my peple&meper; wi&thorn; schenschip|or wi&thorn; schame/ &thorn;at is wi&thorn; foule symonye&meper; as we rehersid aforn/|and &thorn;ei seyn pees pes&meper; whanne &thorn;er was no pees/ &thorn;ei ben wor&thorn;i to|be schent&meper; &thorn;at han done abhominacioun/ miche ra&thorn;er in &thorn;is confucioun&meper;|&thorn;ei be not confoundid/ for &thorn;ei can not be aschamed&meper; of|her owene vilenye<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. '(Thei) heleden the tobrosing of the do&yogh;ter of my puple to|shenshipe, seiende, Pes, pes, whan ther was not pes.  Confoundid thei ben,|for abhomynacioun thei diden; but myche more by confusioun thei ben not|confoundid, and shamen thei kouthen not.'  1388, 'Thei heeliden the sorowe|of the dou&yogh;tir of my puple to schenschipe, seiynge, Pees, pees, whanne no pees|was.  Thei ben schent, for thei diden abhomynacioun; &yogh;he, rather thei weren|not schent bi schenschipe, and kouden not be aschamed.'</NOTE>/ &THORN;us sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord God/ and efte he sei&thorn; ca<SUP>o</SUP>..|xxiii<SUP>o</SUP>.  'A prophetis enim Ierusalem egressa est pollucio super |<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="65b">| omnem terram. hec dicit dominus. Nolite audire verba prophetarum|qui prophetant vobis &amp; decipiunt vos/ visionem cordis sui locuntur&meper;|non de ore domini/ Dicunt hijs qui blasfemant me. locutus est|dominus pax erit vob