<PB N="69">|mali'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Gregorius Magnus, <I>Homiliae in Evangelia</I>, Lib. II, Hom. xxxix. 2 (Migne,|tom. 75, col. 1295).</NOTE>/ yuel prestis ben cause of ruyn or mischef of &thorn;e peple/ and|no wondir. for whanne &thorn;at li&yogh;t is quenchid . &thorn;at schulde schyne|in | prestis/ &thorn;anne is &thorn;er miche stink&meper; wi&thorn; wickid sauour/ &amp; <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="66a">|blyndnes &thorn;at combri&thorn;&meper; &thorn;e leder &amp; &thorn;e folowar/ in to &thorn;e derckness|of helle&meper; &thorn;e gospel beri&thorn; witnes/ Mat. xv<SUP>o</SUP>. Luk. vi<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Cecus|autem si ceco ducatum prestet&meper; nonne ambo in fouiam cadunt'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. xv. 14 'Caecus autem si caeco ducatum praestet, ambo in|foveam cadunt.'  Luke vi. 39 'Numquid potest caecus caecum ducere, nonne|ambo in foveam cadunt?'</NOTE>&Verbar;|Whanne &thorn;e blynde ledi&thorn; &thorn;e blynde. falle &thorn;ei not &thorn;anne bo&thorn;e in to|&thorn;e lake?<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. '&YOGH;if a blynd man &yogh;eue ledynge to a blynd man, bothe fallen doun|in to the diche.'</NOTE> &yogh;his pleynli &Verbar; &THORN;e former blynde is &thorn;e preest/ &thorn;at wanti&thorn;|vndirstonding/ for &thorn;ou&yogh; he haue lettrure&meper; &amp; faile in good lyuyng/|&thorn;anne he is a blynde prest&meper; of whom Crist speki&thorn;/ as &thorn;e comune|gloose sei&thorn;.  'Frustra iactat legis noticiam&meper; qui operibus destruit|doctrinam'/ Aboute nou&yogh;t he boosti&thorn;&meper; &thorn;e knowing of Goddis lawe/|&thorn;at distrie&thorn; &thorn;e loore&meper; wi&thorn; his wickid werkis/ &THORN;e to&thorn;ir blynde is|man &amp; womman&meper; &thorn;at tristen in suche prestis&meper; to lede hem in &thorn;e|weie of lijf&meper; &amp; bringe hem to saluacioun &Verbar; But Crist ha&thorn; iuggid|&thorn;ise bo&thorn;e parties&meper; to falle in to &thorn;e doungun/ Of suche prestis|come&thorn; debate&meper; in al &thorn;is brood world/ &thorn;at distur-|-bli&thorn; verry pees&meper; <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="66b">|&amp; crie&thorn; open veniaunce/ And &thorn;ise prechours ben no prechours&meper;|but oonli in name/ as a luschborue is clepid a peny&meper; &thorn;at is ri&yogh;t|nou&yogh;t wor&thorn;e &Verbar;</P>
<P>Kny&yogh;tis also ben to blame&meper; &thorn;at mysvsen her powere/ and wole|not reede in Goddis lawe&meper; nei&thorn;ir lerne her office/ &amp; perfore &thorn;e wise|man&meper; blame&thorn; hem &amp; sei&thorn;/ Sap. vi<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Audite reges &amp; intelligite|&amp; sequentia. quoniam data est a domino potestas &amp; virtus ab|altissimo qui interrogabit opera uestra &amp; cogitaciones scrutabitur/|Quoniam cum essetis ministri regni illius. non recte iudicastis neque|custodistis legem iusticie neque secundum dei voluntatem ambulastis'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Sap. vi. 2, 4, 5 'Audite ergo reges ... quoniam data est a domino|potestas vobis,' etc.</NOTE>/|Heere &yogh;e kyngis&meper; &amp; vndirstonde &yogh;e kny&yogh;tis/ for power is|oonli of &thorn;e Lord&meper; &amp; streng&thorn;e come&thorn; of him &thorn;at is hi&yogh;est/ &thorn;at schal|aske reckenyng&meper; of alle &yogh;oure werkis/ &amp; schal serche fulli&meper; &thorn;e|inward of &yogh;oure &thorn;ou&yogh;tis/ For whanne &thorn;at &yogh;e were mynystris&meper; of
<PB N="70">|Goddis rewme/ nei&thorn;ir &yogh;e demed ri&yogh;twiseli&meper; nei&thorn;ir &yogh;e kept his lawe/<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="67a">| nei&thorn;ir &yogh;e walkid in &thorn;e weye&meper; aftir Goddis wille<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Hereth thanne, &yogh;ee kingis, and undirstondith; for ther is &yogh;ouen|of the Lord power to &yogh;ou, and vertue of the hei&yogh;este, that shal aske &yogh;oure|werkis, and tho&yogh;tis serchen.  For whan &yogh;ee weren mynestres of his reume, not|ri&yogh;tli &yogh;ee demeden, ne kepten the lawe of ri&yogh;twisenesse, ne aftir the will of|God &yogh;ee wenten.'  1388, 'Therfor, &yogh;e kingis, here, and understonde; for whi|power is &yogh;ouun of the Lord to &yogh;ou, and vertu is &yogh;ouun of the hi&yogh;este, ... and|schal serche thou&yogh;tis.  For whanne &yogh;e weren mynystris of his rewme, &yogh;e|demeden not ri&yogh;tfuli, nether &yogh;e kepten the lawe of ri&yogh;tfulnesse nether &yogh;e &yogh;eden|bi the wille of God.'</NOTE>/ but &yogh;e | straied|al awey&meper; as if it were wilde syouns/ In often takyng of miche|mete&meper; &thorn;at steri&thorn; &yogh;ou to miche drinking &Verbar; &THORN;anne &yogh;e liggen longe in|couchis&meper; &thorn;at drawi&thorn; &yogh;ou to leccherie/ as sumtyme to spousebreche&meper;|&amp; o&thorn;ir foule vnclennes/ &amp; of &thorn;is come&thorn; stryuyng; &amp; fi&yogh;tynge euer|anoon/ &thorn;at bringi&thorn; &yogh;ou to enemyte&meper; &amp; hate of iche o&thorn;ir/ How|schulde &yogh;e kny&yogh;tis maynten pees&meper; whanne &yogh;e forsake it in &yogh;oure silf?|for wi&thorn; &yogh;oure greuouse tirauntrie&meper; oppressioun &amp; extorcioun/ &yogh;oure|awe is lawe. who dar seie naye&meper; but as &yogh;e wole &yogh;oure silf/ But wite|&yogh;e wel &thorn;is is &thorn;e vois&meper; of hem &thorn;at schal be dampned/ as &thorn;e wiseman|sei&thorn;. Sap. ii<SUP>o</SUP>./ 'Sit fortitudo nostra lex iusticie'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Sap. ii. 11.</NOTE> &Verbar; Oure streng&thorn;e|or oure powere&meper; be it to us &thorn;e lawe of ri&yogh;twisenesse<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Be forsothe oure strengthe the lawe of unri&yogh;twisenesse.'  1388,|'But oure strengthe be the lawe of ri&yogh;tfulnesse.'</NOTE>/ Heere &yogh;e &thorn;erfore&meper;|hou dredfulli it folowi&thorn;/ of &thorn;e sentence seide aforn&meper; if &thorn;at &yogh;e|wole amende &yogh;ou/ Sap. vi<SUP>o</SUP>./ 'Horrende &amp; cito apparebit vobis quoniam|iudicium durissimum in hijs qui presunt fiet/ exiguo conceditur<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="67b">| misericordia potentes potenter tormenta pacientur/ | Non enim|personam subtrahet cuiusquam dominus qui est omni dominator. nec|verebitur magnitudinem cuiusquam. quoniam pusillum &amp; magnum|ipse fecit.&amp; equaliter cura est illi de omnibus forcioribus autem forcior|instat cruciacio'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Sap. vi. 6-9 'Horrende et cito apparebit vobis quoniam iudicium|durissimum his qui praesunt fiet.  Exiguo enim conceditur misericordia;|potentes autem potenter ... Non enim subtrahet personam cuiusquam|Deus, nec verebitur ... cruciatio.'</NOTE> &Verbar;  Ferfulli &amp; soone&meper; it schal schewe to &yogh;ou/ &thorn;at|moost hardest iugement&meper; schal be to hem &thorn;at lorden/ or &thorn;at holden|lordschip&meper; ouer her pore bri&thorn;eren/ mercy is grauntid&meper; to hem &thorn;at|ben lowe in herte/ my&yogh;ti men my&yogh;tili&meper; schullen suffre turmentrie/|forso&thorn;e &thorn;e Lord schal not wi&thorn;drawe&meper; &thorn;e persoone of ony man/
<PB N="71">|nei&thorn;ir he schal be aschamed&meper; of ony mannes greetnes/ for he ha&thorn;|made bo&thorn;e smale &amp; greet&meper; &amp; chargi&thorn; nei&thorn;ir oon ne o&thorn;ir/ forso&thorn;e|to &thorn;e strenger&meper; is ordeyned strenger cruciacioun &amp; peyne<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Orribleli and soone he shal apere to &yogh;ou; for most hard dom shal|ben don in hem, that ben biforn.  Forsothe to the litle is grauntid mercy;|my&yogh;ty men forsothe my&yogh;tili tormentis shul suffre.  Forsothe he shal not|withdrawe the persone of any man, the Lord, that is lordshipere of alle|thingus, and he shal not drede the mykilnesse of any man; for litil and gret|he made, and euenli cure is to hym of alle.  To the strengere forsothe|strengere stant in tormenting.'  1388, 'Hidousli and soone he schal appere|to &yogh;ou forwhi hardeste doom schal be maad in hem, that ben souereyns.|Forsothe merci is grauntid to a litil man; but mi&yogh;ti men schulen suffre|turmentis mi&yogh;tili.  For the Lord, which is lord of alle thingis, schal not withdrawe|the persoone of ony man, nether he schal drede the greetnesse of ony|man; for he made the litil man and the greet man, and charge is to hym|evenli of alle men.  But strongere turment nei&yogh;eth to strongere men.'</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;ise|forseide prestis &amp; kny&yogh;tis&meper; &thorn;oru&yogh; suche vicious dedis/ leden &thorn;e|comunes on her ryng&meper; and boolden hem in synne/ &thorn;at al &thorn;is worlde|is sett in rore&meper; in bataile &amp; in werre &Verbar; But now ben comen to &thorn;e|proof&meper; &thorn;e wordis &thorn;at God ha&thorn; seide/ bi &thorn;e prophete Ieremye&meper; to|teche hise chosen seruantis/ Iere. ix<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Omnes adulteri | sunt &amp; <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="68a">|cetus preuaricatorum extenderunt linguam suam quasi arcum|mendacii &amp; non veritatis/ confortati sunt in terra quia de malo ad|malum egressi sunt. &amp; me non cognouerunt dicit dominus vnusquisque|a proximo suo se custodiat. &amp; in omni fratre suo non|habeat fiduciam/ quia omnis frater supplantans supplantabit/ &|omnis amicus fraudilenter incedet/ &amp; vir fratrem suum deridebit|&amp; veritatem non loquetur'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Jer. ix. 2-5.</NOTE> &Verbar;  Alle &thorn;ise ben avowtreris&meper; &amp; a cumpany|&thorn;at breken &thorn;e lawe/ &thorn;ei han strecchid for&thorn;e her tung&meper; as|a bent bowe/ to schete lesyng &amp; no trou&thorn;e&meper; iche man at o&thorn;ir/ &thorn;ei|ben counfortid in &thorn;e er&thorn;e&meper; for &thorn;ei goon from yuel to yuel/ &amp; &thorn;ei|han not knowen me&meper; sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord God/Iche man from his nei&yogh;bore&meper;|kepe he him ful wiseli/ &amp; in his owene bro&thorn;ir&meper; he mai haue no|trist/ for iche a bro&thorn;ir in disceyte&meper; schal bigile o&thorn;ir/ &amp; iche|a frende falseli&meper; schal goo awei from o&thorn;ir/ &amp; &thorn;e man schal scorne|his bro&thorn;ir&meper; &amp; &thorn;ei schal not speke trou&thorn;e/ forso&thorn;e &thorn;ei han tau&yogh;t her|tung&meper; for to speke | lesing&meper; and for &thorn;ei wolde do wickidli&meper; &thorn;ei <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="68b">|han soore traueiled/ &thorn;ei han forsaken in treccherie. to knowe me|sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord God &Verbar; Wherfore &thorn;ise &thorn;ingis&meper; sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord of oostis/|Loo I schal welle hem togidir&meper; &amp; I schal proue hem &Verbar; what schal
<PB N="72">|I ellis do&meper; fro &thorn;e face of my peple?  an arow wounding is her|tung&meper; for it speki&thorn; gile/ &amp; he speki&thorn; wi&thorn; his frende&meper; pees wi&thorn; his|mou&thorn;e/ but priueli he leie&thorn; for him&meper; spies to disceyue him.  No|whe&thorn;ir schal I not visite vpon &thorn;ise &thorn;ingis&meper; sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord God/ or|schal not my wille be vengid&meper; vpon suche a folk?<NOTE PLACE="foot"><P>W. V. 'For alle auoutreris thei ben, and cumpanye of lawe brekeres:|and thei benten out ther tung as ther bowe of lesyng, and not of treuthe.|Thei ben coumfortid in erthe, for fro euel to euel thei wenten out and me thei|knewe not, seith the Lord.  Eche kepe hymself fro his ne&yogh;hebore, and in eche|brother of hym have he not trost: for eche brother supplauntende shal|supplaunte, and eche frend gilendely shal go.  And a man his brother shal|scorne and treuthe shal not speke; thei ta&yogh;ten forsothe ther tunge to speke|lesing; that wickely thei schulden don, thei traveileden.  Thi dwelling in the|myddel of treccherie; in treccherie thei forsoke me to knowen, seith the Lord.|Therfore these thingus seith the Lord of ostus.  Lo! I shall &yogh;eete and preve|them; what forsothe other thing shal Y do fro the face of the sone of my|puple?  An arwe woundende the tunge of hem, treccherie it spak; in his|mouth pes with his friend he speketh, and priveli he putteth to hym aspies.|Whether up on these thingus I shal not visite, seith the Lord, or in to such|a maner folc shal not be vengid my soule?'</P><P>1388, 'Forwhi alle ben auowteris, and the cumpenyes of trespassouris|a&yogh;ens the lawe; and thei helden forth her tunge as a bouwe of leesyng, and|not of treuthe.  Thei ben coumfortid in erthe, for thei &yogh;eden out fro yuel to|yuel, and thei knewen not me, seith the Lord.  Ech man kepe hym from his|nei&yogh;bore, and haue no trist in ony brother of hym; for whi ech brother|disseyvyng schal disseyve, and ech frend schal go gilefuli.  And a man schal|scorne his brother, and schal not speke treuthe; for thei tau&yogh;ten her tunge to|speke leesyng; thei traueliden to do wickidli.  Thi dwellyng is in the myddis|of gile; in gile thei forsoken to knowe me, seith the Lord, Therfor the Lord|of oostis seith these thingis, Lo! Y schal welle togidere; and Y schal preue|hem; for whi what other thing schal Y do fro the face of the dou&yogh;ter of my|puple?  The tunge of hem is an arowe woundynge and spak gile; in his|mouth he spekith pees with his frend, and priueli he settith tresouns to hym.|Whether Y schal not visite on these thingis, seith the Lord, ether schal not|my soule take veniaunce on siche a folc?'</P></NOTE> As if he wolde|seie&meper; I schal be vengid/ for as her wille is to go fro me.  so my|wille is to be vengid vpon hem&meper; whanne I se my tyme &Verbar; But|happeli here summe wole seie.  God wole not take veniaunce&meper; vpon|hise cristen peple/ God wole not leese &thorn;at he deere bou&yogh;t&meper; wi&thorn; his|preciouse blood/ To &thorn;e firste we answeren&meper; bi &thorn;e mou&thorn;e of God/|Iere. xvi<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Deriliquerunt me patres vestri ait dominus &amp; abierunt<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="69a">| post deos alienos &amp; ser-|-uierunt eis &amp; adorauerunt eos &amp; me|deriliquerunt &amp; legem meam non custodierunt/ sed &amp; vos peius|operati estis quam patres vestri/ Ecce enim ambulat vnusquisque
<PB N="73">|post prauitatem cordis sui mali.  &amp; me non audiat &Verbar; Et eiciam vos|de terra hac in terram quam ignoratis vos &amp; patres vestri &amp; seruietis|ibi dijs alienis die ac nocte qui non dabunt vobis requiem'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Jer. xvi. 11-13.</NOTE> &Verbar; &THORN;e|Lord sei&thorn;.  &yogh;oure fadris han forsaken me&meper; &amp; gon aftir straunge|goddis/ for to do hem seruyce&meper; &amp; worschipe hem also/ but &thorn;ei han|forsaken me&meper; &amp; not kept my lawe &Verbar; But &amp; &yogh;e do miche werre&meper; &thorn;an|euere wrou&yogh;t &yogh;oure fadris/ Loo iche of &yogh;ou walki&thorn;&meper; aftir &thorn;e|schrewidnes of his yuel herte/ &thorn;at he heere not me&meper; sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord|God/ &amp; I schal kast &yogh;ou awey&meper; oute of &thorn;is er&thorn;e/ in to a lond &thorn;at|is vnknowen&meper; to &yogh;ou &amp; to &yogh;oure fadris/ &amp; &thorn;ere &yogh;e schal do seruice&meper;|to alien goddis/ &thorn;at schullen &yogh;yue no rest to &yogh;ou&meper; nei&thorn;ir dai ne|ny&yogh;t<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'For forsoken me &yogh;oure fadris, seith the Lord, and &yogh;iden awei aftir|aliene goddis, and serueden to them, and honoureden hem, and me forsoken,|and my lawe kepten not.  But and &yogh;ee wers wro&yogh;ten than &yogh;oure fadris; lo!|forsothe eche goth after the shreudenesse of his euel herte, that me he here|not.  And Y shal caste &yogh;ou out fro this lond, in to the lond that &yogh;ee and &yogh;oure|fadris knowe not; and &yogh;ee shul serue there to alien goddis dai and ny&yogh;t, that|shul not &yogh;iue to &yogh;ou rest.'  1388, 'For &yogh;oure fadris forsoken me, seith the|Lord, and &yogh;eden aftir alien goddis, and seruyden hem, and worschipiden hem,|and thei forsoken me, and kepten not my lawe.  But also &yogh;e wrou&yogh;ten worse|than &yogh;oure fadris; for lo! ech man goith aftir the shrewidnesse of his yuel|herte, that he here not me.  And Y shal caste &yogh;ou out of this lond, in to the|lond which &yogh;e and &yogh;oure fadris knowen not; and &yogh;e schulen serue there to|alien goddis dai and ny&yogh;t, whiche schulen not &yogh;ive reste to you.'</NOTE>/ And to &thorn;e secounde we answeren&meper; as Crist sei&thorn; in his|gospel/ Mat. xxii<SUP>o</SUP>. | 'Amice quomodo huc intrasti non habens <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="69b">|vestem nupcialem at ille obmutuit/ Tunc rex ait ministris. ligatis|manibus eius &amp; pedibus mittite eum in tenebras exteriores. ibi erit|fletus &amp; stridor dencium'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. xxii. 12, 13 'Amice, quomodo ... Tunc dixit rex ministris,'|etc.</NOTE> &Verbar;  Frende hou entridist &thorn;ou hidir&meper; not|hauyng &thorn;e bridal cloo&thorn;? &amp; he wex doombe/ &thorn;anne &thorn;is kyng Iesu|Crist&meper; seide to hise mynystris/ &thorn;is wrecche bounden hand &amp; foot&meper;|sende him in to &thorn;e vttirar dercknes/ &thorn;ere schal be weping&meper; &|gneching of tee&thorn;/<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Frend, hou entridist thou hidir, not hauynge brijd clothe?  And|he was doumbe.  Thanne the kyng seide to the mynystris, His hondis and|feet bounden, sende &yogh;ee hym into uttermore derknessis: there shal be weepyng|and betyng to gidre of teeth.'  1388, 'Freend, hou entridist thou hidir without|bride clothes?  And he was doumbe.  Thanne the kyng bad hise mynystris,|Bynde hym bothe hondis and feet, and sende &yogh;e him in to utmer derknessis:|there schal be wepyng and grentyng of teeth.'</NOTE> vndirstande bi &thorn;is frende&meper; bo&thorn;e man &amp;
<PB N="74">|womman/ &thorn;at ha&thorn; taken cristendom&meper; &amp; holden &thorn;e name/ but &thorn;ei|wanten in her lyuyng&meper; werkis of trewe bileue/ &thorn;erfore Crist|wardi&thorn; hem&meper; in to &thorn;e peyne of helle &Verbar;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 TYPE="chapter" N="10">
<HEAD>How &thorn;e good of &thorn;e secounde chirche acorden wi&thorn; &thorn;e firste|chirche.  Cap<SUP>m</SUP> .X<SUP>m</SUP>. &Verbar;</HEAD>
<P>Here schullen we telle&meper; hou &thorn;e good of &thorn;e secounde chirche/|acordi&thorn; wi&thorn; &thorn;e firste chirche&meper; appropurid to God/ Fei&thorn;. hope. &|charite&meper; as we han seid aforn/ knytten God &amp; man togidir&meper; in<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="70a">| oonhed of &thorn;is | chirche/ &thorn;is knott is knitt so sikerli&meper; &thorn;at it schal|neuer more faile/ nei&thorn;ir here ne ellis-where&meper; as &thorn;e wise man sei&thorn;/|Eccles. iiii<SUP>o</SUP>.  'Triplex funiculus difficile rumpitur'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Eccles. iv. 12.</NOTE> &Verbar;  A &thorn;refolde|corde&meper; ful loo&thorn;e is brostun<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'A thre fold corde hard is to-broken.'  1388, 'A threfolde corde|is brokun of hard.'</NOTE> &Verbar; For to make &thorn;is &thorn;refolde corde&meper; we|must haue &thorn;re lynkis/ &amp; eeke hem for&thorn;e perfi&yogh;tli&meper; til &thorn;is corde be|wrou&yogh;t&meper; bi whiche &thorn;is chirche schal be drawen&meper; vnto &thorn;e holi|trinite/ &THORN;ise ben &thorn;e firste &thorn;re&meper; a chaast bodi. a clene soule. &amp; goodis|treweli disposid/ &thorn;anne it schal be eekid. wi&thorn; good worde. holi|&thorn;ou&yogh;t. &amp; a perfi&yogh;te dede/ moreouere we must large for&thorn;e&meper; schrifte|of mou&thorn;e. sorow of herte. &amp; amendis makyng/ Aftir &thorn;is it axi&thorn;&meper;|preiour. fasting. &amp; almes dede/ Aftir &thorn;is we must putt to. noumbre.|wei&yogh;t. &amp; mesure/ Also we must eeke &thorn;is corde&meper; wi&thorn; mynde. wille.|&amp; resoun/ &amp; helpe for&thorn;e to &thorn;e eende&meper; wi&thorn; fei&thorn;. hope. &amp; charite/|&THORN;anne we schal nei&yogh; to oure God&meper; &thorn;oru&yogh; grace. mercy. &amp; ri&yogh;twisenes/|til we se God in trinite&meper; Fadir &amp; Sone &amp; Holi Goost/<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="70b"></P>
<P>Euery membre of | &thorn;is chirche&meper; helpi&thorn; &thorn;at it may/ for to|worche a parte of &thorn;is corde&meper; for &thorn;e comune profite/ as seint Austin|sei&thorn;. 'Ecclesia est quedam forma forma iusticie. id est commune ius|omnium. in communi orat. in communi operatur. sine ecclesie|catholice societate nec baptismus alicui prodesse potest.  nec opera|misericordie . nisi forte vt minus torqueatur' &Verbar; Holi chirche is|a forme&meper; of al ri&yogh;twisenes/ &thorn;at is to seie a comune acorde&meper; of alle|good &thorn;ingis/ &amp; &thorn;is chirche preie&thorn; in comune&meper; and worchi&thorn; hir|werkis in comune&meper; for wi&thorn;outen felaschip&meper; of &thorn;is general chirche/|baptem may not profi&yogh;te&meper; ne &thorn;e dedis of mercy/ but if it be &thorn;at &thorn;e|peyne&meper; be &thorn;e lesse in helle &Verbar;</P>
<P>Alle &thorn;e membris of a man&meper; traueilen in her ordir/ iche for to|socour o&thorn;ir&meper; &amp; noon for to hindir/ but for to do her comune
<PB N="75">|helpe&meper; to profite of &thorn;e bodi &Verbar; &THORN;us it is of &thorn;e membris&meper; &thorn;at ben in|Cristis chirche/ for it is a goostli bodi&meper; &thorn;at growi&thorn; wi&thorn; hir|membris/ &thorn;ere oone faili&thorn; ano&thorn;ir helpi&thorn;&meper; til &thorn;is corde be made &Verbar;|Summe haue myche of wisdam&meper; to knowe holi writ/ summe haue|faire eloquence&meper; to preche it to &thorn;e peple/ summe han myche of &Verbar;goostli streng&thorn;e&meper; to suffre tribulacioun/ summe han pite &amp; releuen&meper; <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="71a">|her pore nedi nei&yogh;boris/ summe tenten vertuouseli to mynystir &thorn;e|sacramentis/ summe sti&yogh;en hi&yogh;eli&meper; to rest in heuenli likyngis/ But|alle suche &thorn;ingis ben in comune&meper; to hem &thorn;at schal be saued/ as &thorn;e|prophet sei&thorn;. Ps. cxv./ 'Particeps ego sum omnium timencium te&meper;|&amp; custodiencium mandata tua'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ps. cxviii. 63.</NOTE>/ &THORN;e prophete speki&thorn; in &thorn;e|persoone&meper; of &thorn;e general chirche/ Lord I am partenere&meper; of alle|&thorn;at dreden &thorn;ee/ &amp; of alle &thorn;at kepen&meper; &thorn;i hooli comaundementis<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Parcener I am of all men dredende thee: and of kepende thin|hestis.'  1388, 'I am parcener of alle that dreden thee; and kepen thin|heestis.'</NOTE>/|&THORN;is teche&thorn; also &thorn;e comune crede&meper; of &thorn;e .xii. apostlis/ In an article|of oure fei&thorn;&meper; &thorn;at must nede be grauntid/ 'Sanctorum communionem.'|comunyng of seintis/ For what &thorn;at euer be done in|Rome&meper; or in ony o&thorn;ir placis&meper; if &thorn;at &thorn;ing be couenable&meper; in &thorn;e si&yogh;t|of God/ &thorn;anne is it comune to alle &thorn;ise membris&meper; &thorn;at seruen God|in vertu/ to helpe hem to her endeles ioye&meper; as we han seide aforn/|Herto acordi&thorn; seint Ierom&meper; vpon &thorn;is tixte of Cristis gospel/|Mat. xvi<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Tibi dabo claues regni celorum'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. xvi. 19.</NOTE>/ Crist seid to Petir&meper;|&amp; in him to alle his folowars/ to &thorn;ee and alle | suche as &thorn;ou art&meper; <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="71b">|I schal &yogh;yue &thorn;e keyes of &thorn;e rewme of heuenes<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'To thee I shal &yogh;eue the keies of the kyngdam of heuenes.'</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;ise twoo keies.|&thorn;e tone is kunnyng of worde&meper; &thorn;e to&thorn;ir is power of presthood/ &THORN;e|rewme of heuenes&meper; is &thorn;e chirche here in er&thorn;e/ Ierom sei&thorn;&meper; &amp; &thorn;e|maistir of sentence rehersi&thorn; him/ li<SUP>o</SUP>. IIii<SUP>o</SUP>. dist. xix.  'Habent|inquit eandem iudiciariam potestatem omnes ecclesie ministri in|episcopis &amp; presbiteris sicut petrus. sed ideo petrus eam specialiter|accepit vt omnes intelligant quod quicumque ab vnitate fidei &|societate ecclesie se separauerit. nec a peccatis solui. nec celum|potest ingredi'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Petrus Lombardus, <I>Sententiarum Libri quatuor</I>, IV, dist. xix (Migne,|tom. 191, col. 890).</NOTE> &Verbar;  Alle &thorn;e mynystris of &thorn;e chirch&meper; in bischopis
<PB N="76">|&amp; in prestis/ han &thorn;e same iudiciarij powere&meper; as seint Petir|hadde/ But &thorn;erfore Petir speciali&meper; tooke of God &thorn;is power/|&thorn;at alle men moun vndirstand&meper; &thorn;at who euer depart him/ fro|vnite of stedfast fei&thorn;&meper; &amp; felaschip of &thorn;is chirche/ he mai nei&thorn;ir|be asoyled&meper; from bondis of hise synnes/ nei&thorn;ir he mai entre&meper; in to|&thorn;e blisse of heuene &Verbar;</P>
<P>Se now &thorn;anne bo&thorn;e lewid &amp; lerned&meper; hou preiars ben in comune/<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="72a">| and alle o&thorn;ir suffragis&meper; to &thorn;is go-|-ostli chirche &Verbar; Whennes come&thorn;|&thorn;anne &thorn;is outcry&meper; &thorn;at is sette on broche/ saale keene in euery|chirche&meper; to selle &thorn;ise goostli &thorn;ingis/ wi&thorn; suffragis &amp; soilmentis&meper;|&amp; manye &yogh;eeris of pardoun/ &amp; a plener indulgence&meper; 'a pena &amp; a|culpa'/ But miche ra&thorn;ir it schulde be seide 'a gloria &amp; peccunia'/|Certis &thorn;ei comen fro benei&thorn;e&meper; of &thorn;e fendis tempting/ &amp; ben borne|al aboute&meper; of hise cursid membris/ to poysen &thorn;e peple in|mysbileue&meper; as seint Ierom sei&thorn;/ &amp; parte hem from Goddis|felaschip&meper; bi witnesse of seint Austin/ &amp; dryue hem to her|eendeles peyne&meper; as we han seide aforn &Verbar;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 TYPE="chapter" N="11">
<HEAD>Of Ioye in tribulacioun/  Cap<SUP>m</SUP> .XI<SUP>m</SUP>.. &Verbar;</HEAD>
<P>But for &thorn;at we reproue &thorn;ise synnes&meper; &thorn;is yuel parti grucchi&thorn;/ and|pursue&thorn; wi&thorn; strong hand&meper; to prisoun &amp; to slee/ &thorn;erfore must we|lerne &thorn;e loore&meper; of Cristis hooli gospel/  Mat. v<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Beati estis cum|maledixerint vobis homines &amp; persecuti vos fuerint &amp; dixerint|omne malum aduersum vos mencientes propter me &amp;c'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. v. 11 'Beati estis cum maledixerint vobis et persecuti,' etc.</NOTE>/ &yogh;e ben|blessid whanne men han oursid &yogh;ou. &amp; han pursued &yogh;ou. &amp; seid al<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="72b">| yuel | a&yogh;ens &yogh;ou lying for me&meper; Ioye &amp; be myry. for &yogh;oure mede is|miche in heuenes<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. '&YOGH;ee shulen be blessid, when men shulen curse &yogh;ou, and shulen|pursue &yogh;ou, and shulen say al yuel a&yogh;eins &yogh;ou lee&yogh;ing for me.  Joye &yogh;ee with|yn forth, and glade &yogh;ee with out forth, for &yogh;oure meede is plenteuouse in|heuenes.'</NOTE>/ And also seint Petir sei&thorn;. I. Pe. iii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Siquid|patimini propter iusticiam&meper; beati'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. 1 Pet. iii. 14.</NOTE> &Verbar;  Whanne &thorn;at &yogh;e suffren ony|&thorn;ing for ri&yogh;twisenesse&meper; blessid mut &yogh;e be<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'But if &yogh;e suffren ony thing for ri&yogh;twisenesse, &yogh;e ben blessid.'</NOTE> &Verbar;  Seint Poul afferme&thorn;|&thorn;is sentence&meper; &thorn;at Goddis trewe seruauntis/ schullen haue peyne in|&thorn;is lijf&meper; to kepe hem in vertu/  II. Thimo. iii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Omnes qui pie|volunt viuere in christo iesu&meper; persecucionem pacientur'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. 2 Tim. iii. 12.</NOTE> &Verbar;  Alle
<PB N="77">|&thorn;at euer wole lyue mekeli in Crist Iesu&meper; schal suffre persecucioun<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Alle men that wolen lyue piteuously in Crist Jhesu, schulen|suffre persecucioun.'  1388, 'Alle men that wolen lyue feithfull in Crist|Jhesu schulen suffre persecucioun.'</NOTE> &Verbar;|And seint Luk sei&thorn; of &thorn;e wordis of Poul&meper; in dedis of &thorn;e apostlis.|Actus xiiii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Per multas tribulaciones oportet nos intrare in regnum|dei'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Acts xiv. 21.</NOTE> &Verbar;  Bi manye tribulaciouns. it bihoue&thorn; vs to entre&meper; in to &thorn;e|rewme of God<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'By manye tribulaciouns it behoueth us for to entre into the|kingdom of heuenes.'</NOTE>/ And &thorn;us sei&thorn; &thorn;e prophete. Ps. xxxiii. 'Multe tribulaciones|iustorum&meper; et de omnibus hijs liberabit<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. biberauit.</NOTE> eos dominus'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ps. xxxiii. 19.</NOTE>/|many be &thorn;e tribulaciouns&meper; &thorn;at fallen to &thorn;e ri&yogh;twise/ and from hem|alle whanne tyme come&thorn;&meper; God schal delyuer hem<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Manye tribulaciouns of the ri&yogh;twise; and of alle these schal|delyuere them the Lord.'  1388, 'Many tribulaciouns ben of iust men; and|the Lord schal delyuere hem fro alle these.'</NOTE> &Verbar; Crist bihi&yogh;t &thorn;is|maner of lijf&meper; to hise owene disciplis/ and | &yogh;aue hem in counfort &thorn;at <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="73a">|&thorn;ei schal haue&meper; a graciouse delyueraunce/ for &thorn;anne schal blisse be|miche &thorn;e swetter&meper; whanne &thorn;ei comen &thorn;erto/ Ion. xvi<SUP>o</SUP>./ 'Amen amen|dico vobis. quia plorabitis &amp; flebitis vos mundus autem gaudebit|vos autem contristabimini. sed tristicia uestra vertetur in gaudium|&amp; gaudium vestrum. nemo tollet a vobis'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. John xvi. 20, 22.</NOTE> &Verbar;  Treweli I seie to &yogh;ou|&thorn;e trou&thorn;e&meper; &yogh;e schal greete &amp; weepe/ forso&thorn;e &thorn;is world schal ioye&meper;|&amp; &yogh;e schal be ful heuy/ and aftir &thorn;is &yogh;oure heuynes&meper; schal be|turned in to ioie/ &amp; &yogh;oure ioye schal be so siker&meper; &thorn;at no man|schal take it fro &yogh;ou<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Treuli treuli, I seye to &yogh;ou, for &yogh;e schulen morne and wepe.|forsothe the world schal enioye; forso&thorn;e &yogh;e schulen be sorwful, but &yogh;oure|sorwe schal turne into ioye, and no man schal take fro &yogh;ou &yogh;oure ioye.'</NOTE>/ And for &thorn;is ioie schulde sauour wel&meper; to|hem &thorn;at ben hise louears/ he sende&thorn; hem tribulacioun&meper; as seint|Gregor sei&thorn;/ 'Deus electis suis iter ostendit asperum&meper; ne si|delectentur in via obliuiscantur eorum que sunt in patria'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Gregorius Magnus, <I>Moralium</I> Lib. XXIII, cap. xxiv. 47 (Migne, tom.|76, cols. 279, 280).</NOTE>/ &|iterum/ 'tribulaciones que in hoc mundo nos premunt. nos ad|deum ire compellunt'/  Iterum. 'Oculos quos culpa claudit&meper;
<PB N="78">|pena aperit'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Gregorius Magnus, <I>Moralium</I> Lib. XV, cap. li. 58 (Migne, tom. 75,|col. 1111).</NOTE> &Verbar; God schewi&thorn; to hise chosen&meper; scharpnes in &thorn;is<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="73b">| iourney/ lest bihap | if &thorn;ei delited hem&meper; in &thorn;is deedli weye/ &thorn;ei|my&yogh;t for&yogh;ete &thorn;e &thorn;ingis&meper; &thorn;at ben in heuenli countre/ Tribulaciouns|&thorn;at brisen vs doun&meper; in &thorn;is wrecchid world/ &thorn;ei constreynen vs to|go to God&meper; &thorn;at li&yogh;tli my&yogh;t be dampned/ for &thorn;oo i&yogh;en &thorn;at synne|closi&thorn;&meper; peyne maki&thorn; hem open/ and many a man &thorn;at haunti&thorn;|&thorn;eeft&meper; wi&thorn; manye o&thorn;ir synnes/ if &thorn;ei were lame. blynde. or crokid&meper;|of Goddis visitacioun/ &thorn;ei schulden cese &amp; serue her God&meper; &amp; do|penaunce ful treweli/ as Crisostom sei&thorn;.  om. iii. 'Anima spiritus|est &amp; spirituales penas timet.  carnales non timet. verum &amp; sancti|penas huius seculi contempnunt &amp; futurum iudicium timent vbi|spiritus cruciantur &Verbar;  Caro autem spirituales penas non timet.|carnales autem timet. ideo mali non cessant peccare nisi eos iudicia|carnalia &amp; terrena conpescant propterea mittet dominus super|seruos suos carnales temptaciones ut conbusta caro non concupiscat|malum'<NOTE PLACE="foot">S. Ioan. Chrysostomus, (<I>Homilia III, Opera</I>, ed. 1547, tom. ii, col. 763).</NOTE> &Verbar; &THORN;e soule is a spirit&meper; &amp; dredi&thorn; spiritual peynes/ but it<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="74a">| wole not drede&meper; | &thorn;e peynes of &thorn;e fleische/ &amp; &thorn;erfore seyntis|dispisiden&meper; peynes of &thorn;is world/ &amp; dreden &thorn;e last iugement&meper; where|spiritis ben turmentid/ Forso&thorn;e &thorn;e fleische cannot drede&meper; goostli|peynes to cum/ but he dredi&thorn; in &thorn;is lijf&meper; to suffre ony peynes/|&thorn;erfore &thorn;e yuel cessen not&meper; for to do synne/ but if iugement of &thorn;e|fleische&meper; constreynen hem to be stille/ &amp; for &thorn;is cause &thorn;e Lord schal|sende&meper; vpon hise seruauntis/ sore punysching to her fleische&meper; &|o&thorn;ir tribulaciouns/ &thorn;at lust of &thorn;e fleische mai be sweilid&meper; from|coueiting of yuel.  We must nede breke &thorn;e nutt&meper; if we wole haue|&thorn;e kirnel/ we must nedis suffre traueile&meper; if we desiren rest/ So|must we nede suffre peyne&meper; if we wole cum to blisse &Verbar;</P>
<P>He is a fals coward kny&yogh;t&meper; &thorn;at flee&thorn; &amp; hide&thorn; his heed/ whanne|his maistir is in &thorn;e feelde&meper; beten among hise enemyes &Verbar; But oure|Lord Iesu Crist&meper; was beten of &thorn;e Iewis/ &amp; aftir died in &thorn;e felde&meper;<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="74b">| on &thorn;e mount of Calverie/ to paye oure raunsum he tooke his | dee&thorn;&meper;|for he no &thorn;ing giltid/ and his bodi whanne it was offrid&meper; made|asee&thorn; at fulle/ in redempcioun of mankynde&meper; &thorn;erfore &thorn;e wise man|sei&thorn; | Ecc1. xxix<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Gratiam fideiussoris ne obliuiscaris dedit enim|pro te animam suam<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ecclesiasticus xxix. 20.</NOTE>'/  For&yogh;ete &thorn;ou not &thorn;e kyndenes of &thorn;i borow&meper;
<PB N="79">|forso&thorn;e he ha&thorn; &yogh;ouun for &thorn;ee his lijf<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'The grace of the bor&yogh; ne forgete thou; forsothe he &yogh;af for thee|his soule.'  1388, 'For&yogh;ete thou not the grace of the borewe; for he &yogh;af his|lijf for thee.'</NOTE> &Verbar; &THORN;is borow is oure Lord|God&meper; &thorn;at wi&thorn;outen mede/ cam from heuene in to &thorn;is world&meper; for|to borow hise peple/ and in takyng fleische &amp; blood&meper; of &thorn;e virgyn|Mary/ he schewid vs grace &amp; kyndenes&meper; bo&thorn;e in worde &amp; worchyng/|But in &yogh;yuyng of his lijf&meper; he leide his bodi in plege/ &yogh;he to &thorn;e|dee&thorn; he wolde not spare&meper; so miche he loued hise peple &Verbar; If &thorn;at|fei&thorn; be trewe in vs&meper; &thorn;is mai not be for&yogh;eten &Verbar;</P>
<P>Summe forsaken synnes&meper; &amp; swen Crist in vertu/ &amp; &thorn;is is|a greet kyndenes&meper; &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei sti&yogh;e no hi&yogh;er &Verbar; Summe done wake in|abstinence&meper; &amp; studien holi lessouns. &thorn;is is &thorn;anne a gretter kyndenes&meper;|if &thorn;ey flee from synne/ summe ben redi whanne &thorn;ei ben clepid&meper;|of &thorn;e Hooli Goost/ to suffre dee&thorn; for Iesu Crist&meper; &amp; witnesse of | his <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="75a">|lawe/ and whanne &thorn;ei haue clennes in lyuyng&meper; &thorn;is is &thorn;e greetest|kyndenes/ as &thorn;e gospel schewi&thorn;.  Ion. xv<SUP>o</SUP>.  'Maiorem hac dileccionem|nemo habet vt animam suam ponat quis pro amicis suis'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Joh. xv. 13.</NOTE>/|A gretter loue or charite mai no man haue&meper; &thorn;an to leie his lijf. in|sauyng of hise frendis soule<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'No man hath more loue than this, that ony man putte his soul|(that is, lyf), for his frendis.'</NOTE> &Verbar; we were leef &amp; dere to God&meper;|whanne we took &thorn;e baptem/ but we ben miche derwor&thorn;ier&meper; whanne|we done &thorn;e werkis/ &thorn;at God ha&thorn; boden in his lawe&meper; wi&thorn;outen ony|grucchyng &Verbar; And if we maynten &thorn;is bileue&meper; &amp; wole not go &thorn;erfro/|nei&thorn;ir bicum renagatis&meper; for peyne &thorn;at mai falle/ but &thorn;enk on|Cristis passioun&meper; &thorn;at swagi&thorn; al heuynes/ &THORN;anne ben we moost|derwor&thorn;iest&meper; and wor&thorn;i hi&yogh;est merit/ &amp; &thorn;erfore sei&thorn; seint Poul|vnto &thorn;e Galatheis/  Gala. vi<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Michi autem absit gloriari nisi in|cruce domini nostri Iesu Christi per quem mihi mundus crucifixus|est &amp; ego mundo'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Gal. vi. 14.</NOTE>/ Fer be it to me sei&thorn; seint Poul&meper; to make ony|glory/ but in &thorn;e cros&meper; &thorn;at is &thorn;e passioun&meper; | of oure Lord Iesu <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="75b">|Crist/ bi whom &thorn;is world is crucified to me&meper; &amp; I am crucified to|&thorn;e world<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Be it ferr to me to glorie, no but in the cross of oure Lord Jhesu|Christ, by whom the world is crucified to me, and I to the world.'  1388,|'But fer be it fro me to haue glorie, no but in the crosse of oure Lord Jhesu|Crist, bi whom the world is crucified to me, and Y to the world.'</NOTE> &Verbar; For &thorn;is world dispisid Poul&meper; &amp; he dispised &thorn;e world/|Summe be not crucified to &thorn;e world&meper; but &thorn;e world is crucified to
<PB N="80">|hem/ for &thorn;ei dispisen &thorn;is world&meper; but &thorn;is world dispise&thorn; not hem/|Summ ben crucified to &thorn;e world&meper; but not so &thorn;e world to hem/ for|&thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;e world dispise hem&meper; &thorn;ei dispisen it not a&yogh;en &Verbar; Summe ben|no&thorn;ir crucified to &thorn;e world&meper; ne &thorn;e world to hem/ for nei&thorn;ir &thorn;ei|dispise &thorn;e world&meper; ne &thorn;e world hem/ In &thorn;e firste degre&meper; weren &thorn;e|apostlis/ and in &thorn;e secounde degre&meper; ben o&thorn;ir good lyuars &Verbar; But in|&thorn;e &thorn;ridde &amp; &thorn;e four&thorn;e degree&meper; ben &thorn;oo &thorn;at schal be dampned/|And &thorn;erfore we schal vndirstande&meper; &thorn;at summe suffren peyne/ for|to saue &thorn;e peple&meper; &amp; so dide Iesu Crist/ whanne &thorn;ei my&yogh;t not saue|hem silf&meper; &amp; schewid his greet kyndenes &Verbar; Summe suffren peyne&meper; &|largen her mede/ as dide Cristis apostles&meper; &amp; manye o&thorn;ir martris/|Summe suffren peyne&meper; to purge hem of her synne/ &thorn;at &thorn;ei han<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="76a">| done in tyme bifore&meper; &amp; crien God of mercy/ Summe | suffren|peyne&meper; to kepe hem from synne/ &thorn;at &thorn;ei schulde be acumbrid wi&thorn;&meper;|if ne peyne were/ But summe suffren peyne&meper; for &thorn;ei haunten synne/|&amp; for &thorn;ei make non ende &thorn;erof&meper; &thorn;e peyne schal laste wi&thorn;outen|ende &Verbar; Ioyne we &thorn;anne &thorn;e cros of God&meper; vnto oure bare fleische/|&thorn;at oure part mai be founden&meper; among &thorn;ise hooli seyntis/ &thorn;at|wilfulli forsoke hem silf&meper; &amp; ioyed in tribulacioun/ as seint Iames|sei&thorn;. Iaco. i<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Omne gaudium existimaste fratres mei cum in|temptaciones varias incideritis. scientes quod probacio fidei vestre|operatur pacienciam. paciencia autem opus perfectum habet'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Jac. i. 2.</NOTE> &Verbar;|Mi bri&thorn;eren hope &yogh;e al ioye&meper; whanne &yogh;e han sliden in among|diuerse temptaciouns/  witing &thorn;at &thorn;e prouyng of &yogh;oure fei&thorn;&meper;|worchi&thorn; pacience/ forso&thorn;e pacience ha&thorn; a perfi&yogh;t werk&meper; &thorn;at &yogh;e|moun be perfi&yogh;t in soule/ &amp; hool in bodi&meper; &amp; in no &thorn;ing failing<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'My britheren, gesse &yogh;e, (or deme), al ioye, whan &yogh;e shulen falle in|to diuerse temptaciouns, (or tribulaciouns), witynge, that the prouyng of &yogh;oure|feith werchith pacience; sotheli pacience hath parfijt werk, that &yogh;e be parfijt|and hool, in no thing faylinge.'  1388, 'My britheren, deme &yogh;e al joye,|whanne &yogh;e fallen in to diuerse temptaciouns, witynge, that the preuyng of|&yogh;oure feith worchith pacience; and pacience hath a perfit werk, that &yogh;e be|perfit and hole, and faile in no thing.'</NOTE> &Verbar;</P>
