<PB N="91">A&yogh;en &thorn;is comaundement&meper; &thorn;e fende in hise membris/ &yogh;yue&thorn; leue|to chapmen&meper; to bie &amp; to selle/ &yogh;he wi&thorn;ynne &thorn;e sauntwary&meper; on &thorn;e|holi sundai/ and vitileris of &thorn;e countre&meper; holden comune market &Verbar;|&yogh;et se more wlatsumnes&meper; a&yogh;ens &thorn;is Goddis heest/ greet feires of|&thorn;e &yogh;eere&meper; for &thorn;e moost partie&meper; ben sett on | &thorn;e saboth dai&meper; bi &thorn;e <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="85b">|fendis counceile/ God tooke ful hidouse wreeche&meper; vpon &thorn;e children|of Isrel/ whanne &thorn;ei wrou&yogh;t seruyle werke. vpon her saboth dai/|as it is writen. Exo. xxxi<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Custodite sabbatum meum sanctum|enim est vobis. qui polluerit illud. morte morietur/ qui fecerit in|eo opus peribit anima illius de medio populi sui'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ex. xxxi. 14.</NOTE> &Verbar; &THORN;at is to seie.|Halowe &yogh;e my saboth&meper; forso&thorn;e it is holi to &yogh;ou/ who &thorn;at ha&thorn;|defoulid it&meper; he schal be deed/ &amp; he &thorn;at doi&thorn; ony seruyle werke|&thorn;erynne&meper; his lijf schal perische fro &thorn;e myddis of his peple<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Kepith myn holi day, holi forsothe it is to &yogh;ow, who so poluteth|it, with deth dye he; who so doth in it werk. shal perishe the lijf of hym fro|the myddil of his puple.'  1388, 'Kepe &yogh;e my sabat, for it is hooli to &yogh;ou; he|that defoulith it, schal die bi deeth, the soule of hym, that doith werk in the|sabat, schal perische fro the myddis of his puple.'</NOTE>/ &amp; so|for gedring of stikkis&meper; on &thorn;e saboth dai/ a man bi Goddis bidding|was stooned to &thorn;e dee&thorn; &Verbar; &thorn;erfore Neemyas&meper; a man &thorn;at dredde|God/ wolde suffre noon to bie ne selle&meper; on &thorn;e sabot dai/ wi&thorn;ynne|&thorn;e &yogh;atis of Ierusalem&meper; nei&thorn;ir aboute &thorn;e wallis/ and chargid alle|vitileris&meper; &thorn;at &thorn;ei schulde ceese/ And if &thorn;ei wolde not take heede&meper;|&thorn;ei schulde fele his hondis/ for he &thorn;ou&yogh;t to werre on hem&meper; as on|Goddis enemyes/ but &thorn;ei wolde obeie to God&meper; in halowing of his|saboth/ &THORN;is processe is | writen in &thorn;e book of Neemyas&meper; &thorn;e last <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="86a">|chapitir<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Neh. xiii. 15-22.</NOTE> &Verbar;  Loo hou strei&yogh;tli &thorn;e Iewis&meper; kepten Goddis bidding/|&amp; hou God smot hem wi&thorn; bodili peyne&meper; whanne &thorn;at &thorn;ei dide|forfet/  But cristen men maken her boost&meper; &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben more|perfi&yogh;t/ in seruyse of her Lord God&meper; &thorn;an euer were &thorn;e Iewis/|who &thorn;at euer mekeli&meper; proue&thorn; his word in dede/ &thorn;anne mai he
<PB N="92">|seie boldli&meper; &thorn;at &thorn;is tyme of grace/ is of more perfeccioun&meper; per|vertu of &thorn;e sacramentis/ and fredom of &thorn;e gospel&meper; &thorn;an was Moises|lawe/ and &thorn;ou a more perfite man&meper; in keping &thorn;is perfeccioun &Verbar;|But &amp; &thorn;ou be apostataa&meper; in breking of Goddis heestis/ &thorn;anne is|&thorn;i peyne so miche &thorn;e more&meper; as Poul seide to &thorn;e Romayns/ Ro. xi<SUP>o</SUP>./|'Tu autem fide stas. noli altum sapere sed time/ si enim deus|naturalibus ramis non pepercit. ne forte nec tibi parcat'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Rom. xi. 20, 21.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;at|is to seie.  Forso&thorn;e &thorn;ou stondist in &thorn;e fei&thorn;&meper; nyle &thorn;ou be proude/|ne bere &thorn;ee neuere &thorn;e hi&yogh;er&meper; but abide &thorn;ou mekeli/ in &thorn;e holi|drede of &thorn;e Lord &Verbar;  Forso&thorn;e si&thorn;en &thorn;at God sparid not. to &thorn;e<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="86b">| kyndli braunchis/ &thorn;at is to &thorn;e Iewis&meper; &thorn;at | he chase to be hise|kyndeli heiris/ Bi war lest bi happe he spare not &thorn;ee&meper; &thorn;at camest|out of &thorn;e hee&thorn;en stokke/ &amp; arte plauntid in bi grace&meper; of Crist|&amp; hise gospel<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Forsoth thou stondist by feith.  Nyle thou sauere hi&yogh;e thing, but|drede thou, forsothe if God sparide not the kyndely braunchis, lest peraventure|he spare not thee.'</NOTE> &Verbar;  Se now &thorn;yn apostasie&meper; &thorn;ou vnkynde wrecche/|&amp; &thorn;e falsenes &thorn;at &thorn;ou vsest&meper; a&yogh;en Cristis gospel/  Mat. xxi<SUP>o</SUP>.|Mar. ix<SUP>o</SUP>. Luk. xix<SUP>o</SUP>. &amp; Ion. ii<SUP>o</SUP>./ 'Intrauit Iesu in templum dei.|&amp; eiciebat omnes vendentes &amp; ementes in templo &amp; mensas nummulariorum|&amp; cathedras vendencium columbas euertit'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. xxi. 12; Luc. xix. 45; Joh. ii. 15.</NOTE>&Verbar; &THORN;at is to seie.|Iesu entrid in to &thorn;e temple of God&meper; &amp; he cast out alle sellars &|biears in &thorn;e temple&meper; &amp; &thorn;e bordis of mony-makears/ &amp; he turned|vp-so-doun&meper; &thorn;e chaiers of hem &thorn;at soolden dowues/ and he seide|vnto hem&meper; it is writen Isaye .lvi<SUP>o</SUP>.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Isaias lvi. 7.</NOTE> my hous schal be clepid. an|hous<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. hou.</NOTE> of preiour/ forso&thorn;e &yogh;e han made it a den of &thorn;eeues<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Jhesus entride in to the temple of God, and kest out of the|temple alle sellynge and biynge; and he turnyde upsodoun the bordis of|chaungeris, and the chaiers of men sellynge culveris.  And he seith to hem It|is writen, My hous shal be clepid an hous of priere; forsothe &yogh;e han made it|a denne of thefes.'</NOTE> &Verbar; Criste|forbedi&thorn; &thorn;e laite&meper; &thorn;e vsing of her marchaundise/ ei&thorn;ir in toune|or in chirche&meper; on her holy dai/ &amp; he dampne&thorn; more strei&yogh;tlier&meper;<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="87a">| among &thorn;ise visiouse prestis/ biyng of her beneficis&meper; &amp; | selling of|her sacramentis/ as doctour Odo sei&thorn;&meper; vpon &thorn;is same gospel/|'Columbas vendentes sunt qui spiritualia vendunt | &amp; si non|clamant ore. tum cum iuda dicunt/  Quid uultis dare&meper; &amp; ego
<PB N="93">|vobis eum<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. &emacr;&amacr;.</NOTE> tradam?  Sic clamant monachi ceterique religiosi&meper;|habitum &amp; suffragia vendentes. item non sacerdotes diuina celebrantes|&amp; tales in ecclesia dei multiplicantur? vbi credis quod sit|domus orationis. ibi invenies speluncam latronum/ omnes qui|non intrant per hostium id est christum. sed per pecuniam uel|seculi gratiam fures sunt &amp; latrones per murum fractum ingredientes/|quia murus ecclesie rumpitur cum prece uel precio aut|sanguine minus ydoneus ad beneficium ecclesiasticum indigne promoueatur'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Odo of Cheriton, <I>Flores Sermonum</I>, fols. cvi, cvii.</NOTE>/|Hec ille &Verbar;  &THORN;at is to seie. &thorn;ei ben sellers of dowues&meper;|&thorn;at spirituel &thorn;ingis sellen/ &amp; &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei crien not wi&thorn; her mou&thorn;e&meper;|ne&thorn;les<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. ne&thorn;els.</NOTE> &thorn;ei seyn wi&thorn; Iudas/ what wole &yogh;e &yogh;yue&meper; &amp; I schal bitraie|him to &yogh;ou? &THORN;us crien mounkis&meper; &amp; o&thorn;ir bastard religioun/ &thorn;at|sellen as &thorn;ei mai take &thorn;erfore&meper; her habit &amp; her suffragijs/ &amp; o&thorn;ir|prestis don | als wick&meper; &thorn;at treten diuine seruice/ &amp; suche ben <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="87b">|now multiplied&meper; in &thorn;e chirche of God/ &thorn;erfore where as &thorn;ou|wenest&meper; &thorn;at is &thorn;e hous of preiour/ &thorn;ere schalt &thorn;ou redili fynde&meper;|a den of mani &thorn;eues/ forso&thorn;e alle &thorn;at entren not&meper; bi &thorn;e door|&thorn;at is Crist/ but bi money or seculere fauour&meper; &thorn;ei ben ni&yogh;t&thorn;eues|&amp; dai-&thorn;eues/ &thorn;at entren in bi a broken wowe&meper; vnwiting|Iesu Crist/ for he proue&thorn; not her dedis&meper; &amp; &thorn;at is his vnknowyng/|for &thorn;anne is &thorn;e chirche wowe&meper; al to-broken doun/ whanne &thorn;e|vnable is avaunsid&meper; to &thorn;e chirches benefice/ ei&thorn;ir for