<HEAD>&THORN;e .IIII. heeste &Verbar;</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;e four&thorn;e comaundement of God is &thorn;is Exo. xx<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Honora patrem|tuum &amp; matrem tuam vt sis longeuus super terram quam dominus
<PB N="94">|deus tuus dabit tibi'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ex. xx. 12.</NOTE> &Verbar; &THORN;at is to seie. worschip &thorn;ou &thorn;i fadir &amp; &thorn;i|modir &thorn;at &thorn;ou be longlyuyng vpon er&thorn;e&meper; &thorn;e whiche &thorn;i Lord God|schal &yogh;yue to &thorn;ee<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Honour thi fader and thi moder, that thou be of long lijf upon|erthe, that the Lord thi God shal &yogh;yue to thee.'  1388, 'Onoure thi fadir and|thi modir, that thou be long lyuyng on the lond, which thi Lord God schal|&yogh;yue to thee.'</NOTE>/ And it swi&thorn; of &thorn;is comaundement&meper; &thorn;at &thorn;ei &thorn;at|worschipen not her parentis/ schullen haue schort lijf here in er&thorn;e&meper;|&amp; aftir &thorn;e lond of myschef/ &amp; &thorn;erfore Tobie tau&yogh;t his sone&meper; a litil|aforne his diyng/ Tobi. iiii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Corpus meum sepeli &amp; honorem habebis|matri tue omnibus diebus vite eius/ memor enim esse debes que|&amp; quanta pericula passa sit in vtero propter te'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Tob. iv. 3, 4 'Corpus meum ... passa sit propter te in utero|suo.'</NOTE> &Verbar; Sone birie &thorn;ou|my bodi&meper; &amp; &thorn;ou schalt haue worschip to &thorn;i modir. alle &thorn;e daies of|&thorn;i lijf/ &thorn;ou owist for to haue in mynde&meper; what perelles &amp; how mani|sche ha&thorn; suffrid in hir wombe for &thorn;ee<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'My bodi birie; and wrshipe thou shalt han to thi moder alle the|da&yogh;es of thi lif; forsothe myndeful thou owist to be, what and how grete she|suffride perilis for thee in hir wombe.'  1388, 'Byrie thou my bodi; and|thou schal haue onour to thi moder in alle the daies of hir lijf; for thou owist|to be myndeful, what perels and how grete sche suffride for thee in hir|wombe.'</NOTE>/<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="88b"></P>
<P>Summe | counten it for no synne&meper; to take fro her parentis/|suche &thorn;ing as &thorn;ei haue&meper; bi cause &thorn;ei ben her children/ but certis|&thorn;is synne passe&thorn; &thorn;eeft&meper; &amp; more it greue&thorn; God/ as &thorn;e wise man|sei&thorn;.  Prouer. xxviii<SUP>o</SUP>.  'Qui subtrahit aliquid a patre uel a matre|&amp; dicit hoc non est peccatum particeps homicide est'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Prov. xxviii. 24 'Qui subtrahit aliquid a patre suo et a matre et|dicit hoc non esse peccatum,' etc.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;at is to|seie. who &thorn;at wi&thorn;drawi&thorn; ony &thorn;ing from his fadir or his modir. &|sei&thorn; &thorn;at is no synne&meper; he is partener of manslau&yogh;tir<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Who withdrawith any thing fro his fader and moder, and seith|that not to ben synne, parcener is of a man sleere.'  1388, 'He that withdrawith|ony thing fro his fadir and fro his modir, and seith that this is no|synne, is parcener of a manquellere.'</NOTE>/ for worschip|to oure parentes&meper; stondi&thorn; in worde &amp; dede/ bo&thorn;e to teche hem &|rule hem&meper; if &thorn;ei ben lewid or pore/ and it longi&thorn; to &thorn;ise parentes|to gouerne wel her children/ &amp; ordeyn oonli not for hem&meper; &thorn;e|goodis of &thorn;is world/ but miche ra&thorn;ir dispose her lijf&meper; toward &thorn;e|blisse of heuene/ as &thorn;e wise man sei&thorn;.  Prouer. xxiii<SUP>o</SUP>.  'Noli subtrahere
<PB N="95">|a puero disciplinam. si enim percusseris eum virga non|morietur/ tu virga percutis eum &amp; animam eius de inferno|liberabis'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Prov. xxiii. 13.</NOTE>/ &thorn;at is to seie.  'Nile &thorn;ou wi&thorn;drawe&meper; teching from &thorn;i|childe/ for &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ou bete him wi&thorn; a &yogh;eerde&meper; he schal not die|&thorn;erou<NOTE PLACE="foot"> = ? &thorn;erof &thorn;ou&yogh;.</NOTE>/ | &thorn;ou beetist him wi&thorn; a baleys&meper; &amp; &thorn;ou schalt delyuer his <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="89a">|soule from helle/<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Wile thou not withdrawe fro a childe discipline; if forsothe thou|smyte hym with &yogh;erde, he shal not die.  Thou with a &yogh;erde smite hym, and|the soule of hym fro helle thou shalt deliveren.'  1388, 'Nile thou withdrawe|chastisyng fro a child; for thou&yogh; thou smyte hym with a &yogh;erde, he schal not|die.  Thou schalt smyte hym with a &yogh;erde, and thou schalt delyuere his soule|fro helle.'</NOTE> he &thorn;at spari&thorn; &thorn;is balys&meper; hati&thorn; his childe/|forso&thorn;e he &thorn;at loue&thorn; him&meper; wole teche him bisili/ for a wise childe|gladi&thorn; his fadir&meper; forso&thorn;e a foltid childe is &thorn;e sorow of his|modir &Verbar;</P>
<P>A&yogh;en &thorn;is comaundement&meper; &thorn;e fende wi&thorn; hise membris/ what wi&thorn;|ypocrisie&meper; &thorn;at is feyned hoolines/ what wi&thorn; blynd pite&meper; &thorn;at|regne&thorn; in &thorn;e seculeris/ he ha&thorn; encombrid Cristis chirche&meper; wi&thorn;|miche worldli muk/ &amp; ouerladde oure modir&meper; wi&thorn; temperal possessioun/|&thorn;at sche mai not rise&meper; to heuenli contemplacioun/ &thorn;erfore|hir owene children&meper; waxen wilde &amp; wantoune/ &amp; wole no&thorn;ir take|awe ne lawe&meper; alas &thorn;is is greet sorow/ but oure fadir &thorn;at is in|heuene&meper; to whom no &thorn;ing is hid/ seing hise sones frowardnes&meper; is|sterid al to wra&thorn;&thorn;e/ &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;at he abide long&meper; &amp; differre his|veniaunce/ suffring from dai to dai&meper; if &thorn;at &thorn;ei wolde amende/ For|he forbadde to prestis&meper; of &thorn;e oolde lawe/ to take suche possessioun&meper;|among &thorn;e o&thorn;ir tribis/ but holde hem paied of | his part&meper; for he <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="89b">|wolde be her eritage/ for &thorn;ei schulde prynte &thorn;is lore&meper; &amp; neuir go|&thorn;erfro/ &thorn;rise it is rehersid&meper; &thorn;ou&yogh; oones my&yogh;t haue suffisid &Verbar; Firste|in &thorn;e book of Numeri. xviii<SUP>o</SUP>.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Num. xviii. 20-4.</NOTE>/ &THORN;e secounde in Deuto. xviii<SUP>o</SUP>.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Deut. xviii. 1, 2.</NOTE>/ &THORN;e|&thorn;ridde in Ezechiel. xliiii<SUP>o</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ezech. xliv. 28.</NOTE>/  And Crist in his gospel&meper; twise forbedi&thorn;|hise prestis/ to haue &thorn;is temperal lordschip&meper; &amp; regne as|worldli kyngis &Verbar; Oones in his worching&meper; for he forsok it him silf/|Ion. vi<SUP>o</SUP>.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Joh. vi. 15.</NOTE>/ and also in his teching&meper; &thorn;at enemyes schulden not|seie/ who mai lyue as Crist dide? &amp; ne&thorn;les Gregor sei&thorn;/ Gregor.|om. xvii/ 'Dominus Iesu Christus aliquando nos sermonibus|ammonet aliquando operibus ipsa etenim facta eius precepta sunt
<PB N="96">|quia dum taciter aliquid facit quid agere debeamus innotescit'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Gregorius Magnus, <I>Homilia XVII</I> 1 (Migne, tom. 76, col. 1139).</NOTE> &Verbar;|&THORN;at is to seie.  Oure Lord Iesu Crist sumtyme wi&thorn; wordis sumtyme|wi&thorn; dedis techi&thorn; vs/ forso&thorn;e hise dedis ben comaundementis/ for|whanne he doi&thorn; ony &thorn;ing stilli&meper; in &thorn;at he maki&thorn; knowen to vs.|what we schal do/ and notwi&thorn;standing.  Crist forbedi&thorn; suche|possessioun&meper; bi word to hise prestis/ Mat. xx<SUP>o</SUP>/ Mar. x<SUP>o</SUP>/ Luk.<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="90a">| xxii<SUP>o</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. xx. 25-7; Marc. x. 42-4; Luc. xxii. 25, 26.</NOTE> &Verbar; | And if enemyes wollen not accept&meper; God in hise bo&thorn;e|lawes/ nei&thorn;ir obeie to her fadir&meper; for his worde ne for his dede/ to|whom heuene. helle. &amp; er&thorn;e&meper; kneelen on her knees/ but stonden|stille obstinat&meper; as yuel-willi traitours/ to clense her modir holi|chirche&meper; of &thorn;is foule corrupcioun/ &thorn;anne schullen we leie for&thorn;e holi|seyntis&meper; &thorn;at speken of &thorn;is mater/ &amp; saie for &thorn;ei wole acorde&meper; to|wordis &thorn;at &thorn;ei han seide/ and so rise vp to Goddis word&meper; bi &thorn;ise|seintis teching &Verbar;  Seint Austin sei&thorn;. 'Non debet ecclesia suscipere|que filio exheredato sibi offerunt. verum quicumque uult exheredato|filio. heredem facere ecclesiam querat alterum qui suscipiat.  non|Augustinum . ymmo deo propicio&meper; neminem inueniet'/  Hec|Augustinus in sermone de vita clericorum &amp; xvii. q. iiii<SUP>o</SUP>. finali<NOTE PLACE="foot">St. Augustinus, <I>De Vita Clericorum</I>, Sermo II (Gratian, <I>Decreti</I> Pars|Secunda, c. xvii, q. iv, cap. xliii (Migne, tom. 187, col. 1077-88).</NOTE> &Verbar;|&THORN;at is to seie.  &THORN;e chirche owi&thorn; not&meper; to take &thorn;oo &thorn;ingis/ &thorn;at ben|profrid to hir&meper; of hem &thorn;at ha&thorn; no eire/ &thorn;erfore who &thorn;at euer wile&meper;|make &thorn;e chirche his eire/ seeke ano&thorn;ir &thorn;at mai take it&meper; but on|nowise Austin/ but bi &thorn;e mercy of God&meper; he schal fynde no man &Verbar;<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="90b">| And Ierom sei&thorn;/ | 'Ex quo ecclesia creuit in possessionibus&meper;|decreuit in virtutibus' &Verbar; Fro &thorn;at tyme &thorn;at &thorn;e chirche&meper; grew in|possessiouns. sche ha&thorn; lessid or dwyned in vertues &Verbar; Seint Bernard|forbedi&thorn; &thorn;ise possessiouns&meper; to be in prestis handis/ &amp; speki&thorn; to|Eugeny &thorn;e pope&meper; in &thorn;ise witti wordis/  li<SUP>o</SUP>. ii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Esto ut alia|ratione hec tibi vendices/ sed non apostolico iure/ Quomodo potuit|iste tibi dare quod non habuerit&meper; quod habuit hoc dedit solicitudinem|super ecclesias . Numquid dominacionem&meper; audi ipsum neque|dominantes inquit in clero/ sed forma facti gregi/ Et ne dicui sola|humilitate putes &amp; non veritate. vox domini est in euangelio/|reges gencium dominantur eorum&meper; vos autem non sic'<NOTE PLACE="foot">St. Bernard, <I>De Consideratione,</I> Liber II, p. 1528 (<I>D. Bernardi Opera|Omnia</I>, ed. 1552).</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;at is
<PB N="97">|to seie.  Chalenge &thorn;ou &thorn;ise possessiouns&meper; bi ano&thorn;ir resoun/ but|&thorn;ou maist not chalenge hem&meper; bi &thorn;e apostlis ri&yogh;t/ Hou mi&yogh;t &thorn;e|apostle &yogh;yue&meper; &thorn;at he had not? &thorn;at he hadde &thorn;at he &yogh;aue&meper; bisines|vpon chirchis/ No whe&thorn;ir seculere lordschip? heere what he sei&thorn;/|nei&thorn;ir lording in &thorn;e clergie&meper; but mad in forme. to profite of &thorn;e|flok/ &amp; not oonli in mekenes&meper; trowe &thorn;ou &thorn;is to be seid/ | But also <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="91a">|in trou&thorn;e of dede&meper; as Crist sei&thorn; in his gospel/ 'kyngis of er&thorn;e|lorden ouer hem&meper; forso&thorn;e &yogh;e not so' &Verbar; It is pleyn to &thorn;e apostlis|&thorn;is lordschip is entirdi&yogh;tid/ hou darst &thorn;ou &thorn;anne take &thorn;is lordschip|vpon &thorn;ee/ ei&thorn;ir lording apostilhed. ei&thorn;ir apostilhed to lordschip?|pleynli &thorn;ou art forboden &thorn;e tone/ for if &thorn;ou wilt haue bo&thorn;e&meper; &thorn;ou|schalt leese bo&thorn;e/ &thorn;at is to seie. &thorn;i presthod &amp; &thorn;i lordschip/ or|ellis &thorn;ou schalt not be except of &thorn;is noumbre&meper; of &thorn;e whiche God|pleyne&thorn; him &Verbar;  &THORN;ei han regned&meper; but not bi me/ &thorn;ey han ben|princis&meper; but I haue not knowen hem/ Now if it availe to regne|wi&thorn;outen God&meper; &thorn;anne hast &thorn;ou ioye&meper; but not anentis God &Verbar; And|whane prestis holden &thorn;is entirdi&yogh;ting&meper; heere &thorn;ei &thorn;anne &thorn;e Lordis|cry/ 'He &thorn;at is more among &yogh;ou&meper; be he made as &thorn;e &yogh;onger/ and|he &thorn;at is made &thorn;e foregoer&meper; be he mad as &thorn;e mynystir'<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V.  Luc. xxii. 26, He that is the more in &yogh;ou, be maad as the|&yogh;ongere, and he that is bifore goer, as a seruaunt.'  1388, 'He that is grettist|among &yogh;ou, be maad as &yogh;ongere, and he that is bifor goere,