<PB N="100">A&yogh;en &thorn;is comaundement&meper; &thorn;e fende in his membris/ setti&thorn;|wacche &amp; bisie spie&meper; where &thorn;at he may fynde/ ony peple &thorn;at wole|rede&meper; priue or apert/ Goddis lawe in englische&meper; &thorn;at is oure|modir tunge/ ancon he schal be sumned&meper; to come aforne hise iuggis/|to answere what is seide to him&meper; &amp; bring his book wi&thorn; him/ and|ei&thorn;ir he must forsake his book&meper; &amp; reding of englische/ &amp; algatis|he schal forswere&meper; to speke of holi writ &Verbar;  &THORN;ei sein lyue as &thorn;i|fadir dide&meper; &amp; &thorn;at is ynow for &thorn;ee/ or ellis &thorn;ou schalt to prisoun&meper;|as if &thorn;ou were an heretike/ &amp; suffre peynes many &amp; strong&meper; &amp; ful|lickli &thorn;e dee&thorn;/ but &thorn;ou wilt revoke &thorn;i worde&meper; &amp; make an open|wondirment/ at &thorn;i parische chirche at home&meper; or in comune place &Verbar;<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="94a">| And wi&thorn; &thorn;is &thorn;ei prisoun&meper; many an | houngry soule/ wherof|growi&thorn; in &thorn;is rewme&meper; a greuouse goostli moreyn &Verbar;  For who dar|now in &thorn;ise daies&meper; talke of Crist or &thorn;e doom/ &amp; certis &thorn;e bodi|may not lyue&meper; wi&thorn;outen bodili food/ no more may &thorn;e celi soule&meper;|wi&thorn;outen Goddis worde/ as seint Austin sei&thorn;. 'Perit anima fame&meper;|si non pascitur celesti pane'/ &THORN;e soule die&thorn; for hungir&meper; but if it|be fedde wi&thorn; heuenli breed/ and &thorn;is breed is Goddis worde&meper; as|Crist sei&thorn; in his gospel/  Mat. iiii<SUP>o</SUP>.  Deuto. iiii<SUP>o</SUP>.  Mar. i<SUP>o</SUP>.|Luk. iiii<SUP>o</SUP>.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. iv. 4, Deut. viii. 3, (Marc. i. 13), Luc. iv. 4.</NOTE>/  'Non in solo<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. sole.</NOTE> pane viuit homo&meper; sed de omni verbo|quod procedit de ore dei'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. iv. 4 'Non in solo pane vivit homo: sed in omni verbo,' etc.</NOTE>/  A man lyue&thorn; not oonli in bodili|breed&meper; but he lyue&thorn; a betir lijf aftir &thorn;e soule/ of iche worde &thorn;at|passi&thorn;&meper; from &thorn;e mou&thorn;e of God<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'A man lyueth not in breed aloon, bot in euery word that cometh|forth fro the mouthe of God.'  1388, 'Not oonli in breed lyueth man, but in|ech word that cometh of Goddis mouth.'</NOTE> &Verbar;  God tolde long aforn&meper; &thorn;is|houngir for to come/ &thorn;at vntau&yogh;t men schulde aske &thorn;is breed&meper;|&amp; no man schulde &yogh;yue it hem/ as he sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e mou&thorn;e of &thorn;e|prophete Amos. viii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Ecce dies veniunt dicit dominus &amp; mittam|famem in terram. non famem panis. neque sitim aque&meper; sed audiendi<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="94b">| verbum | domini'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Amos vii. 11.</NOTE> &Verbar;  Loo daies comen sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord&meper; &amp; I schal|suffre hungir to be sent in to &thorn;e er&thorn;e/ nei&thorn;ir of breed ne of watir&meper;|but of heeryng &thorn;e word of &thorn;e Lord/  &THORN;anne men schullen be|meved&meper; from &thorn;e ton<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. to.</NOTE> see to &thorn;e to&thorn;ir/ &amp; fro &thorn;e nor&thorn;e vnto &thorn;e|eest&meper; seeking &thorn;e worde of &thorn;e Lord/ &amp; &thorn;ei schal not fynde it&meper; sei&thorn;
<PB N="101">|&thorn;e Lord God<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Loo! the days cummen, saith the Lord, and Y shall sende out|hungre in to erthe; not hungre of breed nether thrist of water, bot of heeryng|of the word of God.  And thei shuln be moued to gydre fro see unto see, and|fro the north unto the eest thei shuln cumpasse, seekynge the word of the|Lord, and thei shuln not fynde.'</NOTE> &Verbar; for &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;er be manye precheours&meper; &thorn;er ben fewe|trewe prechours/ and if ony preche &thorn;e trou&thorn;e&meper; &thorn;e multitude schal|a&yogh;enseie him/ &amp; &thorn;us men abiden stille&meper; in her goostli hungir &Verbar;|for &thorn;ei wot neuer whom to folowe&meper; her preching is so wondirful/|ioynyng in her coriouse wordis&meper; &thorn;e trou&thorn;e to &thorn;e falsehede &Verbar; who|&thorn;at hauntri&thorn; him to &thorn;is breed&meper; for to slek his hungir/ &thorn;ou&yogh; he|were als hooli&meper; as euere was seint Ion Baptist/ he schulde not|faile to be sclaundrid&meper; for a cursid Lollard/ &amp; pursued as an|heretik&meper; of &thorn;ise cruel enemyes &Verbar; But in &thorn;is &thorn;ei ben miche werre&meper;|&thorn;an &thorn;e hee&thorn;en folkis/ &thorn;at trowen in her mawmetis&meper; | for wanting <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="95a">|of bileue/  But &thorn;ise han resceyued &thorn;e fei&thorn;&meper; &amp; falsli gon &thorn;erfro/|and also dryuen beestli men&meper; to peyne hem in her pinfold/ wi&thorn;outen|goostli mete or drinke&meper; til &thorn;ei sterue for hungir &Verbar;  But we|reeden &thorn;e contrarie&meper; of an hee&thorn;en kyng/ for he dide miche betir&meper;|to &thorn;e children of Isrel.  IIII. Re. xvii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Cumque filij Israel habitare|cepissent in Samaria. non timebant dominum &amp; immisit|dominus eis leones qui interficiebant eos'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. 4 Reg. xvii. 25 'Cumque ibi habitare coepissent, non timebant|Dominum et immisit in eos Dominus leones, qui,' etc.</NOTE>/ &THORN;at is to seie. whanne|&thorn;e children of Isrel&meper; bigunne to dwelle in Samarie/ &thorn;ei dreden|not &thorn;e Lord&meper; &amp; &thorn;e Lord sent among hem. liouns &thorn;at slow&yogh;en hem/|&amp; &thorn;anne was it tolde to &thorn;e kyng&meper; of Assiry &amp; seide/ &thorn;e folkis &thorn;at|&thorn;ou hast translatid&meper; &amp; mad hem to dwelle in &thorn;e cetees of Samarye/|&thorn;ei knowe not &thorn;e laweful &thorn;ingis&meper; of &thorn;e God of er&thorn;e/ &amp; &thorn;e Lord|ha&thorn; sent&meper; among hem lyouns/ &amp; lo &thorn;ei slen hem&meper; for as mich as|&thorn;ei knowe not/ &thorn;e ri&yogh;t or &thorn;e lawe&meper; of &thorn;e Lord God of er&thorn;e &Verbar;|Forso&thorn;e &thorn;e kyng | of Assarye&meper; comaundid seiyng/ ledi&thorn; &thorn;idir <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="95b">|oone of &thorn;e prestis&meper; &thorn;at &yogh;e han brou&yogh;t in to &thorn;is &thorn;raldom/ &thorn;at he|may go &amp; wi&thorn; hem dwelle&meper; to teche hem &thorn;e laweful &thorn;ingis. of &thorn;e|God of er&thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'And whanne there thei hadden begunne to dwellen, thei dreden|not the Lord; and the Lord sent to hem lyouns, that slewen hem.  And it is told|to the kyng of Assiries, and seide, The folc that thou hast translatyde and|maad to dwellen in the cytees of Samarye, knowen not the lawful thingis of|the God of the lond; and the Lord sente in to hem lyouns, and loo! thei|shuln slen hem; for thy that thei knowen not the custum of the God of the|lond.  The kyng forsothe of Assiries comaundyde, seyinge, Bringith hidre oon|of the prestis, the whiche in to caytyfte &yogh;e han brou&yogh;t, that he goo, and dwelle|with hem, and teche hem the lawful thingis of God of the lond.'  1388, 'And|whanne thei bigunnen to dwelle there, thei dredden not the Lord; and the|Lord sente to hem liouns, that killiden hem.  And it was teld to the kyng of|Assiriens, and was seid, The folkis whiche thou translatidist, and madist to|dwelle in the cities of Samarie, kunnen not the lawful thingis of God of the|lond; and the Lord sente liouns in to hem, and lo! liouns sleen hem; for thei|kunnen not the custom of God of the lond.  Sotheli the kyng of Assiriens|comaundide, and seide, Lede &yogh;e thidur oon of the prestis, whiche &yogh;e brou&yogh;ten|prisoneris fro thennus, that he go, and dwelle with hem, and teche hem the|lawful thingis of God of the lond.'</NOTE> &Verbar;  God graunt oure cristen kyngis&meper; to mark wel
<PB N="102">|&thorn;is story/ &thorn;at &thorn;ei mowe passe &thorn;is hee&thorn;en kyng&meper; in &thorn;is forseide|mater/ &thorn;anne schulde lyouns &thorn;at ben synnes&meper; soone be distried/|if alle men hadden &thorn;e lawe&meper; writen in her hertis/ as &thorn;e Lord|sei&thorn;. Iere. xxxi<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Dabo legem meam in visceribus eorum&meper; &amp; in|corde eorum scribam eam'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Jer. xxxi. 33.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;at is to seie.  I schal &yogh;yue my|lawe&meper; in &thorn;e bowels of hem/ &amp; I schal write my lawe&meper; in &thorn;e herte|of hem<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Y shal &yogh;yue my lawe in the boweles of hem, and in the herte of|hem Y shal write it.'  1388, 'Y schal &yogh;yue my lawe in the entrails of hem,|and Y schal write it in the herte of hem.'</NOTE>/ O. &yogh;e prestis ben myche to blame&meper; &thorn;at taken from &thorn;e|peple/ &thorn;e lawe &thorn;at God ha&thorn; writen him silf&meper; in myddis of her|herte/ so &thorn;oru&yogh; &yogh;ou &thorn;ise forseide lyouns&meper; now ben comen among|vs/ &thorn;at al to-teeren Cristis scheep&meper; &amp; mur&thorn;eren hem to &thorn;e dee&thorn;/|certis &yogh;e lerned neuir &thorn;is loore&meper; in dedis of &thorn;e apostlis/ for &thorn;us|it is writen. Actus, viii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Et ecce vir ethiops. eunuchus &amp;c.;'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Act. viii. 27.</NOTE>/<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="96a">| Loo | a clene chaast man&meper; &thorn;e quenes tresourer of Ynde/ &thorn;ou&yogh; he|were an hee&thorn;en man&meper; and hadde not taken &thorn;e fei&thorn;/ &yogh;it he radde|in Isaie&meper; sitting in his chaare/  Philip took not awey his booke&meper;|ne werned him to reede &thorn;eronne/  But what &thorn;anne?  Philip|declarid him prophecie&meper; &amp; tau&yogh;t him for to vndirstonde it/ til he|bileued Iesu Crist&meper; to be Goddis son of heuene/ what bitidde|&thorn;anne?  Philip bi stiring of &thorn;e spirit&meper; whanne &thorn;is man bileued/|confermed him in Cristis name&meper; &amp; &yogh;aue to him &thorn;e bapteme/  How|do &yogh;e prestis&meper; performe &thorn;e apostlis lore/ &thorn;at stoppen trewe cristen|men&meper; from werkis of her cristendom / &THORN;e apostlis vsid not &thorn;at|maner&meper; whanne &thorn;ei wenten aboute/ to &thorn;e temple &amp; mennes|housis&meper; preching &amp; techyng/ bo&thorn;e to Iewis &amp; hee&thorn;en men&meper; &thorn;e|lawis of Iesu Crist/  Actus. v<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Omni autem die in templo &amp; circa
<PB N="103">|domos non cessabant&meper; docentes &amp; euangelizantes christum Iesum'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Act. v. 42.</NOTE>/|&THORN;at is to seie.  Forso&thorn;e iche dai in &thorn;e temple &amp; aboute housis&meper;|&thorn;ei ceessid not teching | and preching Crist Iesu<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Forsoth ech day thei ceesiden not in the temple, and aboute|housis, techinge and evangelisynge Jhesu Christ.'</NOTE> &Verbar; <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="96b"></P></DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="commandment" N="6">
<HEAD>&THORN;e sixte heeste &Verbar;</HEAD>
<P>The sixte comaundement of God is &thorn;is. Exo. xx<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Non mechaberis'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ex. xx. 14.</NOTE>&Verbar;| &thorn;ou schalt not do leccherie/ Nei&thorn;ir wi&thorn; &thorn;in i&yogh;e&meper; in|leccherouse lookyng/ Nei&thorn;ir wi&thorn; &thorn;in herte&meper; in lusti &thorn;enkyng/|Nei&thorn;ir wi&thorn; &thorn;i bodi&meper; in &thorn;e dede doinge/ and &thorn;us &thorn;is synne is|forbeden&meper; in sengle. in weddid. &amp; in widowis &Verbar;</P>
<P>Of &thorn;e firste speki&thorn; seynt Austin &amp; sei&thorn;. 'Inpudicus oculus|inpudici cordis est nuncius'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Augustinus, <I>Epistola CCXI</I> 10 (Migne, tom. 33, col. 961).</NOTE> &Verbar;  An vnchaast i&yogh;e&meper; is messagere of|an vnchaast herte &Verbar;</P>
<P>Of &thorn;e secounde speki&thorn; Crist in his gospel. Mat. v<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Qui viderit|mulierem ad concupiscendum eam iam mechatus est eam in corde|suo'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. v. 28.</NOTE>/ &THORN;at is to seie. who &thorn;at ha&thorn; seen a womman to do his lust|wi&thorn; hir&meper; anoon he ha&thorn; done leccherie wi&thorn; hir in his hert/<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Every man that seeth a womman for to coueite hire, now he hath|do lecherie by hire in his herte.'</NOTE>  In|&thorn;is Crist techi&thorn;. hou &thorn;e roote of synne springe&thorn; from &thorn;e herte/</P>
<P>Of &thorn;e &thorn;ridde speki&thorn; Poul. Ephe. v<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Hoc enim scitote intelligentes|quod omnis fornicator aut immundus aut avarus quod est|ydolorum seruitus non habet hereditatem in regno dei &amp; christi'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Eph. v. 5.</NOTE>/|Forso&thorn;e knowe | &yogh;e &thorn;is vndirstonding. &thorn;at nei&thorn;ir fornicarer nei&thorn;ir <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="97a">|vnclene fil&thorn;e. nei&thorn;ir avarouse wrecche. &thorn;at is seruage of ydols ha&thorn;|no heritage in &thorn;e rewme of Crist &amp; God/<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Forsoth this thing wyte &yogh;e, undirstondinge that ech fornycatour,|or unclene man, or coueytous, that is seruage of ydols, (or mawmetis), hath|not heritage in the kingdom of Christ and God.'  1388, 'For wite &yogh;e this, and|undurstonde, that ech letchour, or unclene man, or coueytouse, that serveth to|mawmetis, hath not eritage in the kingdom of Christ and of God.'</NOTE>  Hou euer &thorn;ou lustily|treete&meper; &thorn;e membris of &thorn;i bodi/ a&yogh;ens &thorn;e resoun of &thorn;i soule&meper; &thorn;anne|&thorn;ou art a lecchour/ and &thorn;erfore schulde bo&thorn;e man &amp; womman&meper;|lerne to kepe her bodi/ in clennes &amp; in vertu&meper; to worschip of her
<PB N="104">|God/ &amp; not in foule brennyng desiris&meper; as folkis &thorn;at knowi&thorn; no|resun/ as seint Austin sei&thorn;. 'Dedit tibi deus potestatem per|spiritum sanctum. ut membra tua teneas/ surgit libido&meper; tene tu|membra/ noli exhibere membra tua. arma iniquitatis peccato/ noli|armare aduersarium tuum contra te/ tene pedes. ne eant ad illicita/|libido surrexit&meper; tene tu membra/ tene manus ab omni|scelere/ tene oculos. ne male attendant/ tene aures&meper; ne verba|libidinis libenter audiant/ tene totum corpus tuum/ tene latera.|tene summa/ tene yma/ Quid facit libido? surgere nouit. vincere|non nouit'/  Hec Augustinus de verbis domini. sermone XLIII.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Augustinus, <I>Sermo CXXVIII</I>, cap. x (Migne, tom. 38, col. 719).</NOTE><MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="97b">| God ha&thorn; &yogh;yuen to &thorn;ee | powere&meper; bi &thorn;e Holi Goost/ &thorn;at &thorn;ou holde|&thorn;i membris&meper; from passing of resoun/ luste risi&thorn;&meper; holde &thorn;ou &thorn;i|membris/ nile &thorn;ou &yogh;yue &thorn;i membris armour of wickidnes to synne/|arme not &thorn;in aduersarie a&yogh;ens &thorn;ee&meper; to &thorn;in owene harme/  Holde|&thorn;i feet&meper; &thorn;at &thorn;ei go not to vnleful &thorn;ingis/  Lust ha&thorn; risen&meper; wi&thorn;holde|&thorn;ou &thorn;i membris/ holde &thorn;in handis. from alle felonye/ wi&thorn;holde|&thorn;in i&yogh;en. &thorn;at &thorn;ei tent not to yuel/ wi&thorn;holde &thorn;yn eeris&meper; &thorn;at &thorn;ei|heere not &thorn;e talis of leccherie/ wi&thorn;holde al &thorn;i bodi/ holde &thorn;i|si&yogh;dis/ holde hi&yogh;e/ holde lowe/ what can lust do? rise it can&meper;|ouercum can it not &Verbar;</P>
<P>A&yogh;en &thorn;is comaundement&meper; &thorn;e fende in hise membris/ holdi&thorn;|a court as he sei&thorn;&meper; of holi chirchis lawe/ from oo weeke to|a no&thorn;ir&meper; for to correct synnars/ and &thorn;ere &thorn;ei clepen bi name&meper; &thorn;e|lecchour &amp; his feere/ &thorn;at ledi&thorn; &thorn;e lijf in hoordam&meper; to ioyne hem|to her penaunce/ &thorn;at is to walke &thorn;re market daies&meper; aboute &thorn;e|comune market/ bareheed in her schirt&meper; wi&thorn;outen hosen or<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="98a">| schoon/ &amp; o&thorn;ir &thorn;re sundaies&meper; aboute her pa-|-rische chirche/ wi&thorn;|a tapir in her hond&meper; of a pound of wax/ &amp; go biforn &thorn;e parische|prest&meper; to bete hem wi&thorn; a &yogh;erde/  Also stonding on her feet&meper; til|&thorn;e messe be seide/ &amp; &thorn;anne offre vp her candils&meper; to &thorn;e hi&yogh;e auter/|&THORN;e sumnour is ful bisi&meper; in al &thorn;is mene tyme/ to rowne in her|eeris&meper; &amp; bidde hem aske grace/ 'for &yogh;e schal haue betir grace&meper;|do bi my counseile/  Paie doun money from &yogh;oure purse&meper; to my|lordis almes/ &amp; &yogh;e schullen fynde him graciouse&meper; to relese &yogh;oure|penaunce'/  &THORN;anne &thorn;ei take her leeue bo&thorn;e&meper; whanne &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben|taxid/ to contynue stille in hordam&meper; as &thorn;ei diden biforn/ &yogh;he|summe til her dee&thorn; dai&meper; so &thorn;at &thorn;is rent be paied/  Certis &thorn;is is
<PB N="105">|a cursid synne&meper; &thorn;at oure bischopis vsen/ to maynten lecchours|in her owene hous&meper; &amp; make hem her ordinarijs/ &thorn;at laten synne|to greet hire&meper; for her lordis almes &Verbar;  Heere &yogh;e what God sei&thorn; to|&yogh;ou.  Eze. xliiii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Sufficiant vobis omnia scelera uestra domus|Israel eo quod inducitis filios alienos incircumcisos corde &amp; incircumcisos&Verbar; carne/ ut sint in sanctuario meo. &amp; polluant domum <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="98b">|meam &amp; offertis panes meos adipem &amp; sanguinem/  Et dissoluistis|pactum meum in omnibus sceleribus uestris. &amp; non seruastis precepta|sanctuarij mei. &amp; posuistis custodes obseruacionum mearum|in sanctuario meo vobismetipsis. hec dicit dominus'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ezech. xliv. 6-9.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;at is to|seie.  Suffice &thorn;ei to &yogh;ou&meper; hous of Isrel/ alle &yogh;oure greet felonyes&meper;|&thorn;at &yogh;e vsen among &yogh;ou/ bicause &thorn;at &yogh;e bringen in&meper; alien sones/|vncircumcisid in her herte&meper; &amp; in her fleische also/ &thorn;at &thorn;ei be in|my sauntwary&meper; &amp; defoyle my hous/ and &yogh;e offren my looues&meper; my|blood &amp; my grece/ but &yogh;e vndo my couenaunt&meper; in alle &yogh;oure foule|felonyes/ &amp; &yogh;e han not kept in dede&meper; &thorn;e biddingis of my sauntwary/|but &yogh;e han sette &thorn;e wardeynes&meper; of myn obseruauncis/ in|my sauntwarie&meper; to &yogh;oure owene avauntage/  &THORN;ise &thorn;ingis sei&thorn; &thorn;e|Lord God<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. '&yogh;e hous of Yrael, alle &yogh;our grete trespassis suffice thei to &yogh;ou,|for that that &yogh;e bryng yn alyen sonys, uncircumcided in hert, and uncircumcided|in flesh, that thei be in my sayntuarie, and defoule myn hous.  And|&yogh;e offren my louys, fatnesse and bloode, and &yogh;e undo my couenaunt in alle|&yogh;our grete trespassis.  And &yogh;e kepte not the preceptis of my sayntuarie and &yogh;e|han putte keepers of myn obseruances, in my sayntuarie to &yogh;our self.  These|thingus saith the Lord God.'  1388, '&yogh;e hous of Israel, alle &yogh;oure grete|trespassis... And &yogh;e kepten not the comaundementis of my seyntuarie, and|&yogh;e settiden keperis of my kepyngis in my seyntuarije to &yogh;ou silf.  The Lord God|seith these thingis.'</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;is is &thorn;e moral witt&meper; of &thorn;is forseid sentence/ hi&yogh;e|prelatis of &thorn;e chirche&meper; schulde &thorn;enk ynowe/ of her owene greet|synnes&meper; for to &yogh;yue a rekenyng | aforn God at domesdai&meper; &amp; &thorn;ei <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="99a">|wolde wel avise hem/ &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei dide not sacre&meper; to &thorn;e ordir of|presthood/ vnclene men in bodi &amp; soule&meper; &thorn;at seken to be prestis/|nei&thorn;ir in vertu ne in spirit&meper; but for to lyue in lustis/  &THORN;ise|poluten Cristis chirche&meper; his fleische &amp; his blood/ &amp; causen whi|&thorn;at Goddis lawe&meper; for her false court/ Not cristen lawe. but cursid|lawe&meper; is holden among &thorn;e peple/  &THORN;is was not her couenaunt&meper; at|oo daies tyme/ whanne &thorn;ei hi&yogh;ten fei&thorn; &amp; trou&thorn;e&meper; to swe Cristis|steppis/ &amp; kepe hise biddingis in hem silf&meper; &amp; teche hem o&thorn;ir
<PB N="106">|men &Verbar;  But now &thorn;ei setten ordinarijs&meper; for her worldly profite/|&thorn;at heepen her purs wi&thorn; money&meper; of many soold synnes/  But|soulis &thorn;at God chargi&thorn; hem wi&thorn;&meper; to haue cure ouer hem/ and|bring to &thorn;e blisse of heuene&meper; as scheep vnto &thorn;e foold/ &thorn;ei charge|not whe&thorn;ir &thorn;ei synk or swyme&meper; so &thorn;ei moun regne as lordis/  &THORN;us|ben alle &thorn;re astaatis&meper; enfectid in leccherie/ fro &thorn;e lewid man to|&thorn;e clerk&meper; and noon amenden o&thorn;ir/ and &thorn;erfore &thorn;e Lord sei&thorn;. |<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="99b">| Iere. v. 'Saturaui eos &amp; mechati sunt &amp; in domo meretricis|luxuriabantur/ Equi amatores in feminas &amp; emissarij facti sunt|vnusquisque ad vxorem proximi sui hinniebat<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. inhiebat.</NOTE>/  Numquid super|hijs visitabo dicit dominus &amp; in gente<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. genti.</NOTE> tali vlciscetur anima|mea'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Jer. v. 7-9 'Saturavi eos ... Equi amatores et emissarii ...|Numquid super hiis non visitabo dicit dominus, et in gente tali non,' etc.</NOTE>/  I haue fedde hem&meper; &amp; &thorn;ei han don leccherie/ &thorn;ei han ben|horrels&meper; in &thorn;e comune bordel hous/ &thorn;ei ben as feers on wymmen&meper;|as hors ben on maris/ &amp; &thorn;ei ben made stalowens&meper; &thorn;at seruen of|&thorn;at office/ iche man waxi&thorn; wood<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. waxi&thorn; waxi&thorn; wood.</NOTE>&meper; aftir his nei&yogh;bours wijf/ vpon|&thorn;ise &thorn;ingis I schal visite&meper; sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord God/ and vpon &thorn;is folk|I schal venge my wille&meper; sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord God<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'I fulfilde them, and thei diden fornycacioun, and in the hous of|the strumpet thei diden leccherie.  Horses loueres in to wymmen, and|courseres thei ben mad; eche to the wif of his ne&yogh;hebore ney&yogh;ede.  Whether|upon these thingus Y shal not visite, seith the Lord, and in such a folc of|kynde shal not be vengid my soule?'  1388, 'Y fillide hem, and thei diden|awowtrie, and in the hous of an hoore thei diden letcherie.  Then ben maad|horsis, and stalouns, louyeris to wymmen; ech man nei&yogh;ede to the wijf of his|nei&yogh;bore.  Whether Y schal not visite on these thingis, seith the Lord, and|schal not my soule take veniaunce in siche a folc.'</NOTE> &Verbar;</P></DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="commandment" N="7">
<HEAD>&THORN;e .VII. heeste &Verbar;</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;e seuen&thorn;e comaundement of God is &thorn;is.  Exo. xx<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Non|furtum facies'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ex. xx. 15.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;ou schalt not do &thorn;eeft/  Nei&thorn;ir kny&yogh;tis&meper; by|tirauntrie/  Nei&thorn;ir prestis bi ypocrisie/  Nei&thorn;ir comvnes bi|stel&thorn;e &amp; robry/</P>
<P>Of &thorn;e firste it is writen.  Isaie i<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Principes tui infideles|socij furum'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Isaias i. 23.</NOTE>/  &THORN;i princis ben vnfei&thorn;ful&meper; &amp; felowis of &thorn;eeues/ alle|&thorn;ei louen &yogh;iftis&meper; &thorn;ei folowen rewardingis/ &thorn;ei deeme not ri&yogh;t<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="100a">| doome&meper; | to &thorn;e modirles childe/ &thorn;e cause of &thorn;e widowe&meper; entri&thorn;|not to hem<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Thi princes unfeithfull, felawes of theues; alle thei loouen &yogh;iftus,|folewen &yogh;eldyngus; to the faderles child thei demen not; the cause of the|widewe goth not in to them.'  1388, 'Thi princes ben unfeithful, the felowis|of theuys; alle louen &yogh;iftis, suen meedis; thei demen not to a fadirles child,|and the cause of a widewe entrith not to hem.'</NOTE>/</P>
<P>
<PB N="107">Of &thorn;e secounde speki&thorn; Crist in his gospel.  Ion. x<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Qui non|intrat per hostium in ouile ouium. sed ascendit aliunde&meper; ille fur|est &amp; latro'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Joh. x. 1.</NOTE>/  He &thorn;at entri&thorn; not bi &thorn;e dore&meper; in to &thorn;e foold of|scheep/ but come&thorn; in bi ano&thorn;ir weye&meper; he is a ny&yogh;t-&thorn;eef &amp; a day&thorn;eef<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'He that cometh not in by the dore in to the fold of the sheep, but|sti&yogh;eth up by another weye, is ny&yogh;t thef and day thef.'</NOTE>/|&thorn;is is expouned in &thorn;e &thorn;ridde comaundement &Verbar;</P>
