<P>A&yogh;en &thorn;is comaundement&meper; &thorn;e fende wi&thorn; his cautels/ ha&thorn; whilid<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="101a">| in to | &thorn;e chirche&meper; many strong &thorn;eeues/ &thorn;at don steele bo&thorn;e ny&yogh;t|&amp; dai&meper; &amp; &yogh;it &thorn;ei ben not hangid &Verbar;  But God ha&thorn; ordeyned for|hem&meper; gallous in helle/ &amp; &thorn;ei &thorn;at &thorn;ere ben oones hangid&meper; schal|neuere be delyuered &Verbar;  But &thorn;ei &thorn;at hangen on mannes gallows&meper; bi|iugement of &thorn;is world/ often bi &thorn;is schameful dee&thorn;&meper; &amp; by verry|repentaunce/ ben saued from &thorn;e endeles peyne&meper; &amp; so was &thorn;e &thorn;eef/|&thorn;at hangid on Cristis ri&yogh;t si&yogh;de&meper; in tyme of his passioun &Verbar;  But|&thorn;ei &thorn;at fallen bakwarde&meper; &amp; may not se her fal/  &thorn;ei hang on|Cristis left si&yogh;de&meper; in perel of her soule/ from whom Crist turne&thorn;|his graciouse face&meper; as &thorn;e prophete sei&thorn;/ spekyng wi&thorn; &thorn;e mou&thorn;e|of God&meper; to &thorn;ise forseide &thorn;eeues/ Isaye. lix<SUP>o</SUP>./ 'Iniquitates vestre|diuiserunt inter vos &amp; dominum vestrum &amp; peccata vestra absconderunt|faciem eius a vobis. ne exaudiret. manus enim vestre plene|sunt sanguine &amp; digiti vestri iniquitate<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. iniquitat&emacr;.</NOTE>.  labia vestra locuta sunt|mendacium. &amp; lingua vestra iniquitatem fatur'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Isaias lix. 2, 3.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &YOGH;oure wickidnes|ha&thorn; made a deuorse&meper; bitwixe &thorn;e Lord &amp; &yogh;ou/ &amp; &yogh;oure synnes han<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="101b">| hidde | awey&meper; his graciouse face from &yogh;ou/ &thorn;at he schulde not|heere &yogh;ou&meper; whanne &yogh;e crien vpon him/ forso&thorn;e &yogh;oure handis ben|ful of blood&meper; &amp; &yogh;oure fyngers ful of synne/ &yogh;oure lippis han spoken|lesing&meper; &amp; &yogh;oure tung speki&thorn; wickidnes &Verbar;<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. '&yogh;oure wickidnesses deuydeden betwe &yogh;ou and &yogh;oure God, and|&yogh;oure synnes hidden his face fro &yogh;ou, that he ful out here not.  Fosothe &yogh;oure|hondis ben defoulid with blod, and &yogh;oure fingris with wickidnesse; &yogh;oure lippes|speeken lesing and &yogh;oure tunge wickenesse speketh.'  1388, '&YOGH;oure wickidnesses|han departid bitwixe &yogh;ou and &yogh;oure God, and &yogh;oure synnes han hid his|face fro &yogh;ou, that he shulde not here.  For whi &yogh;oure hondis ben defoulid with|blood, and &yogh;oure fingris with wickidnesse; &yogh;oure lippis spaken leesyng, and|&yogh;oure tunge spekith wickidnesse.'</NOTE>  &THORN;e face of God is here
<PB N="109">|taken&meper; for his grace in mannes mynde/  In ano&thorn;ir place it is|taken&meper; for Cristis incarnacioun &Verbar; and in ano&thorn;ir place it is taken&meper;|for &thorn;e glorie of God. in his euerlasting maieste/  And &thorn;ise &thorn;re|ben turned awey&meper; from &thorn;ise forseide spoylours/ &amp; cause whi &thorn;e|prophete sei&thorn;. ben &thorn;ise twoo &thorn;ingis/  Her handis &amp; her fyngeris&meper;|ben ful of blood and wickidnes &Verbar; vpon &thorn;is sei&thorn; Parsiens/ 'Qui|aut furto aut vi aut fraude possidet vnde pauperes ali deberent&meper;|pauperum sanguine manus habet pollutas'/  Who &thorn;at ha&thorn; ei&thorn;ir|bi &thorn;eeft as robrie. ei&thorn;ir bi streng&thorn;e. as tirauntrie. ei&thorn;ir bi fraude|or gile as ypocrisie. &thorn;o &thorn;ingis of &thorn;e whiche &thorn;e pore owid to be|norischid. he ha&thorn; his handis pollutid. in &thorn;ore mennes blood/ and|who &thorn;at clo&thorn;i&thorn; him wi&thorn; suche goodis. or fedi&thorn; him wi&thorn; suche|goodis. or reri&thorn; vp bildyngis wi&thorn; suche gooten goodis&meper; &thorn;anne is &Verbar;he cladde in pore mennes blood. &thorn;anne is he fedde wi&thorn; pore mennes <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="102a">|blood. &thorn;anne grounde&thorn; he his bilding in pore mennes blood &Verbar;</P>
<P>Summe men seyn it is no synne&meper; to take what &thorn;at men wole|&yogh;yue hem/ summe seyne &thorn;ei wole spende her goodis&meper; &thorn;ere &thorn;ei|haue moost deuocioun/ summe morteisen hous. lond. watir. &|wood&meper; in to deed mennes hondis &Verbar; To &yogh;ou we asken &thorn;is questioun/|what profiti&thorn; &thorn;e hand&meper; wi&thorn;outen fyngeris/ or &thorn;e fyngers&meper; wi&thorn;outen|hand?  If &yogh;e mowen seie &thorn;at ei&thorn;ir of hem may worche his|werke wi&thorn;outen o&thorn;ir to mannes profite&meper; &thorn;anne mai &yogh;e seie &thorn;at|deuocioun mai profite wi&thorn;outen discrecioun. &amp; ellis not/ for &thorn;us|it is writen. Cant. v<SUP>o</SUP>./ 'Manus mee stillauerunt mirram. &amp; digiti|mei mirram probatissimam'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Cant. v. 5 'Manus meae stillaverunt myrrham, et digiti mei pleni|myrrha probatissima.'</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;ise ben &thorn;e wordis of a trewe|soule. myn hondis ha&thorn; droppid mirre&meper; &amp; my fingeris moost proued|mirre<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Myn hondis droppeden mirre, and my fingres ful of best proued|myrre.'  1388, 'Myn hondis droppiden myrre, and my fyngris weren ful of|myrre moost preued.'</NOTE>/ vpon &thorn;is sei&thorn; seint Bernard. 'Deuocio sine discrecione.|vacue iacet/ discrecio sine deuocione precipitat&meper; felix est cui neutra<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. veutra.</NOTE>|deest'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Bernardus, <I>Super Cantica</I>, Sermo XXIII (<I>D. Bernardi Opera Omnia</I>, ed.|1552, p. 843).</NOTE>/ | Deuocioun wi&thorn;outen discrecioun&meper; lie&thorn; voide &amp; doi&thorn; no <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="102b">
<PB N="110">|good/ discrecioun wi&thorn;outen deuocioun&meper; &thorn;rowi&thorn; doun heedlingis/|he is blessid&meper; &thorn;at wanti&thorn; nei&thorn;ir of &thorn;ise/  Loke what it profiti&thorn; to|haue Crist in manhod&meper; wi&thorn;outen his godhood? or to haue a bodi&meper;|wi&thorn;outen a soule? or to haue fei&thorn; in worde&meper; wi&thorn;outen dede? or|to haue &thorn;e letter&meper; wi&thorn;outen vndirstonding? or to haue a laump|wi&thorn;outen oyle?  So profiti&thorn; deuocioun&meper; wi&thorn;outen discrecioun/</P>
<P>Summen &yogh;it bisien hem&meper; to mayntene &thorn;is &thorn;eeft &amp; seyn/  &THORN;ise|men &thorn;at &yogh;e marken&meper; ben good prechours. &thorn;ei ben deuoute preiars&meper;|&amp; algatis amonge hem . God is faire serued &Verbar;</P>
<P>As to her preching&meper; Crist answeri&thorn; &amp; sei&thorn;.  Mat. vii<SUP>o</SUP>.  Luk.|xii<SUP>o</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. vii. 22; Luc. xiii. 25-27.</NOTE>/ 'Multi dicent mihi in illa die. Domine. Domine. nonne|in nomine tuo prophetauimus &amp; in nomine tuo demonia eiecimus|&amp; in nomine tuo virtutes multas fecimus? &amp; tunc confitebor illis|quia nunquam novi vos/ discedite a me omnes qui operamini|iniquitatem' &Verbar; Manye schal come to Crist&meper; &amp; seie to him in &thorn;e dai<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="103a">| of doome &Verbar; Lord. Lord. han not we | prechid in &thorn;i name &amp; casten|out deuelis in &thorn;i name. &amp; wrou&yogh;t many vertues in &thorn;i name/ Seint|Austin sei&thorn;. &thorn;e Lord schal not denaye &thorn;is/ for who euer &thorn;e|prechour be&meper; a deuoute heerer may wynne him mede/ but he schal|knoweleche to hem&meper; &amp; seie/ For I knew &yogh;ou neuer. &thorn;at is to seie.|I approued neuere &yogh;oure werkis&meper; goo fro me alle &yogh;e &thorn;at wirken|wickidness<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Many shul say to me in that day, Lord, Lord, whether we han|not prophecied in thi name, and han cast out deuelis in thi name, and han|don many vertues in thi name? And than Y shal knowliche to hem, For|I knewe &yogh;ou neuer: departe awey fro me, &yogh;e that worchen wickidnesse.'</NOTE>/</P>
<P>And as to her preiars.  seint Austin sei&thorn; in a book &thorn;at he|made&meper; of mounkis lijf/ It profiti&thorn; not to preie&meper; &amp; late &thorn;e lond lie|leie/</P>
<P>And as to her faire seruice&meper; it is seide aforn/ &thorn;at God is no|where faire serued&meper; but &thorn;ere as his lawe is faire kept of &thorn;e peple &Verbar;</P>
<P>But in &thorn;ise &thorn;re&meper; &thorn;ei disceyuen &thorn;e peple of her bileue/ &thorn;ei robben|hem of her vertu&meper; &amp; &thorn;ei spoylen hem of her goodis/ as it is writen.|Miche. iii<SUP>o</SUP>./ 'Hec dicit Dominus super prophetas qui seducunt|populum meum qui mordent dentibus suis &amp; predicant pacem &amp; si|quis non dederit in ore ipsorum quippiam sanctificant super eum<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="103b">| prelium propterea nox<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. vox.</NOTE> erit uobis pro visione | &amp; tenebre vobis pro
<PB N="111">|diuinacione'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Mich. iii. 5, 6.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;ise &thorn;ingis sei&thorn; &thorn;e Lord vpon prechours&meper; &thorn;at|disceyuen my peple as wi&thorn; her preching/ &thorn;at biten wi&thorn; her tee&thorn;&meper;|as for her preiyng/ &amp; prechen pees&meper; as for her faire seruyng/ and|who &thorn;at wole not &yogh;yue sumwhat&meper; in to &thorn;e mou&thorn;e of hem. &thorn;ei|halowen bataile vpon him/ &thorn;erfore &thorn;e Lord sei&thorn;.  Ni&yogh;t schal be to|&yogh;ou&meper; for &yogh;oure visioun/ &amp; dercknes&meper; for &yogh;oure diuinacioun<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'These thingus saith the Lord on the prophetis that disceyuen my|peple, &amp; biten with her teeth, and prechen pees; and &yogh;if eny man shal not|&yogh;eve in the mouth of hem enything, thei halewyn bateyle on hym.  Therefore|ni&yogh;t shal be to &yogh;ou for visioun, (or prophecie), and derknessis to &yogh;ou for|dyuynacioun.'</NOTE>/|&THORN;ise wole be meke&meper; wi&thorn;outen dispite/ pore&meper; wi&thorn;outen defau&yogh;t/|wel clad&meper; wi&thorn;outen bisines/ diligatli fedde&meper; wi&thorn;outen traueile/|whili flatirars&meper; to hem &thorn;at &thorn;ei bigilen/ yuel-willi traitours&meper; to|hem &thorn;at &thorn;ei haten/ hasti pursuars&meper; of hem &thorn;at &thorn;ei sclaundren/|soore bitars&meper; as doggis/ descyuable&meper; as foxis/ proude&meper; as lyouns/|enviouse&meper; as addris/ wi&thorn;outen for&thorn;e&meper; as scheep/ wi&thorn;ynne for&thorn;e|as raueisching wolues/ &THORN;ei wole be iugis&meper; wi&thorn;outen autorite/ &amp; at|&thorn;e laste&meper; false accusars &amp; wanting al vertu/ and &thorn;erfore &thorn;e wise|man sei&thorn;.  Prou. | vi<SUP>o</SUP>.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Prov. vi. 19.</NOTE>  &thorn;at &thorn;e Lord bo&thorn;e hati&thorn; &amp; wlati&thorn; him&meper; <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="104a">|&thorn;at sowi&thorn; discorde among nei&yogh;bours/ &thorn;ise ypocritis wole suffre no|darte&meper; of correccioun to &thorn;rille hem/ but in iche synne &thorn;at &thorn;ei done&meper;|&thorn;ei leien for&thorn;e &thorn;e bockelere of proude defence/ and whanne ony of|hem&meper; is blamed for his wickidnes/ he wil not &thorn;anne anoon&meper; &thorn;enk|hou he mai amende it/ but he seeki&thorn; bisili helpe&meper; hou he mai|defende it/ Hec Gregorius. li<SUP>o</SUP>. xxx.</P></DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="commandment" N="8">
<HEAD>&THORN;e .VIII. heeste &Verbar;</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;e ei&yogh;ti&thorn; comaundement of God is &thorn;is. Exo. xx<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Non loqueris|contra proximum tuum falsum testimonium'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ex. xx. 16.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;ou schalt not|speke fals witnes a&yogh;ens &thorn;i nei&yogh;bour/ Nei&thorn;ir for &yogh;iftis taking/|Nei&thorn;ir for mannes stering/ Nei&thorn;ir &thorn;i silf in synne excusing &Verbar;</P>
<P>Of &thorn;e firste it is writen . Isa. v<SUP>o</SUP>.  'Ve qui iustificatis impium|pro muneribus&meper; &amp; iusticiam iusti aufertis ab eo'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Isaias v. 23.</NOTE> &Verbar; woo to &yogh;ou &thorn;at|iustifien&meper; &thorn;e wickid man for &yogh;iftis/ &amp; take awey &thorn;e ri&yogh;twisenes of|&thorn;e iust man&meper; for he mai not paye<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Wo that iustefien the unpitous for &yogh;iftes, and the ri&yogh;twisnesse of|the ri&yogh;twyse &yogh;ee taken awey fro hym.'  1388, '&yogh;e iustifien a wickid man for|&yogh;iftis, and &yogh;e taken awei the ri&yogh;tfulnesse of a iust man fro hym.</NOTE> &Verbar;<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="104b"></P>
<P>
<PB N="112">Of &thorn;e secounde speki&thorn; &thorn;e wise | man&meper; Prou. xix<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Falsus testis|non erit inpunitus&meper; et qui mendacia loquitur peribit'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Prov. xix. 5 'Testis falsus non erit impunitus, et qui mendacia|loquitur non effugiet.'</NOTE> &Verbar;  A false|witnesberer&meper; schal not be vnpunyschid/ &amp; he &thorn;at speki&thorn; liees&meper;|schal perische<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'A fals witnesse shal not ben unpunshid; and he that lesing|speketh, shal not ascapen.'</NOTE>/ Ps. v<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Perdes omnes qui locuntur mendacium'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ps. v. 6.</NOTE>/|Lord &thorn;ou schalt leese alle &thorn;oo. &thorn;at speken lesing/ for &thorn;e wise man|sei&thorn;.  Sap. i<SUP>o</SUP>.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Sap. i. 11.</NOTE>  &THORN;e mou&thorn;e &thorn;at lie&thorn;&meper; slee&thorn; &thorn;e soule/ and &thorn;erfor|sei&thorn; Crist. Ion. viii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'vos ex patre diabolo estis &amp;c'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Joh. viii. 44.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;at is to|seie. &yogh;e liears&meper; ben sones of &yogh;oure fadir &thorn;e deuel/ &amp; &yogh;e wil do &thorn;e|desiris of &yogh;oure fadir/ He was a mansleer fro &thorn;e bigynnyng&meper; for|he stood not in trou&thorn;e. for trou&thorn;e is not in him/ whanne he speki&thorn;|lesing&meper; he speki&thorn; of his owene autorite/ for he is a lier&meper; &amp; &thorn;e fadir|of lesing<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. '&yogh;e ben of the fadir, the deuel, and &yogh;e wolen do the desyris of|&yogh;oure fadir.  He was a mansleere fro the bigynnyng, and in treuthe he stood|not; for treuthe is not in him.  Whanne he spekith a lesinge he spekith of|his owne thingis; for he is a lyiere, and fadir of it.'</NOTE>/</P>
<P>Of &thorn;e &thorn;ridde speki&thorn; &thorn;e prophete Ps. cxl. 'Pone domine custodiam|ori meo &amp;c'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ps. cxl. 3 (A. V. Ps. cxli. 3).</NOTE> &Verbar;  Lord putt &thorn;ou warde to my mou&thorn;e&meper; &amp; a dore of|circumstaunce to my lippis/ bowe &thorn;ou not my herte&meper; in to &thorn;e|wordis of malice&meper; to excusaciouns to be excusid in synne<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Put, Lord, warde to my mouth; and a dore of circumstaunce to|my lippis.  Bowe thou not doun my herte into the woordis of malice; to ben|excusid excusaciouns in synnes.'  1388, 'Lord, sette thou a keping to my|mouth; and a dore of stonding aboute to my lippis.  Bowe thou not myn|herte in to wordis of malice; to excuse excusing is in synne.'</NOTE>/ for &thorn;e|wise man sei&thorn;. Prou. ii. 'Qui letantur cum male fecerint &amp; exultent<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="105a">| in rebus pessimis puniantur'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Prov. ii. 14 'Qui laetantur cum malefecerint, et exultant in rebus|pessimis.'</NOTE>/  &THORN;at is to | seie. &THORN;ei &thorn;at|maken myry&meper; whanne &thorn;ei han done yuel/ &amp; ioyen in werst &thorn;ingis&meper;|be &thorn;ei punyschid wi&thorn; eendles peyne<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Thei hat gladen, whan thei don euele, and ful out io&yogh;en in werst|thingus.'  1388, 'Whiche ben glad, whanne thei han do yuel, and maken ful|out ioye in worste things.'</NOTE> &Verbar;</P>
<P>A&yogh;en &thorn;is comaundement&meper; &thorn;e fende wi&thorn; hise cautels/ ha&thorn;|&yogh;ouun leue to .XII. men&meper; for twelue grootis/ to passe for&thorn;e on a|quest&meper; a&yogh;en a ri&yogh;twise blood/ &amp; seie a false witnesse&meper; &thorn;at &thorn;e man
<PB N="113">|is gilti/ &amp; anoon he schal be deed&meper; &thorn;ou&yogh; it were Crist him silf &Verbar; In|&thorn;is &thorn;e fendis membris&meper; grounden hem on Iesabel/ III Re. xxi<SUP>o</SUP>.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. 3 Reg. xxi. 8-11.</NOTE> for|sche sent lettris&meper; in &thorn;e name of Acab/ aseelid wi&thorn; his synet&meper; to|iourours of &thorn;e countre/ &amp; chargid hem &thorn;at &thorn;ei schulde cheese&meper;|twoo men of Belial sones/ &thorn;at my&yogh;t seie fals witnes&meper; a&yogh;en &thorn;e|kny&yogh;t Naboth/ &thorn;at he hadde waried&meper; bo&thorn;e God &amp; &thorn;e kyng/ and|by &thorn;is false witnesse&meper; &thorn;ei slowen &thorn;is giltles kny&yogh;t &Verbar;  Certis so in|oure daies&meper; who &thorn;at medi&thorn; &thorn;ise iullars/ &thorn;at ben &thorn;e sones of Belial&meper;|&amp; fals questmongars/ he may slee &amp; he may saue&meper; &thorn;us fals were|neuer &thorn;e Iewis &Verbar;  For whanne tweie oolde prestis&meper; &thorn;at brenned in|leccherie/ of &thorn;e womman Susan&meper; as &thorn;e story telli&thorn;/ | Daniel. <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="105b">|xiii<SUP>o</SUP>.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Dan. xiii. 1-63.</NOTE>/ And sche wolde not consent&meper; to do her foule lust/ &thorn;anne|&thorn;ei &yogh;ouun a sentence&meper; of her fals witnesse/ wherbi sche was iugid&meper;|wor&thorn;i to &thorn;e deed/ As sche was ledde to &thorn;e fire&meper; sche made hir|deuoute preiere/ and &thorn;anne God rerid vp&meper; &thorn;e herte of a &yogh;ong|man/ &thorn;at was clepid Daniel&meper; &amp; he reuokid her doom/ and repreued|&thorn;ise oolde prestis&meper; of her false witnes/ so &thorn;at Goddis aungel&meper; wi&thorn;|a scharp swerid/ slow&yogh;e hem for her false doome&meper; in si&yogh;t of alle &thorn;e|peple/ and &thorn;ei preised God almy&yogh;ti&meper; of &thorn;is faire delyueraunce &Verbar;|How schulde &yogh;e iourours&meper; scape &thorn;e fire of helle&meper; &thorn;at for a litil|money&meper; wole dampne &yogh;e