<P>&yogh;it may we se more cumberaunce&meper; of &thorn;e fendis worchynge/ for|&thorn;er is noon officere&meper; temperal ne spirituel/ &thorn;an he is redi whanne|he may&meper; for to take &yogh;iftis/ of &thorn;e pore comunes&meper; &amp; pille hem euer|anoon/ &amp; ellis &thorn;ei schal no pees haue&meper; from greuousear oppressyng&meper;|as is takyng of her beestis&meper; wi&thorn; corn &amp; o&thorn;ir vitails/ and o&thorn;ir|payment gete &thorn;ei noon&meper; but a whit stik / til &thorn;ei haue loost half on|half&meper; wi&thorn; myche more traueile &Verbar;  Lord! if &thorn;at &yogh;e markid wel&meper;|what Ietro seide to Moyses/ Exo. xviii<SUP>o</SUP>.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ex. xviii. 13-26.</NOTE> soone &yogh;e schulde amende|&thorn;is mys&meper; or ellis &yogh;e ben vncurable &Verbar;  Ietro counseyled Moyses&meper;|&thorn;at he schulde wiseli ordeyne/ mi&yogh;ti men &thorn;at dredden God&meper; in
<PB N="114">|whom was verry trou&thorn;e/ &amp; &thorn;at hatid auarice&meper; wi&thorn; alle hir cursid|braunchis/ &amp; &thorn;ei schulde haue office&meper; in rulyng vndir Moises/|Moyses consentid&meper; &amp; wrou&yogh;t aftir his counseile/ &thorn;erfore pees.|wel&thorn;e. &amp; grace regned in hise daies &Verbar;  Rere vp &yogh;oure wittis &yogh;e|princis&meper; &amp; lordis in &thorn;is world/ &amp; se hou king Iosaphat&meper; chargid<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="106b">| to hise officeris/ II. Para. xix<SUP>o</SUP>. | 'Constituitque iudices terre in|cunctis ciuitatibus iuda precipiens eis.  videte ait quid faciatis/|Non enim hominis exercetis iudicium sed domini.  Et quodcumque|iudicaueritis in vos redundabit/ Sit timor domini vobiscum&meper; &|cum diligencia cuncta facite/ Non est enim apud dominum nostrum|iniquitas. nec personarum accepcio. nec cupido munerum'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. II. Para. xix. 5-7.</NOTE>/ &THORN;at is|to seie. Iosophat ordeyned iugis&meper; in alle &thorn;e citees of Iurie/ &|&yogh;aue hem &thorn;is bidding/ Be war he sei&thorn; what &yogh;e do/ forso&thorn;e &thorn;is|doome &thorn;at &yogh;e haunten. is not &thorn;e doome of man&meper; but &thorn;e doom of|God/ &amp; what &thorn;at &yogh;e demen&meper; schal turne vpon &yogh;oure silf/ loke &thorn;e|drede of God be among &yogh;ou&meper; &amp; doi&thorn; alle &thorn;ingis wi&thorn; diligence/|forso&thorn;e anenst &thorn;e Lord God&meper; is no wickidnes/ nei&thorn;ir accepting of|persoones&meper; nei&thorn;ir coueitise of &yogh;iftis/ and he chargid prestis &|dekenes&meper; &thorn;at &thorn;ei schulde make knowen/ alle &thorn;e dou&yogh;tis of &thorn;e|lawe&meper; leste &thorn;e peple synned<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'And he sette domesmen of the lond in alle the strengthed citees|of Juda, by alle placis.  And comaundyng to the iugis, Seeith, he seith, what|&yogh;e done; forsothe &yogh;e enhaunten not dome of man, bot of the Lord; and what|euer &yogh;e shul demyn in to &yogh;ou it schal redoundyn; be the drede of the Lord|with &yogh;ou, and with diligence alle thingus doith; forsothe ther is not anentis|the Lord oure God wickidnesse, ne acceptynge of persones, ne couetise of &yogh;iftis.|And Josaphath in Jerusalem sette Leuytis, and prestis, and princes of the|meynees of Yrael, that dome and the cause of the Lord thei schulden deemyn|to the dwellers of it.'  1388, 'And he ordeynede iugis of the lond in alle the|strengthid citees of Judia, bi ech place.  And he comaundide to the iugis, and|seide. Se &yogh;e, what &yogh;e doen; for &yogh;e usen not the doom of man, but of the Lord;|and what euere thing &yogh;e demen, schal turne in to &yogh;ou; the drede of the Lord|be with you, and do &yogh;e alle thingis with diligence: for anentis &yogh;oure Lord God|is no wickidnesse, nether takynge of persoones nether coueitise of &yogh;iftis.  Also|in Jerusalem Josaphat ordeynede dekenes, preestis, and the princes of meynees|of Israel, that thei schulden deme the doom &amp; cause of the Lord to the|dwellers of it.'</NOTE> &Verbar;  If &thorn;is loore were wel lerned&meper; of|oure cristen lordis/ &thorn;e harde boondis of anticrist&meper; schulde be|altobrosten/ Cristen peple schulde haue leue&meper; to do her office<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="107a">| treweli/ &amp; iche a man his freedam&meper; to serue God in vertu/ | &THORN;anne|were &thorn;is good gouerneaunce&meper; &amp; sauyng of &thorn;e rewme/ In pees. in
<PB N="115">|wel&thorn;e. in euery astate&meper; as prestis. kny&yogh;tis &amp; comunes/ for &thorn;us sei&thorn;|Crisostom. om. I./ 'Notandum quod quicumque regum placuerunt|deo diucius regnauerunt &amp; prosperati sunt/ &amp; inimicos eorum|humiliauit deus sub eis/ Quotquot autem maligne gesserunt velociter|&amp; a regno &amp; a uita cum amara morte percisi sunt &amp; humiliauit|eos deus sub inimicis eorum'<NOTE PLACE="foot">S. Ioan. Chrysostomus, <I>Homilia I (Opera</I>, ed. 1547, tom. ii, col. 721).</NOTE> &Verbar; &THORN;at is to seie. It is to noote &thorn;at|who of kyngis han plesid God&meper; &thorn;ei han regned &thorn;e lenger/ &amp; &thorn;ei|han ben wel&thorn;i. &amp; God ha&thorn; lowid her enemyes vndir hem/ Forso&thorn;e|als many as han don wickidli&meper; &thorn;ei han ben kitt vp hastili/ bo&thorn;e|from her rewme &amp; from her lijf&meper; wi&thorn; a bittir dee&thorn;/ &amp; God ha&thorn;|lowid hem&meper; vndir her enemyes &thorn;raldom &Verbar;</P></DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="commandment" N="9">
<HEAD>&THORN;e nyn&thorn;e heeste &Verbar;</HEAD>
<P>The nyn&thorn;e comaundement of God is &thorn;is. Exo. xx<SUP>o</SUP>. Deuto. v<SUP>o</SUP>.|'Non concupisces domum proximi tui'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ex. xx. 17.</NOTE>/ &THORN;ou schalt not coueite &thorn;e|hous of &thorn;i neibour &Verbar;  In &thorn;e seuen&thorn;e heest God forbedi&thorn;&meper; &thorn;e vnleful|takyng of o&thorn;ir mennes goodis/ &amp; so in &thorn;at he refreyne&thorn;&meper; &thorn;e vnskilfulnes|of mannes dede/ |  But in &thorn;is heest God forbedi&thorn;&meper; &thorn;e <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="107b">|coueitise of vnleful taking/ &amp; in &thorn;at he refreyne&thorn;&meper; &thorn;e vnordinat|appetite of mannes desire/ namli in alle &thorn;o &thorn;ingis&meper; &thorn;at ben|vnmoveable/ &thorn;at is to seie. &thorn;at moun not move hem silf&meper; bi her|owene my&yogh;t from oo place to ano&thorn;ir/ as ben hous. lond. gold. &|suche o&thorn;ir like to &thorn;ise &Verbar;</P>
<P>And &thorn;is viciouse coueitise&meper; if it be conteyned/ growi&thorn; to dee&thorn;|of &thorn;e soule&meper; from &thorn;e roote of mannes herte/ for whanne &thorn;e wille|ha&thorn; consentid&meper; to do &thorn;at &thorn;ing &thorn;at God forbedi&thorn;/ &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;e dede|folowe not aftir&meper; in outward si&yogh;t of mannes doome/ &amp; no &thorn;ing|letti&thorn; to do &thorn;e dede&meper; saue wille mai not as it wolde/ &thorn;anne &thorn;e|soule is deed goostli&meper; wi&thorn;ynne &thorn;e hous of &thorn;e bodi/ And &thorn;is dee&thorn;|is signified&meper; bi a persoones dou&yogh;tir/ &thorn;at was deed wi&thorn;ynne hir|fadris hous&meper; &amp; Crist bi myracle &yogh;aue hir lijf/ Mat. ix<SUP>o</SUP>./ Mar. v<SUP>o</SUP>.|Luk. viii<SUP>o</SUP>.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. ix. 18-26; Marc. v. 22-43; Luc. viii. 41-56.</NOTE></P>
<P>Summe norischen her coueitise&meper; til it spring vnto a dede/ as a|careyn opunly deed&meper; &thorn;at lie&thorn; bi &thorn;e weye enfecting &thorn;e peple/ and|&thorn;is is tau&yogh;t in &thorn;e widouse sone&meper; &thorn;at was born deed on a beere/
<PB N="116"><MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="108a"> wi&thorn;outen &thorn;e &yogh;atis of &thorn;e | citee&meper; for to putt him in his graue/|Luk. vii<SUP>o</SUP><NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Luc. vii. 11-15.</NOTE>/ Crist rerid him bi his myracle&meper; &amp; &yogh;aue him a&yogh;en to his|modir &Verbar;</P>
<P>Summe feeden her foule coueitise&meper; wi&thorn; lust &amp; lykyng &amp; delectacioun/|in &thorn;ou&yogh;t. in worde. &amp; in werke&meper; &amp; &thorn;is is moost abhomynable/|for it was schewid in Lazarus/ Ion. xi<SUP>o</SUP>.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Joh. xi. 1-46.</NOTE> &thorn;at lay deed foure|daies in his graue/ &amp; Crist bi miracle to turne &thorn;e Iewis&meper; rerid vp|his bodi &amp; &yogh;aue it &thorn;e spirit &Verbar;</P>
<P>Alle &thorn;ise &thorn;re ben a&yogh;enst &thorn;is heest of God/ &amp; ben wor&thorn;i eendles|peyne&meper; but if God &thorn;oru&yogh; his graciouse mercy/ move hem to vertu|&amp; to verry penaunce&meper; &thorn;at ben deed in &thorn;ise forseid foule coueitises/|&THORN;at is to seie. in coueitise of herte&meper; of dede. &amp; of custum/ and|&thorn;erfore &thorn;e wise man. Ecc. xviii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Post concupiscencias tuas non|eas'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ecclesiasticus xviii. 30.</NOTE>/ Go &thorn;ou not awey fro &thorn;i God&meper; aftir &thorn;in owene couetises<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'After thi lustis go thou not.' 1388, 'Go thou not aftir thi|coueitises.'</NOTE> &Verbar;|Lord hou schulde he kepe him from a viciouse dede&meper; &thorn;at doi&thorn; not|out of his herte. &thorn;e coueitise &thorn;erof? Certis it is as vnposible&meper; as to|saue &thorn;at hous from brennyng/ &thorn;at &thorn;ou settist on fire&meper; wi&thorn; &thorn;in<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="108b">| owene handis &Verbar;  A weede may not be distried&meper; but | if &thorn;at|delictable coueitise of synne. be pullid out of &thorn;e herte/ for if &thorn;ere|abide ony part of &thorn;is foule couetise&meper; vndrawen vp in &thorn;e herte/|anoon aftir come&thorn; &thorn;erof. &thorn;eeft. false purchase&meper; &amp; suche o&thorn;ir/ and|&thorn;erfor seide Moyses&meper; vnto &thorn;e children of Israel/ Deuto. xix<SUP>o</SUP>./|'Non assumes &amp; transferes terminos proximi tui quos fixerunt|priores tui in possessione tua quam dominus deus tuus dabit tibi'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Deut. xix. 14.</NOTE> &Verbar;|&THORN;at is to seie. &thorn;ou schalt not take. ne &thorn;ou schalt not passe &thorn;e termes|or &thorn;e boundes of &thorn;i nei&yogh;bore&meper; &thorn;e whiche &thorn;in elderis han sett/ in &thorn;e|whiche possessioun&meper; &thorn;at &thorn;e Lord &thorn;i God schal &yogh;yue to &thorn;ee<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Thou shalt not take, and ouerbere the teermes of thi nei&yogh;bour,|the whiche han maad rather men in thi possessioun, that the Lord thi God|shal &yogh;yue to thee.'  1388, 'Thou schalt not take, and turne over the termes of|thi nei&yogh;bore, which the formere men settiden in thi possessioun, which thi|Lord God schal &yogh;yue to thee.'</NOTE>/ For|who &thorn;at taki&thorn; awey his nei&yogh;boris grounde&meper; &thorn;at is to seie. lond or|place. wood or watir. corn or grasse. in felde or in toune. &thorn;oru&yogh; ony|of &thorn;ise forseide couetises&meper; he stondi&thorn; in &thorn;at acursid of God &amp; his
