<P>The ten&thorn;e comaundement of God is &thorn;is. Exo. xx<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Non desiderabis|vxorem proximi tui. non seruum. non ancillam. non bouem.|non azinum. nec omnia que illius sunt'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ex. xx. 17.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;ou schalt not desire|&thorn;i nei&yogh;bores wijf. ne his seruaunt. ne his handmayde. ne his oxe.|ne his asse. ne no &thorn;ingis &thorn;at ben hise&meper; o&thorn;irwise &thorn;an &thorn;ou wilt he|coueite &thorn;in. aftir resoun &amp; &thorn;e lawe | of Cristis gospel &Verbar;  In &thorn;e <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="113b">|sixte comaundement&meper; God forbedi&thorn; &thorn;e outwarde dede of leccherie/|&amp; in &thorn;at he refreyne&thorn;&meper; &thorn;e vnleful treeting of &thorn;e bodi/ but in &thorn;is|he forbedi&thorn;&meper; &thorn;e inwarde consent of &thorn;e herte/ &amp; in &thorn;at he refreyne&thorn;&meper;|al vnleful desire or wille/ nameli in &thorn;o &thorn;ingis&meper; &thorn;at ben|moveable/ &THORN;at is to seie. &thorn;at han my&yogh;t in hem silf&meper; to remeve fro|oo place to ano&thorn;ir/ for desire &amp; wille &thorn;at resti&thorn; in &thorn;e inward man&meper;|make&thorn; merite or synne more or lesse. in &thorn;e presence of God/ for|charitable werkis. &thorn;at ben in her owene kynde. my&yogh;ti &amp; greet&meper;|ben don sumtyme wi&thorn; a frowarde wille. &amp; &thorn;anne &thorn;ei wanten mede/|as Crist sei&thorn; in his gospel. Mat. vii<SUP>o</SUP>/ 'Non omnis qui dicit mihi|domine domine intrabit in regnum celorum sed qui facit voluntatem|patris mei qui in celis est. ipse intrabit in regnum celorum'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. vii. 21.</NOTE> &Verbar;|&THORN;at is to seie. Not iche man &thorn;at sei&thorn; to me. Lord Lord&meper; schal
