<HEAD>What is &thorn;e fendis chirche&meper; wi&thorn; hir propurtees/</HEAD>
<HEAD>Capitulum .XIII<SUP>m</SUP>.. &Verbar; |</HEAD>
<P>To speke of &thorn;e &thorn;ridde chirche&meper; enproprid to &thorn;e deuel/ &thorn;e <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="119b">|whiche is &thorn;e noumbre&meper; of hem &thorn;at ben encombrid/ to serue him|aftir his tising&meper; a&yogh;en Goddis heestis &Verbar;  Firste we schullen take|oure grounde&meper; in wordis of &thorn;e prophete/ Ps. xxv. 'Odiui ecclesiam|malingnancium'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ps. xxv. 5.</NOTE> &Verbar; I haue haatid &thorn;e chirche of maliciouse lyuars<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'I hatide the chirche of wariende men.'  1388, 'I hatide the|chirche of yuele men.'</NOTE> &Verbar;|&THORN;ise ben &thorn;oo &thorn;at straien awey&meper; aftir hir owene desiris/ walkyng|in &thorn;e large weye&meper; &thorn;at ledi&thorn; hem to helle/ nei&thorn;ir &thorn;ei wil be|gouerned&meper; bi lawe ne bi grace/ nei&thorn;ir &thorn;ei wole for drede ne loue&meper;|cese &amp; go fro synne/ bi cause &thorn;is world is ful of lustis&meper; &amp; profri&thorn;|hise louears. a ioye soone passing &Verbar;  But &thorn;ei &thorn;at traueilen aftir|blisse&meper; here &thorn;ei suffren peyne/ &thorn;erfore foolis wi&thorn;outen noumbre&meper;|ioyen wi&thorn; &thorn;is world/ as Crist sei&thorn; in his gospel. Mat. vii<SUP>o</SUP>./
<PB N="128">|'Intrate per angustiam portam. quia lata porta &amp; spaciosa est via|que ducit ad perdicionem et multi sunt qui intrant per eam &Verbar;  O|quam angusta porta est &amp; arta via que ducit ad vitam &amp; pauci<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="120a">| sunt qui inveniunt eam'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. vii. 13, 14.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;at is to seie. | Entre &yogh;e bi &thorn;e strayt|&yogh;ate. for large is &thorn;e &yogh;ate &amp; brood is &thorn;e weye &thorn;at ledi&thorn; to dampnacioun&meper;|&amp; manye &thorn;er ben &thorn;at entren bi it &Verbar;  O, How peynful is &thorn;e|&yogh;ate &amp; how strei&yogh;t is &thorn;e weye &thorn;at ledi&thorn; to &thorn;e lijf&meper; &amp; fewe &thorn;er ben|&thorn;at fynden it<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Entre &yogh;e bi the streyt &yogh;ate; for the gate that ledith to perdicioun,|or dampnacioun, is brode, and the weye large, and ther ben many that entren|bi it.  Hou streyt is the &yogh;ate, and narewe the weye, that ledith to lijf, and|ther fewe that fynden it.'</NOTE>/ for seint Ion sei&thorn;. v<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Mundus totus in maligno|positus est'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. 1 Joh. v. 19.</NOTE>/  Al &thorn;is world. &thorn;at is. alle &thorn;oo men &amp; wymmen &thorn;at|ben ouercomen wi&thorn; &thorn;is world&meper; ben sett in malice.<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Al the world is put in wickid.'  1388, 'Al the world is set in|yuel.'</NOTE> &thorn;at is brennyng|in &thorn;e fire of foule couetise/  For al &thorn;ing &thorn;at is in &thorn;is world. ei&thorn;ir|it is &thorn;e couetise of i&yogh;en. or ellis it is couetise of &thorn;e fleische. or ellis|it is &thorn;e pride of &thorn;is lijf/ and &thorn;erfor &thorn;is chirche is groundid vpon|&thorn;e deuel&meper; in &thorn;e grauel of false couetise/ as Poul sei&thorn;. Thimo. vi<SUP>o</SUP>. &Verbar;|'Radix enim omnium malorum est cupiditas quam quidam appetentes|errauerunt a fide'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. 1 Tim. vi. 10.</NOTE> &Verbar;  Forso&thorn;e &thorn;e roote of alle yuelis is|couetise/ &thorn;e whiche summe desiryng&meper; haue errid from trewe|bileue/ &amp; han ioyned hemsilf&meper; to many sorowis<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Sothly the roote of alle yuels is couetyse, the which sum men|coueitynge, or desyringe, erreden fro the feith, and bisettiden hem with many|sorwis.'</NOTE> &Verbar;</P>
<P>&THORN;e rering vp of &thorn;is chirche&meper; is in glotenye &amp; leccherie/ as &thorn;e<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="120b">| wisman sei&thorn;. rehersing &thorn;e wordis | of hem &thorn;at schal be dampned/|Sap. ii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'vino precioso &amp; vnguento nos impleamus/ &amp; non preteriat|nos flos temporis.  Coronemus nos rosis antequam marescant/|Nullum pratum sit. quod non pertransiat luxuria nostra &Verbar;  Nemo|nostrum exsors sit luxurie nostre vbique relinquamus/ signa leticie'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Sap. ii. 7-9 'Vino pretioso et unguentis,' etc.</NOTE>/|&THORN;at is to seie. &THORN;ise fendis lymes seyn. go we fille vs wi&thorn;|preciouse wyn and an oyntment/ &amp; suffre we not &thorn;e flour of oure|faire beaute&meper; to passe awey from vs/ croune we vs wi&thorn; roosis of|iolite&meper; or &thorn;at &thorn;ei welken awey/ &thorn;er may be no medowe&meper; but if
<PB N="129">|oure leccherie passe &thorn;erbi/  Noon of vs mai be lootles of his|leccherie&meper; euery where leeue we. &thorn;e tookens of oure gladnes<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'With precyous win and oynemens fille wee us; and passe not us|the flour of tyme.  Crowne wee us with roses, er thei welewen; no medwe be,|that oure leccherie passe not thur&yogh;.  Noon of us be withoute lot of oure|leccherie; ouer al lefe wee signes of gladnesse.'</NOTE>/</P>
<P>And &thorn;e hilling of &thorn;is chirche&meper; is pride &amp; hi&yogh;enes of lijf/ as &thorn;e|prophete sei&thorn;. Ps. xxxvi<SUP>o</SUP>. 'vidi impium superexaltatum&meper; &amp; eleuatum|sicut cedros libani'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ps. xxxvi. 35.</NOTE> &Verbar; &thorn;at is to seie. I haue sen &thorn;e vnpitiuouse|&amp; &thorn;e wickid enhaunsid &amp; vplifted as &thorn;e cedre trees of Liban.<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'I sa&yogh; the unpitouse aboue hauncid; and rerid up as cedris of|Liban.'  1388, 'I si&yogh; a wickid man enhaunsid aboue; and reisid up as the|cedris of Liban.'</NOTE>|&amp; &thorn;ei ben &thorn;e hi&yogh;est trees of &thorn;is world/ But as smoke rise&thorn; sodenli.|&amp; soone vanische&thorn; to nou&yogh;t&meper; so &thorn;e proude ben preisid for | a tyme&meper; <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="121a">|&amp; anoon &thorn;ei fallen awey/ &amp; we witen not&meper; where &thorn;ei bicomen &Verbar;</P>
<P>Off &thorn;e bisines and occupacioun. &thorn;at dwellars of &thorn;is chirche vsen&meper;|speki&thorn; &thorn;e prophete. Ps. liiii. 'Die ac nocte circumdabit eam super|muros eius iniquitas &amp; labor in medio eius &amp; iniusticia'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ps. liv. 11, 12.</NOTE>/  &thorn;at is|to seie. Ni&yogh;t &amp; day. wickidnesse schal cumpasse aboute &thorn;is chirche|vpon hir wallis&meper; &amp; traueile in middis of it &amp; vnri&yogh;twisnesse/ &|okir-julling and treccherie&meper; ha&thorn; not stintid in &thorn;e weies of hir<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Dai and ny&yogh;t wickidnesse shal enuyroune it upon the wallis of it;|and travaile in the myddes of it, and unri&yogh;twisnesse.  And ther failede not fro|the stretis of it usure and treccherie.'  1388, 'Bi dai and ny&yogh;t wickidnesse|schal cumpasse it on the wallis therof, and trauel and unri&yogh;fulnesse ben in|the myddis therof.  And usure and gile failide not fro the stretis therof.'</NOTE> &Verbar;|Of &thorn;is chirche wi&thorn; &thorn;is maner of bilding speki&thorn; Crist in his gospel.|Mat. vii<SUP>o</SUP>. Luk. vi<SUP>o</SUP>.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. vii. 26, 27; Luc. vi. 49.</NOTE> 'Omnis qui audit verba mea &amp; non facit ea|similis est viro stulto qui edificauit domum suam super arenam/|pro primo. &amp; descendit pluuia/ pro 2<SUP>o</SUP>.&amp; flauerunt venti/ pro 3<SUP>o</SUP>.|inruerunt in domum illam/ pro. 4<SUP>o</SUP>.&amp; fuit ruina eius magna'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. vii. 26, 27 'Omnis qui audit verba mea haec, et non facit ea,|similis erit viro stulto, qui aedificavit domum suam super arenam; et descendit|pluvia, et venerunt flumina, et flaverunt venti, et irruerunt in domum illam,|et cecidit, et fuit ruina illius magna.'</NOTE>/|&THORN;at is to seie. who &thorn;at heeri&thorn; my wordis &amp; doi&thorn; hem not. schal|bilijke a foltid man &thorn;at ha&thorn; bildid his hous&meper; vpon &thorn;e grauel of|coueitise &amp; mysbileue/ &amp; reyne of glotenye &amp; leccherie&meper; cam doun
<PB N="130"><MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="121b"> on &thorn;is chirche/ and &thorn;e wyndis of pride&meper; blewen vpon | &thorn;is chirche/|and feersli &thorn;ise forseid synnes fellen in to &thorn;is chirche&meper; &amp; dryuen|it doun/ &amp; &thorn;e fal of hir was greet/ for sche fel from grace &amp; glorie&meper;|to peyne &amp; myschef wi&thorn;outen eend/ as seint Austin sei&thorn; &Verbar; 'Non|enim corpus domini est quod cum illo non erit in eternum quia|ypocrite non cum illo dicendi sunt quamuis in eius vidiantur esse|ecclesia/  Est enim diabolus caput impiorum qui sunt eius quodammodo|corpus ituri cum illo in supplicium ignis eterni'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Augustinus, <I>De Doctrina Christiana</I>, Liber III, cap. xxxvii (Migne, tom.|34, cols. 82, 88).</NOTE>&Verbar;  &THORN;at|is to seie. Forso&thorn;e &thorn;at is not &thorn;e bodi of &thorn;e Lord&meper; &thorn;at schal not be|wi&thorn; him wi&thorn;outen eend/ for ypocritis ben not seid to be wi&thorn;|him&meper; &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;ei be seyn to be in his chirche/  Certis &thorn;e deuel is|heed of alle &thorn;e wickid&meper; &thorn;e whiche ben on sum maner his bodi/ to|goo wi&thorn; him&meper; in to &thorn;e turment of euerlasting fier &Verbar;  For whanne|&thorn;ei tooken baptem&meper; &thorn;ei hi&yogh;ten fei&thorn; &amp; trou&thorn;e/ to kepe Goddis|heestis&meper; as &thorn;e prophete sei&thorn;/ spekyng in &thorn;e persoone&meper; of al &thorn;e|general chirche/ Ps. cxviii &Verbar; 'Iuraui &amp; statui custodire iudicia|iustitie tue'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Ps. cxviii. 106.</NOTE>/  Lord I haue sworn &amp; ordeyned&meper; to kepe &thorn;y|comaundementis<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'I swoor and sette to kepe the domes of thi ri&yogh;twisnesse.'  1388.|'I swoor, and purposide stidefastli; to kepe the domes of thi ri&yogh;tfulnesse.'</NOTE>/ and vpon &thorn;is couenaunt&meper; Crist tooke hem to<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="122a">| his mariage/ wi&thorn; &thorn;e ryng | of stedfast fei&thorn;&meper; he sacrid &thorn;is holi|spousaile/  But now &thorn;ei leeue &thorn;is chast loue&meper; oure Lord Iesu|Crist/ in breking of &thorn;is couenaunt&meper; &amp; han chosen an hoore|maister/ &thorn;e fend &thorn;at is a spouse-breker &amp; ligi&thorn; in avowtrie&meper; wi&thorn;|her sijke soules/ for seint Ion Crisostom sei&thorn;.  'Omnis autem|anima aut est sponsa Christi aut diaboli adultera est'/  Hec|Crisostomus om. xlix. Forso&thorn;e euery soule. ei&thorn;ir it is Cristis|spouse&meper; or ellis it is avowtresse of &thorn;e deuel/ for Crist &amp; &thorn;e deuel|may in no wise rest togidir&meper; in &thorn;e bedde of mannes soule/ for &thorn;ei|ben so contrarie. &thorn;at what euer &thorn;e toon biddi&thorn;&meper; &thorn;e to&thorn;ir forbedi&thorn; &Verbar;|Crist seki&thorn; saluacioun&meper; &thorn;e fende dampnacioun &Verbar;  Crist loue&thorn;|vertu&meper; &thorn;e fende loue&thorn; synne &Verbar;  Crist gadri&thorn; togiddir&meper; &thorn;e fende|scatiri&thorn; abrood &Verbar; as Poul sei&thorn;. II. Cor. vi<SUP>o</SUP>./ 'Que enim participacio|iustitie cum iniquitate? aut<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. ad.</NOTE> que societas lucis ad tenebras &Verbar;|Que autem comunicacio Christi ad Belial? aut que pars fidelis cum
<PB N="131">|infideli &Verbar;  Quis autem consensus templi dei cum ydolis'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. 2 Cor. vi. 14-16 'Quae enim participatio ... quae autem conventio|Christi ad Belial aut quae pars fideli cum infideli?  Qui autem consensus|templo Dei cum idolis?'</NOTE>&Verbar; &THORN;at is|to seie. what participacioun of ri&yogh;twise-|-nesse wi&thorn; wickidnesse? <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="122b">|what felaschip is of li&yogh;t to dercknesse? what comunicacioun of|Crist to Belial? or what part is of a fei&thorn;ful man. to an vnfei&thorn;ful|man? or what consent of &thorn;e temple of God to ydols?<NOTE PLACE="foot">W. V. 'Sothli what partynge, or comunynge, of ri&yogh;twysnesse with|wickidnesse? or what felowschip of li&yogh;t to derknessis? sothli what acordinge|of Crist to Belial? or what part of a feithful or cristen man, with unfeithful,|or hethene? but what consent to the temple of God with ydols? 1388, '...|and what consent to the temple of God with mawmetis?'</NOTE> certis noon&meper;|for iche of &thorn;ise a&yogh;enseyn o&thorn;ir. aftir her owene worching &Verbar;</P>
<P>Now schullen we telle what &thorn;ei be&meper; &thorn;at dwellen wi&thorn; &thorn;e fende/|for to serue him in his chirche&meper; &thorn;at is &thorn;e temple of ydols &Verbar; warars.|cursars. schidars. sclaundirars &amp; blasfemars/ for Poul sei&thorn;. I. Cor.|vi<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Neque malidici regnum dei possidebunt'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. 1 Cor. vi. 10.</NOTE>/ &THORN;ere ben vilen|spekars. liears. glosears. bacbitears. motrars. swerars. &amp; forswerars.|as seint Ion sei&thorn;. Ap. xxi<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Omnibus mendacibus pars illorum|erit in stagno<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. stang<SUP>o</SUP>.</NOTE> ardenti igne &amp; sulphure quod est mors secunda'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Apoc. xxi. 8.</NOTE>/|&THORN;ere ben michars. robbars. and extorcioneris. tyrauntis. &amp; oppressours.|for &thorn;e prophete sei&thorn;. Zac. v<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Omnis fur sicut ibi scriptum|est iudicabitur'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Zach. v. 3.</NOTE>&Verbar;  &THORN;ere ben vntrewe tilliars. vnfei&thorn;ful seruantis.|recheles hired men. &amp; reble disciplis. &amp; vnprofitable labureris | For <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="123a">|Crist sei&thorn;.  Mat. xxv<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Seruum invtilem pericite in tenebras|exteriores'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. xxv. 30 'Inutilem servum eiicite in tenebras exteriores.'</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;ere ben lecchours. fornicareris. avowtreris. incestours.|&thorn;at is defoulears of her owene kyn. &amp; alle vnclene men &|wymmen &thorn;at ben wi&thorn;ynne ordir or professioun/ for seint Ion sei&thorn;.|Ap. vltimo. 'Foris canes &amp; venifici &amp; impudici &amp; homicide &amp; ydolis|seruientes. &amp; omnis qui amat &amp; facit mendacium'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Apoc. xxii. 15.</NOTE>/  &THORN;ere ben|ypocritis. sodomitis. sacrilegers, &amp; sellars of sacramentis &Verbar; for|Crist sei&thorn;. Mat. xxiiii<SUP>o</SUP>. &amp; Luk. xii<SUP>o</SUP>.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Matt. xxiv. 51; Luc. xii. 46.</NOTE>/ 'Diuidet eum partemque|eius ponet cum ypocritis ibi erit fletus &amp; stridor dencium' &Verbar;  &THORN;ere|ben alle &thorn;at preien. seruen or &yogh;yuen &yogh;iftis for chirche or spiritual
<PB N="132">|benefice. alle false possessioneris. alle my&yogh;ti wilful mendineris. &|alle her sturdi maynteners/ for seint Iude sei&thorn;. i<SUP>o</SUP>. ca<SUP>o</SUP>../ 'Ve qui|in via caym abierunt. pro primo. et in errore Balaam mercede|effusi sunt. pro secundo. &amp; in contradiccione chore perierunt.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Jude i. 11.</NOTE> pro|tertio'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Jude i. 11.</NOTE>/ 'Ve' secundum magistrum historiarum notat eternam<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. eterna.</NOTE>|dampnacionem/ &THORN;ere ben &thorn;oo men &thorn;at boosen her bristis. pinchin<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="123b">| her belies. parten her hosis. cracowen | her schoos. &amp; alle disgisears|of garmentis/ for God sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e prophete Sopho. i<SUP>o</SUP>. ca<SUP>o</SUP>../ 'visitabo|super omnes qui induti sunt veste peregrina'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Sophon. i. 8.</NOTE>&Verbar;  &THORN;ere ben &thorn;oo.|&thorn;at steerchen or poppen her facis. &thorn;at bridilen her heedis wi&thorn;|gigge haltiris. &thorn;at setten aboue honycombis.  wi&thorn; miche o&thorn;ir|tatiryng. to make hemsilf salle-kene to synne &amp; setten abrood her|pappis to cacche men wi&thorn; her lym&yogh;erdes/ for God sei&thorn; bi &thorn;e|prophete. Ysa. iii<SUP>o</SUP>. 'Pro eo quod eleuate sunt filie syon et ambulauerunt|collo extento. &amp;c.;/ decaluabit dominus verticem filiarum|syon'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Isaias iii. 16, 17.</NOTE> &Verbar;  &THORN;er ben false lawe makars. Goddis lawe haatars. fyndars|of custumes. distriears of vertues. autours of synnes &Verbar; for Poul sei&thorn;.|Rom. ii<SUP>o</SUP>./ 'In quo enim iudicas alterum te ipsum contempnas'<NOTE PLACE="foot">Vulg. Rom. ii. 1.</NOTE> &Verbar;|In &thorn;is chirche ben mawmetrers. heretikis. ydolatreris. sortilogeris.|enchauntours. arioleris. charmours. &amp; rerars of &thorn;e deuel. &amp; alle &thorn;oo|&thorn;at trowen &thorn;at hel&thorn;e may cum. of vsing Goddis word. &thorn;at we<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="124a">| clepen 